(51, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of A Microorganism In Action As A Disease Vector?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Fungi decomposing dead plant material', 'Mosquito transmitting malaria', 'Bacteria causing food poisoning', 'Algae producing oxygen through photosynthesis', '', ' B Explanation A disease vector is an organism that transmits disease-causing pathogens from one host to another. Female Anopheles mosquitoes can carry and transmit the Plasmodium parasite, which causes malaria. When an infected mosquito bites a person, i', 1, '2024-02-08 08:15:53'),
(52, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Characteristic Of Cells Related To Irritability?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ability to respond to stimuli ', 'Ability To Synthesize Proteins', 'Ability To Generate Energy ', 'Ability To Replicate DNA', '', 'A Explanation Irritability, also known as responsiveness or excitability, refers to the ability of cells to detect and respond to various stimuli or changes in their environment.', 1, '2024-02-08 08:17:57'),
(53, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Membrane Around The Vacuole Is Known As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Elaioplast ', 'Amyloplast ', 'Tonoplast ', 'Cytoplast', '', ' C Explanation The membrane around the vacuole is known as Tonoplast. The tonoplast is the cytoplasmic membrane surrounding a vacuole, separating the vacuolar contents from the cell&apos;s cytoplasm. It is also known as Vacuolar membrane.   ', 1, '2024-02-08 08:21:22'),
(54, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is Evidence Of Evolution?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'All of the above.', 'Similarities in embryonic development', ' Fossils of extinct organisms', 'Homologous structures in different species', '', 'A Explanation All the options provided are evidence of evolution, which supports the idea that species have evolved and changed over time.   ', 1, '2024-02-08 08:25:06'),
(55, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of An Adaptation For Survival In Social Insects?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Migration to warmer climates', 'Production Of Venom For Defense ', 'Formation Of Complex Caste Systems', 'Hibernation During Winter Months', '', 'C Explanation Social insects, such as ants, bees, wasps, and termites, exhibit complex social structures and behaviors that contribute to their survival and success as a colony. ocial insects organize themselves into specialized groups or castes, each wit', 1, '2024-02-08 08:27:30'),
(56, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is NOT A Part Of The Alimentary Canal?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Oesophagus', 'Large Intestine', ' Liver', 'Small Intestine', '', 'C Explanation The alimentary canal, also known as the digestive tract, is a long tube that extends from the mouth to the anus and is responsible for the digestion and absorption of food. The organs that are part of the alimentary canal include the mouth, ', 1, '2024-02-08 08:29:08'),
(57, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Evolutionary Trend Commonly Observed In Organisms?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Decreased complexity over time', 'Increased Dependence On External Resources', 'Increased Genetic Diversity Within Populations', 'Decreased Adaptation To The Environment', '', 'C Explanation Evolutionary trends generally involve changes that occur over time in a population or species. One commonly observed trend is an increase in genetic diversity within populations. Genetic diversity refers to the variety of genetic traits and ', 1, '2024-02-08 08:31:15'),
(58, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Characteristic Feature Of Kingdom Plantae?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Presence of chloroplasts ', 'Ability To Perform Photosynthesis ', 'Lack Of Cell Walls', 'Heterotrophic Mode Of Nutrition', '', 'A Explanation Kingdom Plantae is characterized by the presence of chloroplasts. Chloroplasts are the site of photosynthesis in plant cells, where light energy is converted into chemical energy. This is not to say that all organisms with chloroplasts belon', 1, '2024-02-08 08:33:25'),
(59, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of Physiological Variation In Organisms?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Variation in blood pressure among individuals ', 'Variation In Beak Shape Among Finches ', 'Differences In Fur Color In Rabbits ', 'Variation In Leaf Shape In Plants', '', 'A Explanation Physiological variation refers to differences in physiological traits or functions among individuals within a species. Blood pressure is a physiological parameter that can vary among individuals based on factors such as genetics, health cond', 1, '2024-02-08 08:43:57'),
(60, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Are Components Of The Skeletal System In Humans?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Cartilage and blood vessels ', 'Ligaments And Tendons ', 'Muscles And Nerves ', 'Bones And Joints', '', 'D Explanation The skeletal system in humans is composed of bones and joints. Bones and joints are the primary components of the human skeletal system.', 1, '2024-02-08 08:50:00'),
(61, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Represents An Example Of Ecological Management And Conservation Through A Biological Association?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Construction of a dam for hydroelectric power ', 'Introduction Of An Invasive Species For Pest Control ', 'Clear-Cutting Of A Forest For Timber Extraction ', 'Establishment Of Marine Protected Areas', '', 'D Explanation Ecological management and conservation involve strategies and practices aimed at preserving and protecting natural ecosystems and their biodiversity. Among the options provided, the establishment of marine protected areas is an example of su', 1, '2024-02-08 08:52:37'),
(62, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Term Cell Was Given By&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Robert Hooke ', 'Schwann ', 'De Bary', 'Tatum', '', ' A Explanation The term cell was given by Robert Hooke. The term cell was coined by Robert Hooke. Robert Hooke observed a honeycomb-like structure under the microscope while cutting a thin section of cork, hence he named the structure as a cell.', 1, '2024-02-08 08:54:35'),
(63, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is The Primary Organ Involved In Gas Exchange During Respiration In Humans?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Diaphragm ', 'Bronchi ', 'Lungs ', 'Trachea', '', 'C Explanation The primary organ involved in gas exchange during respiration in humans is the lungs. The lungs are a pair of respiratory organs located in the chest cavity. They are responsible for the exchange of oxygen and carbon dioxide between the air ', 1, '2024-02-08 08:56:20'),
(64, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Gland Is Responsible For Producing The Hormone Insulin?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Thyroid gland ', 'Pituitary Gland ', 'Pancreas ', 'Adrenal Gland', '', 'C Explanation The pancreas is an organ located in the abdomen, and it serves both digestive and endocrine functions. In terms of hormone production, the pancreas is responsible for producing insulin. Insulin plays a crucial role in regulating blood sugar ', 1, '2024-02-08 08:58:26'),
(65, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Most Fishes Do Not Sink In Water Because Of The Presences Of:&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI. Swim Bladder&lt;br /&gt;\r\nII. Air Bladder&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIII. Air Sacs&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIV. Air In Spongy Bones&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'II and III are correct ', 'I And II Are Correct ', 'Â I, II, III And IV Are Correct ', 'III And IV Are Correct', '', 'B Explanation Fishes have a swim bladder or air bladder which helps them to remain buoyant without sinking in water. They are present in the body cavity.   ', 1, '2024-02-08 09:00:52'),
(66, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Monohybrid Inheritance, If An Organism Carries Two Different Alleles For A Particular Gene, It Is Called:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Homozygous ', 'Dominant ', 'Heterozygous ', 'Recessive', '', 'C Explanation In monohybrid inheritance, the inheritance of a single gene is considered. An organism that carries two different alleles for a particular gene is referred to as heterozygous. The alleles may have different versions or variations of the gene', 1, '2024-02-08 09:02:50'),
(67, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Tissue Responsible For Transporting Water And Minerals From The Roots To The Rest Of The Plant?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Xylem ', 'Epidermis ', 'Parenchyma ', 'Phloem', '', 'A Explanation The tissue responsible for transporting water and minerals from the roots to the rest of the plant is called xylem. Xylem is a complex tissue composed of specialized cells, such as tracheids and vessel elements, which form long, interconnect', 1, '2024-02-08 09:05:01'),
(68, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of An Abiotic Ecological Factor?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Temperature', 'Competition ', 'Predation ', 'Symbiosis', '', 'A Explanation Abiotic ecological factors are non-living factors that influence an ecosystem. They include physical and chemical factors such as temperature, sunlight, water availability, soil composition, and air quality', 1, '2024-02-08 09:06:53'),
(69, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Processes Is Involved In The Reproduction Of Developing Organisms?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Budding ', 'Germination ', 'Fertilization ', 'Pollination', '', 'C Explanation Fertilization is the process by which the male and female gametes (reproductive cells) fuse to initiate the development of a new organism.', 1, '2024-02-08 09:08:25'),
(70, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Behavioral Adaptation For Dealing With A Hot Climate Could Include&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Hibernating during the hottest part of the day ', 'Large Scales On The Back Of A Lizard ', 'Feeding During The Hottest Part Of The Day ', 'A Small Kidney To Conserve Water', '', 'A Explanation Estivation: Certain animals enter a state of estivation, which is similar to hibernation but occurs in response to hot and dry conditions. They become inactive, conserve energy, and reduce water loss during the hottest parts of the day or du', 1, '2024-02-08 09:10:31'),
(71, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Natural Place Of An Organism Or Community Is Known As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Niche ', 'Habit ', 'Biome ', 'Habitat', '', 'Option D Explanation The natural place of an organism or community is known as its habitat. A habitat is an ecological or environmental area that is inhabited by a particular species of animal, plant, or other type of organism. It is the natural environme', 1, '2024-02-08 09:13:05'),
(72, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Process In The Nutrient Cycle Converts Atmospheric Nitrogen Into A Form That Plants Can Utilize?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Denitrification', 'Nitrogen Fixation ', 'Ammonification ', 'Nitrification', '', 'B Explanation Nitrogen fixation is the process in the nutrient cycle that converts atmospheric nitrogen (N2) into a form that plants can utilize, typically ammonium (NH4+) or nitrate (NO3-). This process is carried out by nitrogen-fixing bacteria, which c', 1, '2024-02-08 09:14:59'),
(73, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Functions Is Performed By The Skin To Help Maintain Homeostasis In The Human Body?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Regulation of body temperature ', 'Filtration Of Blood ', 'Production Of Hormones ', 'Digestion Of Food', '', 'A Explanation The skin plays a vital role in maintaining homeostasis by regulating body temperature. When the body becomes too hot, the skin helps to cool it down through processes like sweating and vasodilation.', 1, '2024-02-08 09:16:54'),
(74, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Soil Types Becomes Less Fertile Due To The Intense Leaching Caused By Tropical Rains?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Yellow soil ', 'Laterite Soil ', 'Red Soils ', 'Black Soil', '', 'B Explanation Laterite soil becomes less fertile due to intense leaching caused by tropical rains. Leaching is the process by which nutrients are washed out of the soil by rainfall. In the case of laterite soils, which are common in tropical regions, the ', 1, '2024-02-08 09:18:52'),
(75, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Type Of Reproduction Involves The Fusion Of Gametes From Two Parents?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Sexual reproduction ', 'Asexual Reproduction ', 'Binary Fission', 'Budding', '', 'A Explanation Sexual reproduction involves the fusion of gametes from two parents, typically a male and a female. In this process, specialized cells called gametes (sperm and egg) are produced through meiosis. The fusion of these gametes during fertilizat', 1, '2024-02-08 09:21:30'),
(76, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is Autotrophic Nutrition?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Nutrition in which organisms obtain food by breaking down complex organic compounds.', 'Nutrition In Which Organisms Obtain Food From Other Organisms', 'Nutrition In Which Organisms Obtain Food By Consuming Both Plants And Animals ', 'Nutrition In Which Organisms Produce Their Own Food Using Energy From The Sun Or Inorganic Substances', '', 'D Explanation Autotrophic nutrition refers to the ability of organisms to synthesize their own food molecules from simple inorganic substances such as carbon dioxide and water.', 1, '2024-02-08 09:32:12'),
(77, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Theory Of Evolution Can Be Defined As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The belief that all species were created in their current form', 'The Hypothesis That Organisms Strive To Improve Themselves Over Generations ', 'The Idea That Species Change Over Time Through Natural Processes ', 'The Concept That Evolution Occurs Through A Series Of Sudden And Dramatic Changes', '', 'C Explanation The theory of evolution is a scientific explanation for the diversity of life on Earth. It states that species change over time through a process known as natural selection. This theory, proposed by Charles Darwin and Alfred Russel Wallace i', 1, '2024-02-08 09:35:14'),
(78, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Male Reproductive Organ In Humans?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Uterus ', 'Ovary ', 'Testis ', 'D.Â Fallopian Tube', '', 'C Explanation The testis is a male reproductive organ in humans. It is responsible for producing sperm cells and secreting the male sex hormone testosterone. The testes are located within the scrotum, outside the abdominal cavity.', 1, '2024-02-08 09:36:59'),
(79, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of A Behavioral Adaptation For Survival In Animals?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Sharp teeth ', 'Migration ', 'Wings ', 'Camouflage', '', 'B Explanation Migration is an example of a behavioral adaptation for survival in animals. Migration refers to the regular movement of animals from one place to another, often over long distances. Animals may migrate to find better food sources, suitable b', 1, '2024-02-08 09:42:42'),
(80, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Traits Is Not Visible In A Person With Down Syndrome?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Short neck ', 'High Muscle Tone ', 'Small Stature ', 'Slant Eyes', '', ' B Explanation People with Down syndrome always have intellectual or physical disabilities. High muscle tone is not visible in a person with Down syndrome', 1, '2024-02-08 09:50:52'),
(81, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Definition Of Population Ecology?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The study of interactions between organisms and their physical environment ', 'The Study Of Evolutionary Processes And Their Effects On Populations ', 'The Study Of Interactions Between Different Populations In An Ecosystem ', 'The Study Of The Distribution And Abundance Of Individuals Within A Species', '', 'D Explanation Population ecology is a branch of ecology that focuses on the study of populations of organisms belonging to the same species. t involves examining how populations are distributed across different habitats and how their numbers change over t', 1, '2024-02-08 09:54:19'),
(82, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Term Used To Describe The Maximum Number Of Individuals Of A Species That An Environment Can Support Indefinitely?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ecological niche ', 'Limiting Factor ', 'Carrying Capacity ', 'Density-Dependent Factor', '', 'C Explanation Carrying capacity refers to the maximum number of individuals of a species that a particular environment can sustain over a prolonged period of time. It represents the balance between the available resources in the environment and the popula', 1, '2024-02-08 09:56:25'),
(83, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Statements About The Heart Is True?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The heart is responsible for the production of red blood cells ', 'The Heart Pumps Oxygenated Blood To The Lungs', 'he Heart Receives Blood From The Kidneys And Filters Waste Products', 'The Heart Is A Muscular Organ That Contracts To Circulate Blood Throughout The Body', '', ' D Explanation The heart is a vital organ in the circulatory system responsible for pumping and circulating blood throughout the body.', 1, '2024-02-08 09:59:07'),
(84, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Primary Source Of Variation In A Population?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Gene flow ', 'Mutation ', 'Natural Selection ', 'Genetic Drift', '', 'B Explanation The primary source of variation in a population is mutation. Mutation is a spontaneous change in the DNA sequence of an organism&apos;s genome. It introduces new genetic variations by altering the existing genetic information.', 1, '2024-02-08 10:01:09'),
(85, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Component Of Blood Is Responsible For Carrying Oxygen To The Body Tissues?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Platelets ', 'White Blood Cells ', 'Red Blood Cells ', 'Plasma', '', 'C Explanation Red blood cells, also known as erythrocytes, are responsible for carrying oxygen to the body tissues. They contain a protein called hemoglobin, which binds to oxygen in the lungs and transports it to other parts of the body.', 1, '2024-02-08 10:02:48'),
(86, 17, 'JAMB', 'BIOLOGY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Are The Primary Products Of Photosynthesis?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Carbon dioxide and water ', 'Glucose And Oxygen ', 'Glucose And Carbon Dioxide', 'Oxygen And Water', '', 'B Explanation The primary products of photosynthesis are glucose and oxygen. During photosynthesis, plants use sunlight, water, and carbon dioxide to produce glucose, a simple sugar that serves as the main source of energy for the plant. Oxygen is also pr', 1, '2024-02-08 10:05:28'),
