(114, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Shortcut For Creating A New Document ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Ctrl + N  ', 'Ctrl + O', 'Ctrl + Q', 'Ctrl + M', '', 'A Explanation The shortcut for creating a new document is Ctrl + N. This is a standard shortcut across many applications and operating systems.', 1, '2024-02-14 13:15:08'),
(115, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Valid Variable Name In Python?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'my_variable$ ', 'My_variable ', 'My-Variable', '1my_variable', '', 'B Explanation Variable names in Python must start with a letter or underscore, and can only contain letters, numbers, and underscores. The other options are invalid because they either start with a number (option C) or contain a special character (option ', 1, '2024-02-14 13:19:12'),
(116, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;At What Stage In System Development Life Cycle Are All Data Documented In The Form Of Detailed Data Flow Diagrams(DFDs)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'System design', ' Feasibility Study', 'System Analysis', 'Investigative Study', '', 'C Explanation During the System Analysis stage of the System Development Life Cycle (SDLC), all data are documented in the form of detailed Data Flow Diagrams (DFDs). The System Analysis stage involves understanding and documenting the business processes ', 1, '2024-02-14 13:25:01'),
(117, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Translators Are Type Of ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', ' System software', ' Operating System', 'Utility Programs', 'Application Software', '', 'A Explanation Translators are a type of system software. They are used to convert source code written in one programming language (the source language) into another programming language (the target language). Examples of translators include compilers, int', 1, '2024-02-14 13:26:27'),
(118, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Difference Between An Assembler And A Compiler ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'an assembler converts a machine language code into assembly level language code while a compiler converts high level programming language to a machine language code.  ', ' An Assembler Converts Assembly Level Language Code Into Machine Language Code While A Compiler Converts High Level Programming Language Code To A Machine Language Code. ', ' A Compiler Converts Assembly Level Language Code Into Machine Lange While An Assembler Converts High Level Programming Language To A Machine Language Code.', 'They Both Convert Assembly Level Language Code Into Machine Lange', '', ' B Explanation An assembler converts assembly level language code into machine language code while a compiler converts high level programming language code to a machine language code.', 1, '2024-02-14 13:30:37'),
(119, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of These Storage Devices Can Act As A Buffer Between The CPU And The Main Memory ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Hard disk ', ' Floppy Disk ', 'Cache Memory', 'Flash Drive', '', 'C Explanation Cache memory is a very high speed semiconductor memory which can speed up CPU, it acts as a buffer between the CPU and main memory.', 1, '2024-02-14 13:34:12'),
(120, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Evaluate&amp;nbsp;10112+122410112+1224, Leaving Your Answer In Base 10.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '37', '51  ', '47', '73', '', 'A Explanation 10112  = 1 Ã— 23  + 0 Ã— 22  + 1 Ã— 21  + 1 Ã— 20  1 Ã— 8 + 0 Ã— 4 + 1 Ã— 2 + 1 Ã— 1 = 8 + 0 + 2 + 1 = 11 1224  = 1 Ã— 42  + 2 Ã— 41  + 2 Ã— 40  1 Ã— 16 + 2 Ã— 4 + 2 Ã— 1 = 16 + 8 + 2 = 26 11 + 26 = 37   ', 1, '2024-02-14 13:36:57'),
(121, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Part Of The Central Processing Unit Coordinates Other Units And Manages The Computer Resources ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'coordinating unit', 'Memory Unit', 'Arithmetic Logic Unit ', 'Control Unit', '', 'D Explanation The Control Unit of the Central Processing Unit (CPU) coordinates other units and manages the computer resources. It directs the operation of the processor, and interacts with the other hardware components in the system to carry out the inst', 1, '2024-02-14 13:38:24'),
(122, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Does R Stands For In The CRUD Acronym ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', ' Retrieve', 'Redirect', 'Read', 'Relate', '', 'C Explanation In the CRUD acronym, R stands for &apos;Read&apos;. CRUD stands for Create, Read, Update, and Delete. These are the four basic functions of persistent storage in databases.', 1, '2024-02-14 13:40:04'),
(123, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Output Will Be A HIGH For Any Case When One Or More Inputs Are One For A(an)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'OR gate ', 'AND Gate', 'NOR Gate', 'NOT Gate', '', 'A Explanation An OR gate is a digital logic gate that implements logical disjunction - it behaves according to the truth table to the right. A HIGH output (1) results if one or more of the inputs to the gate is HIGH (1). If neither input is high, a LOW ou', 1, '2024-02-14 13:43:59'),
(124, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Type Of Booting Does The Computer Go Through When Starting Up From A Powered Down ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Cold booting ', 'Soft Booting', 'Warm Booting', 'Rebooting', '', 'A Explanation Cold booting is when you start a computer from a powered-down, or off, state. This is often referred to as a system restart or a system reset. Warm booting, on the other hand, is restarting the computer while it&apos;s powered on. Rebooting ', 1, '2024-02-14 13:45:35'),
(125, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Connection Between Two Or More Computers To Share Resources Or Allow Electronic Communication Is Called ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Connection', 'Communication', ' Transfer', 'Network', '', 'D Explanation A network consists of two or more computers that are linked together in order to share resources, exchange files or allow electronic communication', 1, '2024-02-14 13:48:55'),
(126, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is The Standard Keyboard Layout ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Dvorak  ', ' QWERTY', 'AZERTY', 'ABCD', '', ' B Explanation The standard keyboard layout is QWERTY. This layout was patented by Christopher Sholes who invented the typewriter and later adapted to the world&apos;s first computers.   ', 1, '2024-02-14 13:50:17'),
(127, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Analog, Digital And Hybrid Computers Are Classification Of Computers Based On&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'the type of data-handling techniques ', 'The Purpose', 'The Size ', 'The Functionality', '', 'A Explanation Computers are classified into analog, digital, and hybrid based on the type of data-handling techniques they use. Analog computers work with continuous data and are used for tasks such as measuring and controlling voltages. Digital computers', 1, '2024-02-14 13:52:23'),
