(138, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Shortcut For Performing Warm Booting ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'y pressing the Ctrl + Alt keys simultaneously ', 'y pressing the Ctrl + Alt + F1 keys simultaneously ', 'Y Pressing The Ctrl + Del Keys Simultaneously ', 'By Pressing The Ctrl + Alt + Del Keys Simultaneously', '', 'D Explanation Warm booting refers to the process of restarting a computer system which is already on. This can be done by pressing the Ctrl + Alt + Del keys simultaneously. This is a common shortcut for warm booting in many operating systems.', 1, '2024-02-14 14:16:05');
