(140, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When The Computer Reboots Itself Without Triggering The Hardware Based Reset, It Is Called ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'cold booting ', 'Hard Reboot ', 'Cold Reboot ', 'Soft Reboot', '', 'D Explanation soft or warm reboot involves restarting a computer under software control without triggering the hardware based reset.', 1, '2024-02-14 14:18:59'),
