(142, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Difference Between Internal And External Modem&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â external modems are PCI or ISA expansion cards while internal modems are traditionally plug into a serial port on the computer.', 'internal modems are PCI or ISA expansion cards while external modems are traditionally plug into a serial port on the computer.', 'external modems are PCI or ISA expansion cards while internal modems are USB modems', 'Â they are PCI or ISA expansion cards', '', 'B Explanation Internal modems are PCI or ISA expansion cards, they tend to be simple to install while external modems are traditionally plug into a serial port on the computer.', 1, '2024-02-14 14:21:26'),
(143, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Two Types Of Operating System Are&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'command line and graphical user interface', 'Â translators and assemblers', 'system software and application software', 'UNIX and LINUX', '', ' A Explanation Operating systems can be categorized into two types based on their user interface: Command Line Interface (CLI) and Graphical User Interface (GUI). CLI requires users to type commands to interact with the system, while GUI uses visual eleme', 1, '2024-02-14 14:22:46'),
(144, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of These Application Packages Can Be Used To Create A Spreadsheet ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Microsoft powerpoint', 'Microsoft excel', 'Macwrite', 'Microsoft word', '', 'B Explanation Microsoft Excel is an application package that is specifically designed for creating spreadsheets. It provides features for creating, editing, and managing data in a tabular format.', 1, '2024-02-14 14:23:43'),
(145, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Technical Feasibility, The Priority Is ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'whether the probolem can be solved in the user&apos;s environment', 'Â if the likely benefits outweight the cost of solving the problem', 'whether the problem can be solved using existing technology and resources available', 'whether the problem can be solved without causing any social issues', '', 'C Explanation In technical feasibility, the priority is to check whether the problem can be solved using existing technology and resources available.', 1, '2024-02-14 14:24:46'),
(146, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Generation Of Computer Is Characterized By The Use Of Vacuum Tubes For Circuitry And Magnetic Drums For Main Memory?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â second generation', 'Â fourth generation', 'first generation', 'third generation', '', 'C Explanation The first generation computer systems used vacuum tubes for circuitry and magnetic drums for main memory, and they were often enormous, taking up entire rooms.   ', 1, '2024-02-14 14:26:22'),
