(156, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Monitors Has Only Two Colours&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'colour monitor', 'colour graphic adapter (CGA)', 'dichrome monitor', 'monochrome monitor', '', 'D Explanation A monochrome monitor is a type of CRT computer monitor which was very common in the early days of computing, from the 1960s through the 1980s, before color monitors became popular. They are designed to display one color of information (usual', 0, '2024-02-15 08:24:11'),
(157, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Computers Manipulate Data In Many Ways, And This Manipulation Is Called ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'batching', 'utilizing', 'processing', 'upgrading', '', 'C Explanation Computers manipulate data in many ways, and this manipulation is called processing. Data processing refers to the conversion of raw data into meaningful output by performing computations, logical comparisons, and other operations.', 0, '2024-02-15 08:25:26'),
(158, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Computers Manipulate Data In Many Ways, And This Manipulation Is Called ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'batching', 'utilizing', 'processing', 'upgrading', '', 'C Explanation Computers manipulate data in many ways, and this manipulation is called processing. Data processing refers to the conversion of raw data into meaningful output by performing computations, logical comparisons, and other operations.', 0, '2024-02-15 08:25:29'),
(159, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Computer That Combines The Functions Of Both Analog And Digital Computers Is Called ?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Digital computer', 'Analog computer', 'Hybrid computer', 'multipurpose computer', '', 'C Explanation A hybrid computer is a type of computer that combines the characteristics of both digital and analog computers. It is designed to offer the speed of analog equipment and the accuracy and memory of digital equipment.', 0, '2024-02-15 08:27:19'),
