(173, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Let &amp;#39;*&amp;#39; And &amp;#39;^&amp;#39; Be Two Binary Operations Such That A * B = A\\(^2\\)b And A ^ B = 2a + B. Find (-4 * 2) ^ (7 * -1).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', ' -49 ', '64', '113', '15', '', 'D Explanation Given that, a * b = a2 b and a ^ b = 2a + b  (-4 * 2) = (-4)2  x 2 = 16 x 2 = 32  (7 * -1) = 72  x (-1) = 49 x (-1) = -49  âˆ´ (-4 * 2) ^ (7 * -1) = 2(32) + (-49) = 64 - 49 = 15', 0, '2024-02-21 09:32:32'),
