(176, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Interior Angle Of A Regular Polygon Is Five Times The Size Of Its Exterior Angle. Identify The Polygon.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'dodecagon ', 'Â Enneadecagon', 'Icosagon', 'Hendecagon', '', ' A Explanation An interior angle of a regular polygon = (2nâˆ’4)Ã—90n   An exterior angle of a regular polygon = 360n   (2nâˆ’4)Ã—90n  =5 Ã—   360n  (Given) = (2n-4) x 90 = 5 x 360 = 180n - 360 = 1800 = 180n = 1800 + 360 = 180n = 2160 = n = 2160180  = 12 ', 0, '2024-02-21 09:42:16'),
