(178, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Make X The Subject Of The Formula:y =&amp;nbsp;3x&amp;minus;9c4x+5d3ï¿½&amp;minus;9ï¿½4ï¿½+5ï¿½&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â x =Â (âˆ’9câˆ’5dy)4yâˆ’3(âˆ’9ï¿½âˆ’5ï¿½ï¿½)4ï¿½âˆ’3', 'Â X =Â âˆ’9c+5dy4yâˆ’3âˆ’9ï¿½+5ï¿½ï¿½4ï¿½âˆ’3 ', 'Â X =Â (âˆ’9c+5dy)4yâˆ’3(âˆ’9ï¿½+5ï¿½ï¿½)4ï¿½âˆ’3', 'Â X =Â âˆ’(9c+5dy)4yâˆ’3', '', 'D Explanation y = 3xâˆ’9c4x+5d y1=3xâˆ’9c4x+5d = y(4x + 5d) = 3x - 9c  = 4xy + 5dy = 3x - 9c  = 4xy - 3x = -9c - 5dy  = (4y - 3)x = -9c - 5dy  = x = âˆ’9câˆ’5dy4yâˆ’3 x = âˆ’(9c+5dy)4yâˆ’3', 0, '2024-02-21 09:46:03'),
(179, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Solve For X: 3(x &amp;ndash; 1) &amp;le; 2 (x &amp;ndash; 3)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â x â‰¤ -3 Â ', 'X â‰¥ -3', 'X â‰¤ 3', 'X â‰¥ 3', '', 'A Explanation 3(x â€“ 1) â‰¤ 2 (x â€“ 3)  = 3x â€“ 3 â‰¤ 2x â€“ 6  Add 3 to both sides  = 3x â€“ 3+ 3 â‰¤ 2x â€“ 6+ 3  = 3x â‰¤ 2x â€“ 3  Subtract 2x from both the sides  = 3x â€“ 2x â‰¤ 2x â€“ 3 â€“ 2x  âˆ´ x â‰¤ -3', 0, '2024-02-21 09:47:43'),
(180, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Alt=&quot;Open Photo&quot; Src=&quot;https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.15752-9/387472042_368035129000646_4138759283531780509_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_p206x206&amp;amp;_nc_cat=111&amp;amp;ccb=1-7&amp;amp;_nc_sid=510075&amp;amp;_nc_aid=0&amp;amp;_nc_eui2=AeHBWK__ie7XharUeLO0le2KI-v_BbEs8MAj6_8FsSzwwOal-LdiDhgSAv8alBVkAnJvNWbZIgtQ6Yn8PritI3VJ&amp;amp;_nc_ohc=Q0YBBErn2pkAX8zj7nt&amp;amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;amp;_nc_ht=scontent.xx&amp;amp;cb_e2o_trans=q&amp;amp;oh=03_AdTy3RyZS8RZfbV2XsH1jdb87w28u6FRnJGANWNSD28QHQ&amp;amp;oe=65C5E351&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Diagram Above Is A Circle With Centre C. P, Q And S Are Points On The Circumference. PS And SR Are Tangents To The Circle. &amp;ang;PSR = 36oï¿½. Find &amp;ang;PQR&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 7200 ', '3600', '14400', '540', '', 'A Explanation From âˆ†PSR  |PS| = |SR| (If two tangents are drawn from an external point of the circle, then they are of equal lengths)  âˆ´ âˆ†PSR is isosceles  âˆ PSR + âˆ SRP + âˆ SPR = 180o  (sum of angles in a triangle)  Since |PS| = |SR|; âˆ SRP = â', 0, '2024-02-21 09:50:28'),
(181, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If A Car Runs At A Constant Speed And Takes 4.5 Hrs To Run A Distance Of 225 Km, What Time Will It&amp;nbsp;take To Run 150 Km?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', ' 2 hrs ', '4 Hrs', '3 Hrs', '1 Hr', '', 'C Explanation Let T be the time taken and D is the distance  For the case given in the problem, the distance covered is directly proportional to the time taken i.e D Î± T  â‡’ D = ST where S is the constant speed  D = 225 km and T = 4.5 hrs  âˆ´ 225 = S x', 0, '2024-02-21 09:52:42'),
