(184, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Value Of T, If The Distance Between The Points P(&amp;ndash;3, &amp;ndash;14) And Q(t, &amp;ndash;5) Is 9 Units.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '3 B.Â C.Â  D.', '2 ', '- 3', 'Â - 2', '', 'C Explanation Let the given points be:  P(-3, -14) = (x1 , y1 )  Q(t, -5) = (x2 , y2 )  PQ = 9 units (given)  Using the distance formula,  d = âˆš [ (x2âˆ’x1)2+(y2âˆ’y1)2 ]  PQ = âˆš [ (tâˆ’(âˆ’3))2+(âˆ’5+14)2 ]  âŸ¹  âˆš [ (t+3)2+81 ] = 9  Squaring on bo', 0, '2024-02-21 09:59:35'),
(185, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;At Simple Interest, A Man Made A Deposit Of Some Money In The Bank. The Amount In His Bank Account After 10 Years Is Three Times The Money Deposited. If The Interest Rate Stays The Same, After How Many Years Will The Amount Be Five Times The Money Deposited?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '15 yearsÂ ', '25 Years', '20 Years', '30 Years', '', 'C Explanation Amount (A) = Principal (P) + Interest (I) i.e. A = P + I  1 = PTR100 A = 3P; T = 10 years (Given)  Since A = P + I  âŸ¹3P=P+PÃ—10Ã—R100 âŸ¹3P=P+10PR100 âŸ¹3P=P+PR10 âŸ¹3Pâˆ’P=PR10 âŸ¹2P=PR10 âŸ¹2P1=PR10 âŸ¹  PR = 20P  âˆ´  R = 20%  Since the', 0, '2024-02-21 10:01:20'),
