(188, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If D =&amp;nbsp;âŽ¡âŽ£âŽ¢241&amp;minus;11&amp;minus;3321âŽ¤âŽ¦âŽ¥[2&amp;minus;134121&amp;minus;31]&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Find |D|&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 16', '14', '-23', 'Â -37', '', 'C Explanation âŽ¡âŽ£âŽ¢241âˆ’11âˆ’3321âŽ¤âŽ¦âŽ¥ = 2[(1 x 1) - (2 x -3)] - (-1)[(4 x 1) - (2 x 1)] + 3[(4 x -3) - (1 x 1)]  = 2(1 - (-6)) + 1(4 - 2) + 3(-12 - 1)  = 2(1 + 6) + 1(2) + 3(-13)  = 2(7) + 1(2) + 3(-13)  = 14 + 2 - 39  âˆ´ |D| = -23', 0, '2024-02-21 10:17:05'),
(189, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Boat Sails 8 Km North From P To Q And Then Sails 6 Km West From Q To R. Calculate The Bearing Of R From P. Give Your Answer To The Nearest Degree.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 217oï¿½ ', '323oï¿½', '037oï¿½', 'Â 053oï¿½', '', 'B Explanation Open photo  tan Î¸ = oppadj=RQQP=68 tan Î¸ = 0.75  Î¸ = tanâˆ’1(0.75)=36.87o   âˆ´ The bearing of R from P = 360o  - 36.87o  = 323o  (to the nearest degree)', 0, '2024-02-21 10:18:47'),
(190, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Coin Is Thrown 3 Times. What Is The Probability That&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;atleast One&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;head Is Obtained?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '7878', '3838', 'None The Above', '1818', '', 'A Explanation Sample space = {HHH, HHT, HTH, THH, TTH, THT, HTT, TTT}  Total number of possible outcomes = 2 x 2 x 2 = 8  favourable number of outcomes = 7  âˆ´Pr(at least one head) = 78', 0, '2024-02-21 10:20:06'),
(191, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Equation Of Straight Line Passing Through (2, 3) And Perpendicular To The Line&amp;nbsp;3x+2y+4=03ï¿½+2ï¿½+4=0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '3y = 5x - 2 ', 'Y =Â 53Ã—âˆ’253Ã—âˆ’2 ', 'None Of These', '3y = 2x + 5', '', 'D Explanation 3x+2y+4=0 Rearrange:  2y=âˆ’3xâˆ’4 Divide both sides by 2  y = âˆ’3Ã—âˆ’42 y = âˆ’32Ã—âˆ’2 âˆ´ the gradient of the line 3x + 2y + 4 = 0 is âˆ’32 If two lines are perpendicular to each other âˆ´ m1xm2  = -1  Let m1=âˆ’32âˆ´m2=âˆ’1m1=âˆ’1âˆ’3/', 0, '2024-02-21 10:21:52'),
(192, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Differentiate The Function Y =&amp;nbsp;x2&amp;minus;&amp;minus;&amp;radic;3(2x&amp;minus;x2)ï¿½23(2ï¿½&amp;minus;ï¿½2)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â dydx=10x5/33âˆ’8x2/33ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½=10ï¿½5/33âˆ’8ï¿½2/33 ', 'Dydx=10x2/33âˆ’8x5/33ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½=10ï¿½2/33âˆ’8ï¿½5/33 ', 'Dydx=10x5/33âˆ’8x5/33ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½=10ï¿½5/33âˆ’8ï¿½5/33 ', 'Dydx=10x2/33âˆ’8x2/33ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½=10ï¿½2/33âˆ’8ï¿½2/33', '', 'B Explanation y = x2(2xâˆ’x2)âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆš3=x2/3(2xâˆ’x2) = 2x5/3âˆ’x8/3 Now, we can differentiate the function  âˆ´dydx=10x2/33âˆ’8x5/33', 0, '2024-02-21 10:23:57'),
(193, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Calculate The Mean Deviation Of The First Five Prime Numbers.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2.72 ', '5.6', '5.25', '13.6', '', 'A Explanation The first five prime numbers are 2, 3, 5, 7 and 11  M.D = âˆ‘(xâˆ’xÌ„ )n n = 5  xÌ„ =âˆ‘xn=2+3+5+7+115=285=5.6 M.D = (2âˆ’5.6)+(3âˆ’5.6)+(5âˆ’5.6)+(7âˆ’5.6)+(11âˆ’5.6)5 = (âˆ’3.6)+(âˆ’2.6)+(âˆ’0.6)+(1.4)+(5.4)5=13.65 Take the absolute value ', 0, '2024-02-21 10:25:23'),
(194, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Determine The Area Of The Region Bounded By Y =&amp;nbsp;2x22ï¿½2&amp;nbsp;+ 10 And&amp;nbsp;Y&amp;nbsp;=&amp;nbsp;4x+164ï¿½+16.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '18 ', ' âˆ’103', ' 443', ' 643', '', 'D Explanation To find the point of intersection, equate the two equations  â‡’ 2x2  + 10 = 4x + 16  â‡’ 2x2  + 10 - 4x - 16 = 0  â‡’ 2x2  - 4x - 6 = 0  Factorize  â‡’ 2(x + 1)(x - 3) = 0  âˆ´ x = -1 or 3  The curves will intersect at -1 and 3  Open photo ', 0, '2024-02-21 10:29:16'),
(195, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Value Of Y If&amp;nbsp;402y=102ten402ï¿½=102ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4', '2 ', 'Â 5', 'Â 3', '', 'C Explanation 402y=102ten â‡’ 4 x y2  + 0 x y1  + 2 x y0  = 102  â‡’ 4y2  + 0 + 2 x 1 = 102  â‡’ 4y2  + 2 = 102  â‡’ 4y2  = 102 - 2  â‡’ 4y2  = 100  â‡’ y2=1004 â‡’ y2  = 25  âˆ´ y = âˆš25 = 5', 0, '2024-02-21 10:31:02'),
(196, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Value Of Y, If Log (y + 8) + Log (y - 8) = 2log 3 + 2log 5&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â y = Â±5', 'Y = Â±10', 'Y = Â±17', 'Â Y = Â±13', '', 'C Explanation log (y + 8) + log (y - 8) = 2log 3 + 2log 5  â‡’ log (y + 8)(y - 8) = 2log 3 + 2log 5 (log ab = log a + log b)  â‡’ log (y2  -8y + 8y - 64) = log 32  + log 52   â‡’ log (y2  - 64) = log 32  + log 52   â‡’ log (y2  - 64) = log 9 + log 25  â‡’', 0, '2024-02-21 10:32:57'),
(197, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In A Group Of 500 People, 350 People Can Speak English, And 400 People Can Speak French. Find How Many People Can Speak Both Languages.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '750 ', '850', '250 ', '150', '', 'C Explanation Let F be the set of people who can speak French and E be the set of people who can speak English. Then,  n(F) = 400  n(E) = 350  n(F âˆª E) = 500  We have to find n(F âˆ© E).  Now, n(F âˆª E) = n(F) + n(E) â€“ n(F âˆ© E)  â‡’ 500 = 400 + 350', 0, '2024-02-21 10:35:01'),
(198, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Factorize:&amp;nbsp;16x4&amp;minus;y416ï¿½4&amp;minus;ï¿½4&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â (2xâˆ’y)(2x+y)(4x2+y2)(2ï¿½âˆ’ï¿½)(2ï¿½+ï¿½)(4ï¿½2+ï¿½2) ', '(2x+Y)(2x+Y)(4x2+Y2)(2ï¿½+ï¿½)(2ï¿½+ï¿½)(4ï¿½2+ï¿½2) ', '(2xâˆ’Y)(2xâˆ’Y)(4x2+Y2)(2ï¿½âˆ’ï¿½)(2ï¿½âˆ’ï¿½)(4ï¿½2+ï¿½2) ', 'Â (2xâˆ’Y)(2x+Y)(4x2âˆ’Y2)', '', 'A Explanation 16x4âˆ’y4   = 24x4âˆ’y4   = (2x)4âˆ’y4   = ((2x)2)2âˆ’(y2)2   Using a2âˆ’b2  = (a - b)(a + b) identity  = ((2x)2âˆ’y2)((2x)2+y2)   Using the identity one more time  = (2xâˆ’y)(2x+y)((2x)2+y2)   âˆ´ (2xâˆ’y)(2x+y)(4x2+y2)', 0, '2024-02-21 10:36:50'),
(199, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If A = { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}, B = { 2, 4, 6, 8 }. Find (A &amp;ndash; B) â‹ƒ (B &amp;ndash; A).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â {1, 3, 5, 8} ', 'Â {8} ', 'Â {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8} ', 'Â {1, 3, 5}', '', 'A Explanation A = { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}  B = { 2, 4, 6, 8 }  A - B = { 1, 3, 5 }  B - A = { 8 }  âˆ´ (A - B) â‹ƒ (B - A) = {1, 3, 5, 8}', 0, '2024-02-21 10:38:38'),
(200, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Bag Contains 8 Red Balls And Some White Balls. If The Probability Of Drawing A White Ball Is Half Of The Probability Of Drawing A Red Ball Then Find The Probability Of Drawing A Red Ball And A White Ball If The Balls Are Drawn Without Replacement.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1313 ', '2929 ', '2323 ', '833833', '', 'D Explanation Let the number of white balls be n  The number of red balls = 8  Now, the probability of drawing a white ball = nn+8 The probability of drawing a red ball = 8n+8 Since Pr(White ball) = 12  x Pr(Red ball)  âˆ´nn+8=12Ã—8n+8 = nn+8=4n+8 âˆ´n=4 ', 0, '2024-02-21 10:40:41'),
(201, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Ages Of Students In A Small Primary School Were Recorded In The Table Below.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;table Border=&quot;1&quot; Cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; Cellspacing=&quot;1&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Age&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;5-6&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;7-8&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;9-10&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frequency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; 29&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; 40&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;38&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nEstimate The Median.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 7.725', 'Â 6.225', 'Â 7.5', 'Â 6.5', '', 'A Explanation N+12=107+12  th = 54th value i.e the median age is in the interval &quot;7 - 8&quot; (29 + 25 = 54)  Median = 1m+(âˆ‘f/2âˆ’fbfm) c  lm =lower class boundary of the median age = 6.5  âˆ‘f  = 107  fb  = sum of all frequencies before the median', 0, '2024-02-21 10:42:39'),
(202, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Matrix A&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;A&amp;nbsp;[021&amp;minus;1][012&amp;minus;1]&amp;nbsp;=&amp;nbsp;[21&amp;minus;10][2&amp;minus;110]&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â [2âˆ’1/21âˆ’1/2][21âˆ’1/2âˆ’1/2] ', 'Â [01/211/2][011/21/2] ', '[201âˆ’1][210âˆ’1]', 'Â [21/21âˆ’2][211/2âˆ’2]', '', ' B Explanation Let A = [acbd] i.e [acbd]  [021âˆ’1]  = [21âˆ’10] âŸ¹[a(0)+b(2)c(0)+d(2)a(1)+b(âˆ’1)c(1)+d(âˆ’1)]  = [21âˆ’10] âŸ¹[2b2daâˆ’bcâˆ’d]  = [21âˆ’10] By comparing  2b = 2  a - b = -1  2d = 1 and  c - d = 0  âˆ´ b = 2/2  = 1  a - b = -1  â‡’ a - 1', 0, '2024-02-21 10:44:47'),
