(204, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If&amp;nbsp;&amp;minus;2x3+6x2+17x&amp;minus;2ï¿½3+6ï¿½2+17ï¿½&amp;nbsp;- 21 Is Divided By&amp;nbsp;(x+1)(ï¿½+1), Then The Remainder Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '32 ', 'Â 30', 'Â -30', '-32', '', 'C Explanation Let p(x)=âˆ’2x3+6x2+17xâˆ’21   Using the remainder theorem  Let x+1=0   âˆ´ x=âˆ’1   Since, (x+1)  divides p(x) , then, remainder will be p(-1)  â‡’ p(-1) = -2(-1)3+6(âˆ’1)2  + 17(-1) - 21  âˆ´ p(-1) = -30', 0, '2024-02-21 10:49:10'),
(205, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Let A Binary Operation &amp;#39;*&amp;#39; Be Defined On A Set A. The Operation Will Be Commutative If&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â a*b = b*a ', '(A*B)*C = A*(B*C) ', 'Â (B ÎŸ C)*A = (B*A) ÎŸ (C*A)', 'None Of The Above', '', 'A Explanation A binary operation &apos;*&apos; defined on a set A is said to be commutative only if a*b=b*a, âˆ€a, bâˆˆA.  If (a*b)*c=a*(b*c), then the operation is said to associative âˆ€ a, bâˆˆ A.  If (b Î¿ c)*a=(b*a) Î¿ (c*a), then the operation is sa', 0, '2024-02-21 10:50:41'),
(206, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Solve The Following Quadratic Inequality:&amp;nbsp;x2&amp;minus;xï¿½2&amp;minus;ï¿½&amp;nbsp;- 4 &amp;le; 2&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â âˆ’3&lt;x&lt;2âˆ’3&lt;ï¿½&lt;2 ', 'Â âˆ’2â‰¤Xâ‰¤3âˆ’2â‰¤ï¿½â‰¤3', 'Xâ‰¤âˆ’2,Xâ‰¤3ï¿½â‰¤âˆ’2,ï¿½â‰¤3', 'Â âˆ’2&lt;X&lt;3âˆ’2&lt;ï¿½&lt;3', '', 'B Explanation x2âˆ’xâˆ’4â‰¤2  Subtract two from both sides to rewrite it in the quadratic standard form: = x2âˆ’xâˆ’4âˆ’2â‰¤2âˆ’2  = x2âˆ’xâˆ’6â‰¤0  Now set it = 0 and factor and solve like normal. = x2âˆ’x  - 6=0 = (xâˆ’3)(x+2) =0 x  + 2 = 0 or x  - 3 = ', 0, '2024-02-21 10:52:23'),
(207, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The General Term Of The Sequence 3, 8, 13, 18, ...?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 5n - 2 ', '5n + 2 ', 'Â 5', 'Â 5n', '', 'A Explanation Given the sequence 3, 8, 13, 18, ... which is an arithmetic sequence  a = 3  d = T2  - T1  = 8 - 3 = 5  The general term of an A.P is:  Tn  = a + (n - 1)d  â‡’ Tn  = 3 + (n - 1)5  = Tn  = 3 + 5n - 5  âˆ´ Tn  = 5n - 2', 0, '2024-02-21 10:53:56'),
