(215, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Man Sells Different Brands Of An Items.&amp;nbsp;1/91/9&amp;nbsp;of The Items He Has In His Shop Are From Brand A,&amp;nbsp;5/85/8&amp;nbsp;of The Remainder Are From Brand B And The Rest Are From Brand C. If The Total Number Of Brand C Items In The Man&amp;#39;s Shop Is 81, How Many More Brand B Items Than Brand C Does The Shop Has?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 243 ', '108', '54', '135', '', 'C Explanation Let the total number of items in the man&apos;s shop = y Number of Brand A&apos;s items in the man&apos;s shop = 19y Remaining items = 1 - 19y=89y Number of Brand B&apos;s items in The man&apos;s shop = 58of89y=59y Total of Brand A and Brand', 0, '2024-02-21 11:07:55'),
(216, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Area, To The Nearest Cm22, Of The Triangle Whose Sides Are In The Ratio 2 : 3 : 4 And Whose Perimeter Is 180 Cm.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 1162 cm22 ', '1163 Cm22 ', '1160 Cm22', 'Â 1161 Cm2', '', ' A Explanation Let the length of the sides of triangle be 2x, 3x and 4x.  Perimeter of triangle = 180cm  â‡’ 2x+3x+4x=180 â‡’ 9x=180 â‡’ x=1809  = 20cm  Then the sides of the triangle are:  2x=2Ã—20=40cm;3x=3Ã—20  = 60cm and 4x  = 4Ã—20 = 80cm  Using Hero', 0, '2024-02-21 11:09:35'),
