(219, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Third Term Of An A.P Is 6 And The Fifth Term Is 12. Find The Sum Of Its First Twelve Terms&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '201 ', 'Â 144', '198', 'Â 72', '', 'C Explanation T3  = 6  T5  = 12  S12  = ?  Tn  = a + (n - 1)d  â‡’ T3  = a + 2d = 6 ----- (i)  â‡’ T5  = a + 4d = 12 ----- (ii)  Subtract equation (ii) from (i)  â‡’ -2d = -6  â‡’ dâˆ’6âˆ’2  = 3  Substitute 3 for d in equation (i)  â‡’ a + 2(3) = 6  â‡’ a', 0, '2024-02-21 11:14:51'),
