(229, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Rectangle Has One Side That Is 6 Cm Shorter Than The Other. The Area Of The Rectangle Will Increase By 68 Cm22&amp;nbsp;if We Add 2 Cm To Each Side Of The Rectangle. Find The Length Of The Shorter Side.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '15 cm ', '19 Cm ', 'Â 13 Cm', 'Â 21 Cm', '', 'C Explanation Let the length of the longer side = x  cm  âˆ´ The length of the shorter side = (x  - 6) cm  If we increase each side&apos;s length by 2 cm, it becomes  (x  + 2) cm and (x  - 4) cm respectively  Area of a rectangle = L x B  A1=x(xâˆ’6)=x2âˆ’', 0, '2024-02-21 11:33:00'),
