(234, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Solve The Logarithmic Equation:&amp;nbsp;log2(6&amp;minus;x)=3&amp;minus;log2xï¿½ï¿½ï¿½2(6&amp;minus;ï¿½)=3&amp;minus;ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½2ï¿½&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â xï¿½Â = 4 or 2 ', 'Â Xï¿½Â = -4 Or -2', 'Xï¿½Â = -4 Or 2', 'Â Xï¿½Â = 4 Or -2', '', 'A Explanation log2(6âˆ’x)=3âˆ’log2x â‡’ log2(6âˆ’x)=3log22âˆ’log2x  (since log2  2 = 1)  â‡’ log2(6âˆ’x)=log223âˆ’log2x  (alog  c = log  ca) â‡’ log2(6âˆ’x)=log28âˆ’log2x â‡’log2(6âˆ’x)=log28x  (log  a - log  b = logab) â‡’ 6âˆ’x=8x â‡’ x(6âˆ’x)=8 â‡’ 6xâ', 0, '2024-02-21 11:41:42'),
(235, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/p8e2fPmBN5KV0iBs3mEzF1bR5Oi5zwmgx7KM85KX.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Calculate The Area Of The Composite Figure Above.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '6048 m22', '3969 M2', '4628 M2', '5834 M2', '', 'B Explanation Area of the composite figure = Area of semi circle + Area of rectangle + Area of triangle  Area of semi circle = 12Ï€r2=12Ã—Ï€Ã—d24=12Ã—227Ã—4224=693m2 Area of rectangle = l x b = 42 x 60  =2520 m2 Area of triangle = 12Ã—bÃ—h=12Ã—36Ã—42=756m', 0, '2024-02-21 11:43:47'),
(236, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/NdYkqLFIYjPXvWMm3JNJJstGNctCogPaEBtUDaKW.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Find The Value Of X In The Diagram Above&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '10 units ', '15 Units', '5 Units ', 'Â 20 Units', '', ' A Explanation Intersecting Chords Theorem states that If two chords intersect in a circle, then the products of the measures of the segments of the chords are equal.  â‡’ AE * EB = CE * ED  â‡’ 6 * x  = 4 * (x  + 5)  â‡’ 6x  = 4x  + 20  â‡’ 6x  - 4x  = 2', 0, '2024-02-21 11:45:18'),
(237, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/1ImYK0mW2LqcON9rrW1oybK9jlLcOdY2zwql7ltr.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Which Inequality Describes The Graph Above?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 4y+5xâ‰¥204ï¿½+5ï¿½â‰¥20 ', '5y+4xâ‰¤205ï¿½+4ï¿½â‰¤20 ', '4y+5xâ‰¤204ï¿½+5ï¿½â‰¤20', 'Â 5y+4xâ‰¥20', '', ' B Explanation First, we find the equation of the boundary line using the two intercepts.The slope is  m = 4âˆ’00âˆ’5=45 The y-intercept is 4  The slope-intercept form of the equation is therefore  y = -45x+4 âŸ¹y+45x=4 Multiply both sides by 54 âŸ¹54(y+4', 0, '2024-02-21 11:46:50'),
(238, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Volume Of A Cone Which Has A Base Radius Of 5 Cm And Slant Height Of 13 Cm.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '300Ï€300ï¿½Â cm33 ', '325Ï€325ï¿½Â Cm33', '3253Ï€3253ï¿½Â Cm33', '100Ï€100ï¿½Â Cm3', '', ' D Explanation  Volume of a cone = 13Ï€r2h   r = 5 cm  l = 13 cm  Using Pythagoras theorem  â‡’ 132=52+h2   â‡’ 169=25+h2   â‡’ 169âˆ’25=h2   â‡’ h2=144   â‡’ h=1â€“âˆš44=12cm âˆ´ Volume of the cone = 13Ã—Ï€Ã—52x12=100Ï€  cm3  ', 0, '2024-02-21 11:48:46'),
(239, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/Tpxv7MwjFjgwxoPtdYr2xHa4vV8OZDeyc3goefQQ.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Study The Given Histogram Above And Answer The Question That Follows.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;What Is The Total Number Of Students That Scored&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;at Most&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;50 Marks?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '380 ', '340 ', 'Â 360 ', '240', '', 'C Explanation Total number of students that scored at most 50 marks = 100 + 80 + 60 + 40 + 80 = 360', 0, '2024-02-21 11:50:20'),
(240, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Area Of A Trapezium Is 200 Cm22. Its Parallel Sides Are In The Ratio 2 : 3 And The Perpendicular Distance Between Them Is 16 Cm. Find The Length Of Each Of The Parallel Sides.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '10 cm and 15 cm', '8 Cm And 12 Cm ', '6 Cm And 9 Cm', '12 Cm And 18 Cm', '', 'A Explanation  Area of trapezium = 12(a+b)h â‡’ 12(a+b)Ã—16=200 â‡’ 8(a + b) = 200  â‡’ a + b = 2008  = 25 -----(i)  â‡’ a : b = 2 : 3  â‡’ ab=23 â‡’ 3a = 2b  â‡’ a = 2b3  -------(ii)  Substitute 2b3  for a in equation (i)  â‡’ 2b3  + b = 25   5b3  = 25  ', 0, '2024-02-21 11:51:56'),
(241, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Student Pilot Was Required To Fly To An Airport And Then Return As Part Of His Flight Training. The Average Speed To The Airport Was 120 Km/h, And The Average Speed Returning Was 150 Km/h. If The Total Flight Time Was 3 Hours, Calculate The Distance Between The Two Airports.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 270 km ', '200 Km ', '360 Km ', '450 Km', '', 'B Explanation Speed = DistanceTime â‡’ Time = DistanceTime Let D = distance between the two airports  âˆ´ Time taken to get to the airport = D120  and Time taken to return =D150 Since total time of flight= 3hours,  â‡’ D120+D150  = 3  â‡’ 15D+12D1800  = 3', 0, '2024-02-22 09:56:49'),
(242, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Perimeter Of An Isosceles Right-angled&amp;nbsp;triangle Is 2 Meters. Find The Length Of Its Longer Side.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2 -Â 2â€“âˆš ', '-4 + 32â€“âˆš ', 'It Cannot Be Determined ', '-2 + 22â€“âˆšÂ M', '', 'D Explanation  Perimeter of a triangle = sum of all sides  â‡’ P=y+x+x=2 â‡’ y+2x=2 â‡’ y=2âˆ’2x -----(i)  Using Pythagoras theorem  y2=x2+x2 â‡’ y2=2x2 â‡’ y=2â€“âˆšx2 â‡’ y=x2â€“âˆš -----(ii)  Equate y â‡’ 2âˆ’2x=x2â€“âˆš Square both sides  â‡’ (2âˆ’2x)', 0, '2024-02-22 09:58:28'),
(243, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Ship Sets Sail From Port A (86oï¿½N, 56oï¿½W) For Port B (86oï¿½N, 64oï¿½W), Which Is Close By. Find The Distance The Ship Covered From Port A To Port B, Correct To The Nearest Km.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\n[Take&amp;nbsp;&amp;pi;ï¿½&amp;nbsp;= 3.142 And R = 6370 Km]&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '62 km ', '97 Km ', '389 Km ', '931 Km', '', 'A Explanation AB = Î¸360Ã—2Ï€Rcosâˆ  (distance on small circle)  = 64 - 56 = 8o âˆ=86o â‡’ AB = 8360  x 2 x 3.142 x 6370 x cos 86  â‡’ AB = 22,338.29974360 âˆ´ AB = 62km (to the nearest km)', 0, '2024-02-22 09:59:37'),
(244, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/LgZHyZml1wF9auEVGuzUKvz48kG4HiQ4NNeTfnTx.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Use The Graph Of Sin (&amp;theta;) Above To Estimate The Value Of &amp;theta; When Sin (&amp;theta;) = -0.6 For&amp;nbsp;0o&amp;le;&amp;theta;&amp;le;360o0ï¿½&amp;le;&amp;theta;&amp;le;360ï¿½&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Î¸ = 223oï¿½, 305oï¿½', 'Î˜ = 210oï¿½, 330oï¿½ ', 'Î˜ = 185oï¿½, 345oï¿½ ', 'Î˜ = 218oï¿½, 323o', '', 'D Explanation  On the y -axis, each box is 1âˆ’05=15  = 0.2unit  On the x -axis, each box is 90âˆ’06=906=15o â‡’ Î¸1=180o+(2.5Ã—15o)=180o+37.5o=217.5oâ‰ƒ218o (2 and half boxes were counted to the right of 180o )  â‡’ Î¸2=270o+(3.5Ã—15o)=270o+52.5o=322.5oâ', 0, '2024-02-22 10:01:04'),
(245, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Circle Has A Radius Of 13 Cm With A Chord 12 Cm Away From The Centre Of The Circle. Calculate The Length Of The Chord.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 16 cm', '8 Cm', '5 Cm', '10 Cm', '', ' D Explanation  |AP| = |PB| = x  (The perpendicular to a chord bisects the chord if drawn from the center of the circle.)  From âˆ†OPB  Using Pythagoras theorem  â‡’ 132=122+x2   â‡’ 169=144+x2   â‡’ 169âˆ’144=x2   â‡’ x2=25   â‡’ x=2â€“âˆš5=5cm   âˆ´ Len', 0, '2024-02-22 10:04:59'),
(246, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Give The Number Of Significant Figures Of The Population Of A Town Which Has Approximately 5,020,700 People&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '7 significant figures B.C.Â  D.', '3 Significant Figures ', '4 Significant Figures', '5 Significant Figures', '', 'D Explanation The two trailing zeros in the number are not significant, but the other five are, making it a five-figure number.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:07:46'),
(247, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;200 Tickets Were Sold For A Show. VIP Tickets Costs â‚¦1,200 And â‚¦700 For Regular. Total Amount Realised From The Sale Of The Tickets Was â‚¦180,000. Find The Number Of VIP Tickets Sold And The The Number Of Regular Ticket Sold.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â VIP = 80, Regular = 100 ', 'VIP = 60, Regular = 120', 'VIP = 60, Regular = 100', 'VIP = 80, Regular = 120', '', ' D Explanation Let x  = number of VIP tickets sold and  y  = number of regular tickets sold  Total number of tickets sold = 200  â‡’ x  + y  = 200 ---- (i)  If it costs â‚¦1,200 for a VIP ticket, then it costs â‚¦1200x for x  number of VIP tickets sold an', 0, '2024-02-22 10:10:31'),
(248, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;It Takes 12 Men 8 Hours A Day To Finish A Piece Of Work In 4 Days. In How Many Days Will It Take 4 Men Working 16 Hours A Day To Complete The Same Piece Of Work?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '6 days ', '8 Days', '10 Days', '12 Days', '', 'A Explanation 12 men working 8 hours a day can complete the work in 4 days  12 men working 1 hour a day will complete the same work in (8 x 4) days [working less hours a day means they have to work for more days]   1 man working 1 hour a day will complete', 0, '2024-02-22 10:12:16'),
(249, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Happens To The Position Of Equilibrium, If A Reversible Exothermic Reaction Is Subjected To A Decrease In Temperature?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The position of equilibrium shifts to the left', 'The Position Of Equilibrium Shifts To The Right.', 'The Position Of Equilibrium Remains Unchanged ', 'The Reaction Stops', '', 'B Explanation When the temperature is decreased in a reversible reaction, the equilibrium shifts in the direction that produces heat (exothermic direction). For an exothermic reaction, this means the equilibrium position shifts to the right, favoring the ', 0, '2024-02-22 10:15:36'),
(250, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Noble Gas Is Radioactive And Is Produced As A Decay Product Of Uranium And Thorium?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Argon ', 'Â Krypton ', 'Radon', 'Neon', '', 'C Explanation Radon is a radioactive noble gas and is produced as a decay product of uranium and thorium in the Earth&apos;s crust. It is colorless, odorless, and tasteless, making it potentially hazardous when it accumulates in enclosed spaces.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:17:01'),
(251, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Reactions Would Be Expected To Have The Highest Entropy Change?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Liquid â†’ Gas ', 'Solid â†’ Liquid ', 'Gas â†’ Liquid', 'Gas â†’ Solid', '', ' A Explanation The phase change from a liquid to a gas involves an increase in entropy. In the gas phase, molecules have higher degrees of freedom and are more dispersed compared to the liquid phase, resulting in higher entropy change.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:18:24'),
(252, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;According To The Kinetic Theory Of Gases, The Pressure Exerted By A Gas Is Due To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â The vibrations of gas particles. ', 'The Weight Of The Gas Particles', 'The Attractive Forces Between Gas Particles ', 'The Collisions Of Gas Particles With The Container Walls', '', 'D Explanation In the kinetic theory of gases, the pressure exerted by a gas is a result of the frequent and random collisions of gas particles with the walls of the container. The force of these collisions creates pressure on the container walls.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:22:40'),
(253, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Name Of The Process By Which Ammonia Is Produced On An Industrial Scale?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Nitrogenation ', 'Ammoniation ', 'Nitrification', 'Haber Process', '', 'D Explanation The industrial production of ammonia is known as the Haber process. It involves the reaction of nitrogen gas (N2 ) and hydrogen gas (H2 ) at high temperature and pressure in the presence of a catalyst to produce ammonia (NH3 ).', 0, '2024-02-22 10:28:52'),
(254, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Who Proposed The Planetary Model Of The Atom With Electrons Orbiting The Nucleus?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Erwin SchrÃ¶dinger ', 'Â Ernest Rutherford ', 'Niels Bohr', 'J.J. Thomson', '', 'C Explanation Niels Bohr proposed the planetary model of the atom in 1913. According to this model, electrons move in circular orbits around the positively charged nucleus, much like planets orbiting the sun. However, this model has been refined in modern', 0, '2024-02-22 10:30:08'),
(255, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of An Endothermic Reaction?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Combustion of propane (C33H88) to produce carbon dioxide (CO22) and water (H22O).', 'Burning Of Methane (CH44) In The Presence Of Oxygen ', 'Â Formation Of Table Salt (NaCl) From Sodium (Na) And Chlorine (Cl22). ', 'Decomposition Of Hydrogen Peroxide (H22O22) Into Water (H22O) And Oxygen (O22).', '', ' D Explanation The decomposition of hydrogen peroxide (H2 O2 ) into water (H2 O) and oxygen (O2 ) is an endothermic reaction because it requires energy to break the bonds in the hydrogen peroxide molecule. The process absorbs heat from the surroundings to', 0, '2024-02-22 10:32:11'),
(256, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Happens To The Value Of The Equilibrium Constant (Kc) For A Reaction If The Reaction Is Reversed?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'It becomes zero ', 'It Becomes Negative', 'It Remains The Same', 'It Becomes The Reciprocal Of The Original Value', '', 'D Explanation If a reaction is reversed, the equilibrium constant (Kc) for the reversed reaction becomes the reciprocal of the original equilibrium constant. For a reaction: A + B â‡Œ C + D The equilibrium constant Kc = [C][D]/[A][B] For the reversed reac', 0, '2024-02-22 10:34:13'),
(257, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Chemical Structure Of Soap And Detergent Molecules?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Hydrophilic head and hydrophobic tail', 'Hydrophilic Head And Hydrophilic Tail ', 'Hydrophobic Head And Hydrophobic Tail', 'Â Hydrophilic Tail And Hydrophobic Head', '', ' A Explanation Both soap and detergent molecules have a hydrophilic (water-attracting) head and a hydrophobic (water-repelling) tail. The hydrophilic head allows the molecules to interact with water, while the hydrophobic tail interacts with oils and grea', 0, '2024-02-22 10:35:54'),
(258, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Solubility Product Constant (Ksp) Used For?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'To measure the total mass of a solute that can dissolve in a solvent ', 'Â To Determine The Concentration Of A Solute In A Saturated Solution', 'To Calculate The Solubility Of A Solute In A Given Solvent', 'To Compare The Solubilities Of Different Solutes In The Same Solvent', '', ' B Explanation The solubility product constant (Ksp) is a constant specific to a given solute and solvent at a particular temperature. It is used to calculate the concentration of a solute in a saturated solution, where no more solute can dissolve at equi', 0, '2024-02-22 10:37:55'),
(259, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Trace Gas In The Atmosphere Plays A Significant Role In The Greenhouse Effect?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Oxygen ', 'Argon', 'Carbon Dioxide', 'Â Nitrogen', '', 'C Explanation Carbon dioxide (CO2) is a trace gas in the atmosphere, but it plays a significant role in the greenhouse effect. It absorbs and traps heat from the Earth&apos;s surface, contributing to global warming.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:39:18'),
(260, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Methods Can Be Used To Remove Temporary Hardness From Water?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Boiling ', 'Filtration', 'Sedimentation', 'Chlorination', '', ' A Explanation Temporary hardness in water can be removed by boiling. When water is boiled, the calcium and magnesium bicarbonates decompose, forming insoluble calcium carbonate (CaCO3) and magnesium carbonate (MgCO3), which precipitate out of the water.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:40:43'),
(261, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is Faraday&amp;#39;s Constant?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 6.022 x 102323Â molâˆ’1âˆ’1 ', '3.00 X 1088Â M/S', '9.81 M/S22', '96,485 C/Mol', '', 'D Explanation Faraday&apos;s constant is a proportionality constant that relates the amount of electric charge (in coulombs) required to liberate or deposit one mole of substance during an electrolytic reaction. Its value is approximately 96,485 C/mol.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:42:11'),
(262, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Gas Occupies A Volume Of 1.5 Liters At A Pressure Of 2 Atmospheres. If The Pressure Is Increased To 4 Atmospheres While The Temperature Remains Constant, What Will Be The New Volume Of The Gas?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 6 liters ', '1.5 Liters', '0.75 Liters', '3 Liters', '', ' C Explanation According to Boyle&apos;s law (for constant temperature), the product of initial pressure and initial volume is equal to the product of final pressure and final volume. Therefore, (1.5 liters) Ã— (2 atmospheres) = (new volume) Ã— (4 atmosph', 0, '2024-02-22 10:43:28'),
(263, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Stainless Steel Is An Alloy Made Up Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Iron and zinc', 'Copper And Tin', 'Iron And Chromium', 'Iron And Carbon', '', 'C Explanation Stainless steel is an alloy composed of iron and chromium, with small amounts of other elements like nickel and molybdenum. The addition of chromium provides stainless steel with excellent corrosion resistance.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:45:13'),
(264, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The State Of Matter In Which Particles Are Widely Spaced And Move Freely With High Kinetic Energy?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Liquid ', 'Solid ', 'Plasma', 'Gas', '', ' D Explanation In the gas state of matter, particles are widely spaced and move freely with high kinetic energy. Gases do not have a definite shape or volume and will fill the entire available space.', 0, '2024-02-22 10:46:42'),
(265, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Identify The Reducing Agent In The Following Reaction:&lt;br /&gt;\r\nZn + CuSO44&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; ZnSO44&amp;nbsp;+ Cu&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Cu ', 'Â Zn', 'ZnSO44', 'CuSO4', '', 'B Explanation The reducing agent is the species that undergoes oxidation and causes the reduction of another species. In this reaction, zinc (Zn) is being oxidized to form zinc sulfate (ZnSO4 ) while reducing copper sulfate (CuSO4 ) to copper (Cu).', 0, '2024-02-22 10:48:04'),
(266, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Balance The Following Redox Reaction:&lt;br /&gt;\r\nFe22O33&amp;nbsp;+ CO &amp;rarr; Fe + CO22&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Fe22O33Â + CO â†’ 2Fe + 2CO22 ', 'Â 2Fe22O33Â + 3CO â†’ 4Fe + 3CO22 Â ', 'Fe22O33Â + 2CO â†’ 2Fe + 2CO22 ', 'Fe22O33Â + 3CO â†’ 2Fe + 3CO2', '', ' D Explanation To balance the redox reaction, we need to ensure that the number of atoms of each element and the total charge are the same on both sides of the equation. In this reaction, we can see that the number of oxygen (O) atoms is not balanced. To ', 0, '2024-02-22 10:49:54'),
(267, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Trend For Ionization Energy Across A Period In The Periodic Table?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Increases from left to right.', 'Remains Constant', 'Varies Randomly', 'Decreases From Left To Right', '', 'A Explanation Ionization energy generally increases from left to right across a period. Ionization energy is the energy required to remove an electron from a neutral atom, and as you move from left to right, the atomic size decreases, making it harder to ', 0, '2024-02-22 10:53:23'),
(268, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Type Of Chemical Combination Involves The Transfer Of Electrons From One Atom To Another, Resulting In The Formation Of Oppositely Charged Ions?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Ionic bonding ', 'Hydrogen Bonding', 'Covalent Bonding', 'Â Metallic Bonding', '', ' A Explanation Ionic bonding occurs between a metal and a non-metal. The metal atom donates one or more electrons to the non-metal atom, resulting in the formation of positively charged cations and negatively charged anions. These oppositely charged ions ', 0, '2024-02-22 10:54:39'),
(269, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Alkanes Has A Straight-chain Structure?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Cyclopentane (C5H10) ', 'Isobutane (C4H10)', '2 - Methyl Propane (C4H10)', 'Â Pentane (C5H12)', '', ' D Explanation Pentane (C5H12) is a straight-chain alkane. Alkanes are hydrocarbons with the general formula CnH2n+2. They are called straight-chain alkanes if all the carbon atoms are connected in a continuous chain without any branches. Butane and Isobu', 0, '2024-02-22 10:55:59'),
(270, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Product Of The Electrolysis Of Aqueous Sodium Chloride (NaCl) Using Inert Electrodes?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Hydrogen gas at the cathode and chlorine gas at the anode ', 'Hydrogen Gas At The Cathode And Oxygen Gas At The Anode ', 'Sodium Metal At The Cathode And Chlorine Gas At The Anode ', 'Sodium Metal At The Cathode And Oxygen Gas At The Anode', '', 'B Explanation During the electrolysis of aqueous sodium chloride using inert electrodes (such as platinum or carbon), the cations (H+ ) are attracted to the cathode and are reduced to form hydrogen gas (H2 ). The anions (OHâˆ’ ) are attracted to the anode', 0, '2024-02-22 10:57:41'),
(271, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When An Acidic Solution Is Diluted, What Happens To Its PH?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â It depends on the specific acid ', 'It Decreases', 'Â It Remains The Same', 'It Increases', '', ' D Explanation When an acidic solution is diluted by adding more solvent (usually water), the concentration of hydrogen ions (H+ ) decreases. As a result, the pH of the solution increases, making it less acidic', 0, '2024-02-22 10:58:56'),
(272, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Factors Does NOT Affect The Rate Of A Chemical Reaction?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Concentration of reactants ', 'Presence Of A Catalyst', 'Molecular Weight Of Products', 'Temperature', '', ' C Explanation The molecular weight of products is not directly related to the rate of a chemical reaction. The factors that affect the reaction rate include concentration of reactants, temperature, presence of catalysts, surface area, and the nature of t', 0, '2024-02-22 11:00:45'),
(273, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Organic Compound Is Responsible For The Characteristic Aroma Of Fruits?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Alkane', 'Alkyne', 'Ester', 'Amine', '', 'C Explanation Esters are organic compounds that have a pleasant, fruity aroma. They are responsible for the characteristic smells of fruits and many other fragrant substances.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:06:49'),
(274, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Molar Mass Of Water (H2O)?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '18 g/mol ', '22 G/Mol', '16 G/Mol', '12 G/Mol', '', 'A Explanation The molar mass of water (H2O) is calculated by adding the atomic masses of its constituent elements: 2 hydrogen atoms (each with a molar mass of approximately 1 g/mol) and 1 oxygen atom (with a molar mass of approximately 16 g/mol). Therefor', 0, '2024-02-22 11:09:39'),
(275, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Chemical Formula Of Rust, Which Is Formed On The Surface Of Iron In The Presence Of Oxygen And Moisture?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Fe33O44 B. C.Â  D.Â ', 'Â FeO', 'Fe(OH)3', 'Fe22O33', '', 'D Explanation Rust is a reddish-brown compound that forms on the surface of iron in the presence of oxygen and moisture. Its chemical formula is Fe2 O3 , indicating the presence of two iron atoms and three oxygen atoms in the compound.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:11:00'),
(276, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;How Many Pi (&amp;pi;ï¿½) Bonds Are There In An Alkene With Six Carbon Atoms?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4 B.Â  C.Â  D.Â ', '6', '5', '3', '', ' A Explanation In an alkene with six carbon atoms, there are 5 sigma (Ïƒ) bonds (single bonds) between the carbon atoms. Additionally, there are 4 pi (Ï€ ) bonds associated with the double bonds between the carbon atoms.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:12:17'),
(277, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Principal Ore Of Iron, From Which Iron Is Extracted?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Calcite ', 'Bauxite', 'Magnetite', 'Hematite', '', 'D Explanation Hematite (Fe2 O3 ) is the principal ore of iron and is widely mined for the extraction of iron metal.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:13:33'),
(278, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Group Does Calcium Belong To In The Periodic Table?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Alkaline earth metals ', 'Halogens', 'Alkali Metals', 'Noble Gases', '', ' A Explanation Calcium belongs to the alkaline earth metals group in the periodic table. It is located in Group 2 and has two valence electrons.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:14:46'),
(279, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Primary Constituent Of Crude Oil?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Pentane ', 'Â Ethanol', 'Â Heptane', 'Methane', '', 'D Explanation Crude oil is a mixture of hydrocarbons of various chain lengths. methane is one of the primary constituents of crude oil, and it belongs to the group of alkanes.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:16:04'),
(280, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Main Source Of Carbon Monoxide (CO) In Urban Areas?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Volcanic eruptions', 'Vehicle Emissions', 'Forest Fires ', 'Industrial Processes', '', 'B Explanation The main source of carbon monoxide (CO) in urban areas is vehicle emissions, especially from incomplete combustion of gasoline and diesel in engines.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:17:40'),
(281, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Empirical Formula Of A Compound Containing 40.00% Carbon, 6.67% Hydrogen, And 53.33% Oxygen By Mass?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'C4 H8 O4', 'CH2 O', 'C2 H4 O2', 'C3 H6 O3', '', ' B Explanation To determine the empirical formula, we first need to convert the percentages to moles by assuming a convenient mass for the sample. Let&apos;s assume we have 100 grams of the compound.  Mass of carbon = 40.00 grams Mass of hydrogen = 6.67 g', 0, '2024-02-22 11:20:11'),
(282, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Separation Technique Is Used To Separate Different Pigments In A Mixture Based On Their Affinity For A Stationary Phase And A Mobile Phase?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Chromatography ', 'Â Filtration', 'Decantation', 'Distillation', '', 'A Explanation Chromatography is a separation technique used to separate and analyze components of a mixture based on their differential partitioning between a stationary phase (e.g., paper or a column) and a mobile phase (e.g., solvent). Different compone', 0, '2024-02-22 11:22:34'),
(283, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Common Name For Ethanoic Acid?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Acetic acid', 'Butyric Acid', 'Propionic Acid', 'Formic Acid', '', ' A Explanation Ethanoic acid is commonly known as acetic acid. It is the main component of vinegar and is used in various industrial processes.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:24:07'),
(284, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Type Of Reaction Is Involved In The Formation Of Alkanols From Alkenes?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Elimination reaction ', 'Redox Reaction', 'Substitution Reaction', 'Â Addition Reaction', '', ' D Explanation Alkanols can be formed from alkenes through an addition reaction. In this reaction, the carbon-carbon double bond of the alkene is broken, and a hydroxyl group (-OH) is added to one of the carbon atoms, resulting in the formation of an alco', 0, '2024-02-22 11:25:28'),
(285, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Mass Percentage Of Carbon (C) In Methane (CH4)? (The Molar Mass Of Carbon Is Approximately 12 G/mol.)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 25%', '12% ', '75%', '50%', '', 'C Explanation The molar mass of methane (CH4) is calculated by adding the atomic masses of carbon (approximately 12 g/mol) and hydrogen (approximately 1 g/mol). Therefore, the molar mass of CH4 is 12 g/mol + 4 x 1 g/mol = 16 g/mol. The mass percentage of ', 0, '2024-02-22 11:26:44'),
(286, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Common Property Of Non-metals?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Exist as solids at room temperature ', 'Tend To Gain Electrons In Chemical Reactions', 'High Thermal Conductivity', 'Readily Form Cations In Chemical Reactions', '', 'B Explanation Tend to gain electrons in chemical reactions. Non-metals typically have a high electronegativity and tend to gain electrons to achieve a stable electron configuration. This results in the formation of negatively charged ions (anions) during ', 0, '2024-02-22 11:28:12'),
(287, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Symbol Used To Represent An Alpha Particle?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', ' Î±', 'Î³', ' Î´', ' Î²', '', ' A Explanation An alpha particle is represented by the Greek letter &apos;Î±&apos;. Alpha particles are a type of ionizing radiation ejected by certain types of radioactive materials. They consist of two protons and two neutrons, so they can be represente', 0, '2024-02-22 11:30:04'),
(288, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When A Substance Is Oxidized, It&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Loses electrons ', 'Â Gains Oxygen Atoms ', 'Gains Electrons', 'Loses Protons (H+ Ions)', '', 'A Explanation When a substance is oxidized, it loses electrons. Oxidation is a chemical reaction that involves the moving of electrons. Specifically, it&apos;s a process that involves the substance losing electrons. This is an old definition of oxidation,', 0, '2024-02-22 11:31:50'),
(289, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Blue Litmus Paper Turns Red When Dipped Into A Solution. What Does This Indicate About The Solution?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The solution is basic', 'The Solution Is Neutral ', 'The Solution Is Acidic', 'The Litmus Paper Is Faulty', '', 'C Explanation If a blue litmus paper turns red when dipped into a solution, it indicates the presence of an acid in the solution. Acids turn blue litmus paper red.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:33:06'),
(290, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Compounds Is An Example Of An Electrovalent Bond?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'NaCl (sodium chloride)', 'CO2 (Carbon Dioxide) ', 'Â H2O (Water)', 'CH4 (Methane)', '', ' A Explanation NaCl, commonly known as sodium chloride or table salt, is an example of an electrovalent bond. Sodium (Na) donates one electron to chlorine (Cl), resulting in the formation of Na+ and Cl- ions, which are held together by the ionic bond.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:34:42'),
(291, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If Gas A Has A Molar Mass Of 32 G/mol And Gas B Has A Molar Mass Of 64 G/mol, What Is The Ratio Of Their Diffusion Rates?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2:1 ', '1:2', '1:1', '1:4', '', 'A Explanation According to Graham&apos;s law of diffusion, the ratio of the diffusion rates of two gases is the inverse of the square root of the ratio of their molar masses. Therefore:  Rate of A / Rate of B = âˆš(Molar mass of B / Molar mass of A) Rate ', 0, '2024-02-22 11:35:48'),
(292, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Contact Process Is Used For The Industrial Production Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'sulfuric acid (H2SO4) ', 'Hydrochloric Acid (HCl) ', 'Sodium Hydroxide (NaOH)', 'Calcium Oxide (CaO)', '', 'A Explanation The contact process is used for the industrial production of sulfuric acid (H2SO4), not any of the options provided. The process involves the oxidation of sulfur dioxide (SO2) to sulfur trioxide (SO3) which is then absorbed in sulfuric acid ', 0, '2024-02-22 11:37:01'),
(293, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Unique Property Of Water Compared To Other Liquids?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'It is a poor solvent ', 'It Does Not Evaporate', 'It Expands When Freezing', 'It Has A Low Heat Capacity', '', 'C Explanation One unique property of water is that it expands when it freezes. Most substances contract and become denser when they freeze, but water expands and becomes less dense. This is why ice floats on water.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:38:23'),
(294, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Sodium Reacts Vigorously With Water To Produce&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Sodium chloride (NaCl) and oxygen gas (O2)', 'Sodium Nitrate (NaNO3) And Water (H2O)', 'Sodium Hydroxide (NaOH) And Hydrogen Gas (H2) ', 'Sodium Oxide (Na2O) And Hydrogen Gas (H2)', '', 'C Explanation When sodium reacts with water, it undergoes a highly exothermic reaction, producing sodium hydroxide (NaOH) and hydrogen gas (H2).', 0, '2024-02-22 11:39:56'),
(295, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;At Room Temperature And Standard Pressure, Chlorine Gas Is In Which State Of Matter?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Plasma ', 'Solid', 'Â Liquid', 'Gas', '', 'D Explanation Chlorine gas exists in the gaseous state at room temperature (around 25 degrees Celsius) and standard pressure.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:41:09'),
(296, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Molecular Geometry Of A Molecule With Three Bonding Pairs And No Lone Pairs Around The Central Atom?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Tetrahedral ', 'Trigonal Planar', 'Linear', 'Octahedral', '', 'B Explanation In a molecule with three bonding pairs and no lone pairs around the central atom, the electron pairs arrange themselves in a trigonal planar geometry, with bond angles of approximately 120 degrees.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:42:18'),
(297, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Isotopes Of An Element Have&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The same number of protons but different numbers of neutrons. ', 'The Same Number Of Neutrons And Electrons', 'The Same Number Of Protons And Neutrons', 'The Same Number Of Protons And Electrons', '', 'A Explanation Isotopes of an element have the same number of protons (which defines the element) but may have different numbers of neutrons. Since atoms are electrically neutral, the number of protons must equal the number of electrons in an atom.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:43:35'),
(298, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Element Is Placed At The Top Of The Electrochemical&amp;nbsp;series?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Copper ', 'Hydrogen', 'Sodium', 'Oxygen', '', 'C Explanation In the electrochemical series, also known as the reactivity series, Sodium is placed at the top. The electrochemical series is a list of elements in the order of their standard electrode potentials (or redox potentials). Elements at the top ', 0, '2024-02-22 11:45:05'),
(299, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Transition Metal Is Known For Its Multiple Colorful Oxidation States And Compounds Used In Pigments And Paints?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Silver (Ag) ', 'Copper (Cu)', 'Gold (Au)', 'Zinc (Zn)', '', 'B Explanation Copper is known for its multiple oxidation states, including +1 and +2, and its compounds are used in pigments and paints to create various colors, such as blues and greens.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:46:26'),
(300, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Methods Is Commonly Used To Remove Suspended Impurities From Water?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Fluoridation ', 'Â Chlorination', 'Filtration', 'Â Distillation', '', 'C Explanation Filtration is commonly used to remove suspended impurities, such as dirt, sand, and other particles, from water. In this process, water is passed through a filter medium that traps the solid impurities while allowing the clean water to pass ', 0, '2024-02-22 11:48:00'),
(301, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Valency Of An Element With The Electronic Configuration 2, 8, 7?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '7 ', '1', 'Â 2 ', '3', '', 'B Explanation The valency of an element is determined by the number of electrons it gains or loses to achieve a stable electron configuration. For an element with the electronic configuration 2, 8, 7, the outermost shell (valence shell) has 7 electrons. T', 0, '2024-02-22 11:49:18'),
(302, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When Anhydrous Cobalt Chloride Paper Is Exposed To Water, What Color Change Is Observed?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â From pink to blue B.Â C.Â  D.', 'From White To Blue ', 'From Blue To White', 'Â From Blue To Pink', '', 'D Explanation nhydrous cobalt chloride paper is blue in the absence of water. However, when it comes into contact with water, it undergoes a color change to pink due to the formation of hydrated cobalt chloride.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:50:42'),
(303, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Type Of Salt Is Found In Antacid Medications And Is Used To Relieve Heartburn And Indigestion?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Aluminum chloride B. C.Â  D.Â ', 'Â Magnesium Chloride', 'Sodium Chloride', 'Calcium Chloride', '', 'B Explanation Magnesium chloride is used in antacid medications to relieve heartburn and indigestion. It helps neutralize excess stomach acid.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:52:12'),
(304, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Atomic Number Of Aluminium?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '13', '26 ', '14 ', '12', '', 'A Explanation The atomic number of an element is the number of protons in the nucleus of an atom of that element. The atomic number of aluminium is 13, which means it has 13 protons in its nucleus.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:53:57'),
(305, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Metals Is Commonly Alloyed With Copper To Make Brass?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Iron ', 'Nickel ', 'Aluminum ', 'Â Zinc', '', 'D Explanation Brass is an alloy made by combining copper with zinc. It is a versatile material with a golden appearance and is used in various applications, including musical instruments, plumbing fittings, and decorative items.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:55:20'),
(306, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Happens When Alkanoic Acids React With Alcohols In The Presence Of An Acid Catalyst?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Saponification B.Â C.Â  D.Â ', 'Esterification ', 'Polymerization', 'Hydrolysis', '', 'B Explanation When alkanoic acids react with alcohols in the presence of an acid catalyst, esterification occurs. This chemical reaction forms esters and water.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:56:58'),
(307, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Functional Group Is Present In Alkanals?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Carbonyl group (C=O) ', 'Hydroxyl Group (-OH) ', 'Alkyl Group (-R)', 'Carboxyl Group (-COOH)', '', ' A Explanation The carbonyl group (C=O) is the functional group present in alkanals. It consists of a carbon atom double-bonded to an oxygen atom.', 0, '2024-02-22 11:58:43'),
(308, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;At 2.0 Atm Pressure, The Volume Of A Gas Is 4.0 L. If The Pressure Is Reduced To 1.0 Atm While Keeping The Temperature Constant, What Will Be The New Volume Of The Gas?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2.0 L ', '6.0 L', '8.0 L', '4.0 L', '', 'C Explanation According to Boyle&apos;s law, when the temperature is constant, the initial pressure multiplied by the initial volume is equal to the final pressure multiplied by the final volume. Mathematically, P1V1 = P2V2, where P1 and V1 are the initia', 0, '2024-02-22 12:00:24'),
(309, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Main Environmental Concern Associated With Sulfur Dioxide Emissions?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Formation of acid rain ', 'Global Warming Potential ', 'Depletion Of The Stratospheric Ozone ', 'Depletion Of The Ozone Layer', '', 'A Explanation Sulfur dioxide, when released into the atmosphere, can react with water vapor and other atmospheric components to form sulfuric acid (H2SO4), which contributes to the formation of acid rain. Acid rain can have harmful effects on the environm', 0, '2024-02-22 12:02:16'),
(310, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Benzene Can Be Converted To Its Derivative Toluene By The Addition Of A Methyl Group. The Reaction Is An Example Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Nucleophilic substitution', 'Elimination Reaction', 'Â Electrophilic Substitution ', 'Addition Reaction', '', 'C Explanation The conversion of benzene to toluene involves an electrophilic aromatic substitution reaction. In this reaction, a methyl group (CH3) is added to the benzene ring, replacing one of the hydrogen atoms, and the reaction proceeds through electr', 0, '2024-02-22 12:03:52'),
(311, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Why Is Water Often Referred To As The &amp;quot;universal Solvent&amp;quot;?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Water is the most abundant substance on Earth ', 'Water Is Essential For All Living Organisms.', 'Water Is Involved In Many Chemical Reactions ', 'Water Can Dissolve A Wide Variety Of Substances Due To Its Polar Nature', '', 'D Explanation Water is often referred to as the &quot;universal solvent&quot; because of its ability to dissolve a wide range of substances. This unique property is mainly due to water&apos;s polar nature. Water molecules have a slightly positive charge o', 0, '2024-02-22 12:05:47'),
(312, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Mixtures Is An Example Of A Colloid?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Milk', 'Orange Juice ', 'Saltwater', 'Sugar Dissolved In Water', '', 'A Explanation A colloid is a type of mixture where one substance is dispersed in another in the form of tiny particles that do not settle out. In milk, fat globules are dispersed in water, forming a colloid.', 0, '2024-02-22 12:07:36'),
(313, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Substances Is NOT Hygroscopic?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Salt', 'Sugar ', 'Silica Gel', 'Aluminum', '', 'D Explanation Aluminum is not hygroscopic. It does not have a strong affinity for water vapor and does not absorb moisture from the air.', 0, '2024-02-22 12:09:28'),
(314, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Mass (in Grams) Of 500 ML Of Ethanol? (density Of Ethanol = 0.789 G/mL)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '394.5 mL', '500 ML', '394.5 G', '500 G', '', 'C Explanation To calculate the mass of a substance, we can use the formula: Mass = Volume x Density Given the volume of ethanol is 500 mL and the density of ethanol is 0.789 g/mL, we can plug the values into the formula: Mass = 500 mL x 0.789 g/mL = 394.5', 0, '2024-02-22 12:11:12'),
(315, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHEMISTRY', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Heat Of Reaction Can Be Determined Experimentally Using A Device Called A&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Calorimeter ', 'Barometer ', 'Spectrometer', 'Thermometer', '', 'A Explanation A calorimeter is a device used to measure the heat of reaction experimentally. It is designed to isolate the reaction from the surroundings and measure the temperature change in the surroundings to calculate the heat exchanged.   ', 0, '2024-02-22 12:12:39');
