(364, 17, 'JAMB', 'PHYSICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Sensitivity Of A Thermometer Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'All of the above ', 'Â How Quickly A Temperature Change Can Be Detected ', 'The Difference Between The Maximum And The Minimum Temperature ', 'The Smallest Temperature Change That Can Be Detected Or Measured', '', 'D Explanation The sensitivity of a thermometer is defined as the smallest temperature change that can be detected or measured, NOT how quickly that temperature change can be detected.  In contrast, the difference between the maximum and the minimum temper', 0, '2024-02-23 10:40:45'),
(365, 17, 'JAMB', 'PHYSICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/TlrMuFZmOxdApvXNLbeGJGyF2wqvNwvKimJUBGiQ.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Diagram Above Illustrates The Penetrating Power Of Some Types Of Radiation. X, Y And Z Are Likely&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'X = Î±-particle; Y = Î³-ray; Z = Î²-particle', 'X = Î±-particle; Y = Î²-particle; Z = Î³-ray', 'X = Î³-ray; Y = Î±-particle; Z = Î²-particle', 'X = Î²-particle; Y = Î³-ray; Z = Î±-particle', '', 'C Explanation The penetrating power of alpha rays, beta rays, and gamma rays varies greatly. Alpha particles can be blocked by a few pieces of paper. Beta particles pass through paper but are stopped by aluminum foil. Gamma rays are the most difficult to ', 0, '2024-02-23 10:42:17'),
