(399, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Main Source Of Funding For Public Corporations In Nigeria?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Government budget allocations ', 'Foreign Aid', 'Revenues Generated From Their Operations', 'Donations From Private Companies', '', 'A Explanation The main source of funding for public corporations in Nigeria is Government budget allocations. Public corporations are owned and operated by the government, and their operations are funded through the government&apos;s budget. This is diffe', 0, '2024-02-23 11:31:11'),
(400, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Limitation Of Pressure Groups?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'They only represent the interests of the wealthy.  ', 'They Have No Influence On The Government Policies ', 'They May Prioritize Their Own Interests Over The Public Interest ', 'They Often Resort To Violent Tactics', '', 'C Explanation Pressure groups may prioritize their own interests over the public interest. This is because pressure groups are formed by individuals or organizations with specific interests or objectives. They aim to influence public policy and decision-m', 0, '2024-02-23 11:32:44'),
(401, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Function Of The Public Complaints&amp;nbsp;Commission?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Managing public transportation  ', 'Enforcing Criminal Laws', 'Conducting Investigations And Enquiries ', 'Â Implementing Foreign Policies', '', 'C Explanation Public commissions are responsible for conducting investigations and enquiries. They are established to investigate matters of public concern and to make recommendations based on their findings. They do not implement foreign policies, enforc', 0, '2024-02-23 11:33:56'),
(402, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Term For A System Of Government In Which Power Is Held By A Small Group Of People?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Oligarchy', 'Â Monarchy', 'Theocracy', 'Â Democracy', '', 'A Explanation An oligarchy is a system of government in which power is held by a small group of people. This can be contrasted with a democracy, where power is held by the people, or a monarchy, where power is held by a single individual.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:34:59'),
(403, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which African Country Successfully Resisted European Imperialism And Maintained Its Independence?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Ghana ', 'Ethiopia ', 'Â Kenya', 'Algeria', '', 'B Explanation Ethiopia is the African country that successfully resisted European imperialism and maintained its independence. Ethiopia was able to maintain its independence after defeating Italy at the Battle of Adwa in 1896.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:35:57'),
(404, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Feature Of Nigerian Federalism?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Single-party system B.Â  C.Â D.Â ', 'Centralized Fiscal System', 'Autonomy of local government', 'Strong Central Government', '', 'C Explanation A feature of Nigerian Federalism is the autonomy of local government. This means that local governments have the power to govern themselves in certain areas. A strong central government, a single-party system, and a centralized fiscal system', 0, '2024-02-23 11:38:08'),
(405, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Feature Of Nigerian Federalism?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Single-party system ', 'Centralized Fiscal System', 'Autonomy of local government', 'Strong Central Government', '', 'C Explanation A feature of Nigerian Federalism is the autonomy of local government. This means that local governments have the power to govern themselves in certain areas. A strong central government, a single-party system, and a centralized fiscal system', 0, '2024-02-23 11:38:27'),
(406, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If The President Refuses To Sign A Bill Within A Specific Period, It Can Still Become A Law Through&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â legislative override ', 'Â None Of The Above', 'Judicial Review', 'Public Petition', '', 'A Explanation If the president refuses to sign a bill within a specific period, it can still become a law through legislative override. This means that if a sufficient majority of the legislature votes in favor of the bill, they can override the president', 0, '2024-02-23 11:39:30'),
(407, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Document Serves As The Constitution Of The United Nations?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Universal Declaration of Human Rights', 'Â Geneva Conventions', 'Treaty Of The Non-Proliferation Of Nuclear Weapons', 'Â Charter Of The United Nations', '', 'D Explanation The document that serves as the constitution of the United Nations is the Charter of the United Nations. This document outlines the rights and obligations of member states and establishes the United Nations&apos; organs and procedures.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:40:41'),
