(411, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Nigeria Is A Founding Member Of Which Regional Organization?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'ECOWAS ', 'Non-Aligned Movement ', 'OPEC', 'IMF', '', 'A Explanation Nigeria is a founding member of the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS). ECOWAS is a regional political and economic union of fifteen countries located in West Africa. It was established on May 28, 1975, and Nigeria is one of ', 0, '2024-02-23 11:47:55'),
(412, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Current Constitution Of Nigeria Is Based On The Model Of Which Country?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Germany ', 'United States ', 'France', 'United Kingdom', '', 'B Explanation The current constitution of Nigeria is based on the model of the United States. This is evident in the structure of the government, which includes a separation of powers among three branches: the executive, the legislative, and the judicial.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:49:16'),
(413, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Arm Of Government Responsible For Budget Approval And Oversight Is The&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â judiciary ', 'Executive ', 'Administrative ', 'Legislative', '', ' D Explanation The legislative arm of government is responsible for budget approval and oversight. This is because the legislature has the power of the purse, meaning it is responsible for approving the government&apos;s budget and overseeing its implemen', 0, '2024-02-23 11:50:28'),
(414, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Key Principle Of The Socialist System Of Government Is The ___________.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'minimal government intervention in the economy ', 'Private Ownership Of The Means Of Production', 'Power Concentrated In The Hands Of A Few Elite Individuals ', 'Equality Of Opportunity And Outcome', '', 'D Explanation A key principle of the socialist system of government is the equality of opportunity and outcome. This means that in a socialist system, the government controls the means of production and wealth is distributed equally among the population t', 0, '2024-02-23 11:51:47'),
(415, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In A Communist System, Who Owns And Controls The Means Of Production?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â corporations  ', 'The Government', 'Private Individuals', 'Non-Profit Organizations', '', 'B Explanation In a communist system, the means of production are owned and controlled by the government. This is because communism advocates for a classless society where wealth and power are distributed equally among the citizens. Therefore, the governme', 0, '2024-02-23 11:53:48'),
(416, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The National Assembly Is Composed Of How Many Chambers?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Two  ', 'Four ', 'One ', 'Three', '', 'A Explanation The National Assembly in Nigeria is bicameral, meaning it is composed of two chambers: the Senate and the House of Representatives.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:54:52'),
(417, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Was A Significant Trade Commodity In The Pre-colonial Kingdom Of Benin?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ivory  ', 'Gold ', 'Rubber ', 'Salt', '', 'A Explanation Ivory was a significant trade commodity in the pre-colonial Kingdom of Benin. The Kingdom of Benin, located in modern-day Nigeria, was known for its ivory carvings, which were traded with European merchants.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:55:49'),
(418, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;__________ Was A Major Factor That Contributed To The Rise Of The Sokoto Caliphate.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Agricultural revolution. ', 'Slave Trade', 'European Colonization', 'Islamic Jihad', '', 'D Explanation Islamic Jihad was a major factor that contributed to the rise of the Sokoto Caliphate. The Sokoto Caliphate was an Islamic state in what is now northern Nigeria, led by Usman dan Fodio, who led a jihad to spread Islam in the region.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:56:49'),
(419, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Political Party Was Known For Its Socialist Ideology And Populist Policies In The 1980s?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â People&apos;s Redemption party ', 'All Nigeria&apos;s People&apos;s Party', 'National Party Of Nigeria', 'Nigerian National Democratic Party', '', 'A Explanation The People&apos;s Redemption Party was known for its socialist ideology and populist policies in the 1980s. The party was founded by Mallam Aminu Kano and was known for its commitment to representing the interests of the common people.', 0, '2024-02-23 11:58:08'),
(420, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In A Parliamentary System, The Head Of Government Is Usually The&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Chief Justice ', 'King Or Queen', 'President ', 'Prime Minister', '', 'D Explanation In a parliamentary system, the head of government is usually the Prime Minister. The Prime Minister is the leader of the political party that has the most seats in the parliament. The Prime Minister is responsible for running the government ', 0, '2024-02-23 11:59:15'),
(421, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Major Event In Nigerian History That Led To The Suspension Of Nigeria&amp;#39;s Constitution And The Declaration Of A State Of Emergency By The Colonial Authorities In 1953 Was The ________.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Aba women&apos;s riot  ', 'Zikist Movement ', 'Kano Riots ', 'Action Group Crisis', '', ' C Explanation The Kano riots were a series of violent clashes in Northern Nigeria in 1953. The riots were sparked by political and ethnic tensions over proposed reforms in the Northern House of Assembly. The British colonial authorities suspended Nigeria', 0, '2024-02-23 12:00:35'),
(422, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Countries Operate A Direct Democracy?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Russia ', 'United Kingdom', 'United States Of America ', 'Switzerland', '', 'D Explanation Switzerland operates a direct democracy. In a direct democracy, citizens have the right to vote on every issue that affects them, rather than their elected representatives making those decisions. This is different from a representative democ', 0, '2024-02-23 12:01:39'),
(423, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Civil Service In Nigeria Operates Under The Principle Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'autonomy  ', 'Separation Of Powers', 'None Of The Above', 'Meritocracy', '', ' D Explanation The civil service in Nigeria operates under the principle of meritocracy. This means that positions and promotions in the civil service are based on merit, rather than factors such as political affiliation or personal connections. This is i', 0, '2024-02-23 12:09:22'),
(424, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Commonwealth Of Nations Was Initially Known As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'British Commonwealth  ', 'Imperial Commonwealth', 'Commonwealth Realm ', 'League Of Nations', '', 'A Explanation The Commonwealth of Nations was initially known as the British Commonwealth. It was created as a way for countries that were formerly part of the British Empire to maintain political, economic, and social connections.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:11:03'),
(425, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Nigeria Shares Its Longest Border With Which West African Country?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Niger ', 'Chad ', 'Ghana ', 'Benin', '', 'A Explanation Nigeria shares its longest border with Niger. The border between Nigeria and Niger is approximately 1,497 kilometers long, making it Nigeria&apos;s longest international border.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:11:56'),
(426, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Electoral System Used In Nigeria Is Primarily Based On __________&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'mixed-member proportional  ', 'Preferential Voting', 'First-Past-The-Post ', 'Proportional Representation', '', 'C Explanation The electoral system used in Nigeria is primarily based on the first-past-the-post system. This means that the candidate with the most votes in an election wins, regardless of whether they have a majority of the total votes. This system is u', 0, '2024-02-23 12:13:06'),
(427, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Nigerian Leader Advocated For The New Partnership For Africa&amp;#39;s Development(NEPAD)?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Olusegun Obasanjo ', 'Yakubu Gowon', 'Muhammadu Buhari ', 'Shehu Shagari', '', 'A Explanation The New Partnership for Africa&apos;s Development (NEPAD) was advocated for by Olusegun Obasanjo, who was the President of Nigeria from 1999 to 2007. NEPAD is a socio-economic development tool of the African Union that aims to provide an ove', 0, '2024-02-23 12:15:09'),
(428, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which African Country Experienced A Violent Resistance Movement Against British Colonial Rule Known As The Mau Mau Rebellion?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Sudan  ', 'Kenya ', 'Ghana ', 'Nigeria', '', 'B Explanation The Mau Mau rebellion was a military conflict that took place in British Kenya between 1952 and 1960. It was a violent resistance movement against British colonial rule. The Mau Mau, a secret society that was predominantly Kikuyu, initiated ', 0, '2024-02-23 12:16:17'),
(429, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Public Corporations And Parastatals Are Typically Established By&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'private individuals  ', 'Legislative Acts And Statutes ', 'Trade Unions', 'International Organizations', '', 'B Explanation Public corporations and parastatals are typically established by legislative acts and statutes. These are government-owned entities created to undertake commercial activities on behalf of the government.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:17:29'),
(430, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Civil Servants Are Typically Protected By&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Military forces and security agencies ', 'Civil Service Commission', 'Trade Union And Labour Laws', 'Human Rights Organizations', '', 'B Explanation Civil servants are typically protected by the Civil Service Commission. The Civil Service Commission is a government agency that is responsible for the appointment, promotion, and discipline of civil servants.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:22:57'),
(431, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Judiciary Checks The Other Arms Of Government Through&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Judicial recall ', 'Judicial Precedence ', 'Judicial Review', 'Judicial Oversight', '', 'C Explanation The judiciary checks the other arms of government through judicial review. Judicial review is a process under which executive and legislative actions are subject to review by the judiciary. This is a key aspect of the separation of powers.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:24:03'),
(432, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Primary Source Of Revenue For The Local Government In Nigeria?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'taxes  ', 'Grants From Foreign Countries', 'Oil Revenue ', 'Â Federal Government Allocations', '', 'D Explanation The primary source of revenue for local governments in Nigeria is the Federal government allocations. This is because a significant portion of the revenue generated by the country is distributed among the three tiers of government - federal,', 0, '2024-02-23 12:25:08'),
(433, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Jus Sanguinis Is A Principle That Grants Citizenship Based On&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'parental citizenship  ', 'Place Of Birth', 'Ethnic Background ', 'Length Of Residency', '', 'A Explanation Jus Sanguinis is a principle of nationality law by which citizenship is determined or acquired by the nationality or ethnicity of one or both parents. This contrasts with jus soli, which is a principle by which citizenship is determined by p', 0, '2024-02-23 12:26:52'),
(434, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;which Pre-colonial Nigerian Kingdom Was Known For Its Artistic And Cultural Achievement?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Nupe ', 'Igbo ', 'Kanem-Bornu ', 'Benin', '', 'D Explanation The Benin Kingdom, in pre-colonial Nigeria, was known for its artistic and cultural achievements. The kingdom was renowned for its brass sculptures, its ivory carvings, and its palace architecture. The Benin Kingdom&apos;s art was so highly ', 0, '2024-02-23 12:28:00'),
(435, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Nigeria&amp;#39;s Foreign Policy Is Guided By The Principle Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'military dominance  ', 'Â Economic Self-Sufficiency', 'Â National Interest ', 'Territorial Expansion', '', 'C Explanation Nigeria&apos;s foreign policy is guided by the principle of national interest. This means that the country&apos;s foreign relations and actions are primarily based on what is beneficial or of interest to the nation. This could be in terms of', 0, '2024-02-23 12:29:15'),
(436, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Nigerian Constitution Guarantees Freedom Of Speech Under Which Fundamental Right?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Right to freedom of thought  ', 'Â Right To Privacy ', 'Right To Freedom Of Expression ', 'Right To Life', '', 'C Explanation The Nigerian constitution guarantees freedom of speech under the Right to freedom of expression. This right allows individuals to express their thoughts, ideas, and opinions without fear of government restraint.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:30:24'),
(437, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Term &amp;#39;lobbying&amp;#39; Refers To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'campaigning for political office  ', 'Advocating For Social Justice', 'Organizing Grassroots Movements', 'Seeking To Influence Government Decisions', '', 'D Explanation The term &apos;lobbying&apos; refers to the act of seeking to influence government decisions. This is typically done by pressure groups who try to persuade government officials to make decisions that favor their cause.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:31:33'),
(438, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Characteristic Of Pressure Groups?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'They aim to gain political power  ', 'They Are Funded By The Government', 'They Are Political Parties ', 'They Represent The Interest Of A Specific Section Of The Society', '', 'D Explanation Pressure groups are organizations that aim to influence public policy or legislation in a way that benefits their specific interests. They represent the interest of a specific section of the society, not the entire society. They are not poli', 0, '2024-02-23 12:32:38'),
(439, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Oputa Panel Was Established In Nigeria To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'monitor military spending ', 'Facilitate Arms Trades Regulations', 'Investigate Human Rights Abuses During The Military Rule ', 'Promote Military Intervention In Politics', '', 'C Explanation The Oputa panel, officially known as the Human Rights Violations Investigation Commission, was established in Nigeria in 1999 to investigate human rights abuses during the military rule. The panel was tasked with investigating abuses from 19', 0, '2024-02-23 12:38:24'),
(440, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Without Presidential Assent, The Legislature Can Pass A Bill Into Law With The Votes Of ______ Majority&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'one-fifth ', 'Two-Third ', 'Â One-Third', 'Absolute', '', 'B Explanation Without presidential assent, the legislature can pass a bill into law with the votes of two-third majority. This is a provision in many democratic constitutions to ensure that the executive does not have absolute veto power over legislation.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:39:16'),
(441, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Institution Is Responsible For The Regulation And Supervision Of Capital Markets In Nigeria?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Nigerian Stock Exchange(NSE)  ', 'Securities And Exchange Commission(SEC) ', 'Financial Reporting Council Of Nigeria(FRCN) ', 'Corporate Affairs Commission(CAC)', '', 'B Explanation The Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) is the main regulatory institution of the Nigerian capital market. It is responsible for regulating and developing the Nigerian capital market. Its main function is to protect investors and ensure', 0, '2024-02-23 12:40:24'),
(442, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Zoning System In Nigerian Politics Refers To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â the rotation of power among different regions', 'The Process Of Selecting Party Leaders', 'The Allocation Of Campaign Funds ', 'The System Of Proportional Representation', '', 'A Explanation The zoning system in Nigerian politics refers to the rotation of power among different regions. This is a political arrangement to ensure that political power is not monopolized by a particular region, but is rotated among different regions ', 0, '2024-02-23 12:41:25'),
(443, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Judges In The International Court Of Justice Are Appointed For A Period Of _____ Years.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'twelve ', 'Five ', 'Four', 'Nine', '', 'D Explanation Judges in the International Court of Justice are appointed for a period of nine years. The International Court of Justice, also known as the World Court, is the main judicial organ of the United Nations. It settles legal disputes submitted b', 0, '2024-02-23 12:42:20'),
(444, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The 1963 Constitution Created A List Of Powers Exclusively Reserved For The&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Federal government  ', 'State Governments ', 'Regional Governments', 'Â Local Governments', '', 'A Explanation The 1963 constitution of Nigeria created a list of powers that were exclusively reserved for the Federal government. These powers included defense, foreign affairs, and the economy. The regional governments were given powers over areas such ', 0, '2024-02-23 12:43:28'),
(445, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When Africa Is The Centrepiece Of Nigeria&amp;#39;s Foreign Policy, It Is Said To Be _________&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Afrocentric ', 'Regional ', 'Concentric ', 'Pan-African', '', 'A Explanation When Africa is the centerpiece of Nigeria&apos;s foreign policy, it is said to be Afrocentric. This means that the policy is centered on African issues and values, and prioritizes African unity and interests.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:44:18'),
(446, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Electoral Commission That Organized The 1979 General Elections Was&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'FEDECO  ', 'INEC ', 'ECN ', 'NECON', '', 'A Explanation The electoral commission that organized the 1979 general elections was FEDECO (Federal Electoral Commission). This body was established in 1976 during the military regime of General Olusegun Obasanjo, and it conducted the elections that led ', 0, '2024-02-23 12:45:15'),
(447, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Process Of Forming Public Opinion Is Known As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'polling ', 'Socialization', 'Mobilization', 'Persuasion', '', 'B Explanation The process of forming public opinion is known as socialization. This is the process through which individuals acquire the knowledge, language, social skills, and values to conform to the norms and roles required for integration into a group', 0, '2024-02-23 12:46:30'),
(448, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Nigeria&amp;#39;s Foreign Policy Is Influenced By Its Position As A Major Exporter Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'military equipments ', 'Â Natural Resources ', 'Â Agricultural Products', 'Technology', '', 'B Explanation Nigeria&apos;s foreign policy is influenced by its position as a major exporter of natural resources. Nigeria is known for its vast natural resources, especially crude oil, which significantly influences its foreign relations and policy deci', 0, '2024-02-23 12:47:33'),
(449, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Constitution Established The Public Service Commission?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â The 1963 constitution  ', 'The 1979 Constitution', 'Â The 1999 Constitution', 'The 1989 Constitution', '', ' B Explanation The Public Service Commission was established by the 1979 constitution of Nigeria. The commission is responsible for the appointment, promotion, and discipline of public officers in Nigeria.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:48:58'),
(450, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Statements About Pressure Groups Is True?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'They have no influence on the decision-making process  ', 'They Can Have Both Positive And Negative Impact On The Government', 'They Operate Independently Of The Government ', 'They Are Only Concerned With Social Issues', '', 'B Explanation Pressure groups can have both positive and negative impacts on the government. On the positive side, they can bring important issues to the attention of the government and the public. On the negative side, they can exert undue influence on t', 0, '2024-02-23 12:50:16'),
(451, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Public Opinion Refers To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'the opinion of majority of the people in a society ', 'The Opinion Of The Media ', 'The Opinion Of Political Leaders', 'The Opinion Of Intellectuals And Scholars', '', ' A Explanation Public opinion refers to the opinion of the majority of the people in a society. It is the collective opinion or attitude of the public towards a particular issue or topic. It is often used to gauge the public&apos;s views and attitudes tow', 0, '2024-02-23 12:51:21'),
(452, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Process Of Decolonization In Nigeria Was Hugely Impacted By&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The Renaissance ', 'Â World War I', 'The Cold War', 'World War II', '', 'D Explanation The process of decolonization in Nigeria was hugely impacted by World War II. The war led to a change in the attitudes of colonial powers and the colonized people. The colonized people were more assertive in their demand for independence, an', 0, '2024-02-23 12:52:30'),
(453, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is A Concurrent Power In The Nigerian Federal System?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Currency and coinage  ', 'Â Education And Healthcare', 'Â Foreign Affairs And International Relations', 'Defense And National Security', '', 'B Explanation In a federal system of government, concurrent powers are powers that are shared by both the federal and state governments. In the context of Nigeria, Education and Healthcare are examples of such powers. Defense and National security, Curren', 0, '2024-02-23 12:53:38'),
(454, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Proportional Representation&amp;nbsp;electoral System, Seats In The Legislature Are Allocated Based On&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â primary elections  Â ', 'Â Political Party Membership', 'The Percentage Of Votes A Party Receives ', 'A Winner-Takes-All System', '', 'C Explanation In a proportional representation electoral system, seats in the legislature are allocated based on the percentage of votes a party receives. This system is designed to ensure that the proportion of seats a party has in the legislature reflec', 0, '2024-02-23 12:54:50'),
(455, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When&amp;nbsp;an Election Fails To Produce A Clear Winner, The Process Of Determining A Winner Is Called&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â a recall  ', 'A Re-Run Election', 'A Bye-Election', 'A Referendum', '', 'B Explanation When an election fails to produce a clear winner, the process of determining a winner is called a re-run election. This is a second election conducted to determine a clear winner when the first election was inconclusive.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:55:52'),
(456, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Committee Is Responsible For The Detailed Scrutiny Of A Bill?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ad hoc committee ', 'Standing Committee ', 'Joint Committee ', 'Select Committee', '', 'D Explanation A Select Committee is responsible for the detailed scrutiny of a bill. They are small legislative bodies that are set up to investigate specific issues or bills. The committee members are usually experts in the bill&apos;s subject matter.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:57:14'),
(457, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Constitutional Amendment Introduced The Six Geopolitical Zones In Nigeria?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Sixth Amendment ', 'Fourth Amendment', 'Fifth Amendment', 'None Of The Above', '', 'D Explanation The concept of six geopolitical zones in Nigeria is not a constitutional provision. It was created for administrative convenience and does not have any backing in the Nigerian constitution. Therefore, none of the options is correct.', 0, '2024-02-23 12:58:24'),
(458, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Arm Of Government Has The Power To Declare Laws Unconstitutional?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Judiciary ', 'Legislature ', 'Â Executive ', 'Parliament', '', 'A Explanation The Judiciary arm of government has the power to declare laws unconstitutional. This is because the Judiciary interprets the law and has the constitutional authority to declare a law unconstitutional if it violates the provisions of the cons', 0, '2024-02-23 12:59:28'),
(459, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Political Party That Advocates For Social Equality, Workers&amp;#39; Rights And Wealth Redistribution Is Most Likely Aligned With Which Ideology&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â liberalism', 'Socialism ', 'Â Conservatism ', 'Libertarianism', '', 'B Explanation Socialism is a political ideology that advocates for social equality, workers&apos; rights, and wealth redistribution. Socialists believe in a system where the means of production, such as factories and farms, are owned and controlled by the', 0, '2024-02-23 13:00:39'),
(460, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Gerontocracy Is A Form Of Government In Which Power Is Held By&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'military junta  ', 'Â A Single Ruler', 'Religious Leaders', 'Â The Old', '', 'D Explanation Gerontocracy is a form of government in which power is held by the old. The term comes from the Greek words geron, &apos;old man&apos;, and kratos, &apos;rule&apos;. It is a political structure where the government is ruled by leaders who ar', 0, '2024-02-23 13:01:42'),
(461, 17, 'JAMB', 'COMPUTER SCIENCE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of A Public Pressure Group?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Red cross  ', 'Â Amnesty International ', 'National Farmers Union ', 'Green Peace', '', 'D Explanation Green Peace is an example of a public pressure group. Public pressure groups are those that seek to achieve their objectives by influencing public opinion and policy. Green Peace does this by advocating for environmental issues.', 0, '2024-02-23 13:02:52'),
(462, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Who Amongst The Following Did Not Serve As Secretary General Of The League Of Nations?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Josip Broz Tito  ', 'Sean Lester ', 'Joseph Avenoi', 'Eric Drummond', '', 'A Explanation Josip Broz Tito did not serve as secretary general of the League of Nations. He was a Yugoslav communist revolutionary and statesman, serving in various roles from 1943 until his death in 1980. The League of Nations was an intergovernmental ', 0, '2024-02-23 13:04:08'),
(463, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Nigerian Leader Played A Significant Role In Mediating Peace Talks During The Liberian Civil War?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Olusegun Obasanjo ', 'Muhammadu Buhari ', 'Goodluck Jonathan ', 'Â Ibrahim Babangida', '', 'A Explanation Former Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo played a significant role in mediating peace talks during the Liberian civil war. He was instrumental in the negotiations that led to the end of the war and the establishment of a transitional gove', 0, '2024-02-23 13:05:25'),
(464, 17, 'JAMB', 'GOVERNMENT', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Under General Aguiyi Ironsi, Decree 34 Introduced The ____ System Of Government.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'unitary  ', 'Confederal', 'Federal ', 'None Of The Above', '', 'A Explanation Under General Aguiyi Ironsi, Decree 34 introduced the unitary system of government in Nigeria. This decree abolished the federal structure of the country and replaced it with a unitary system. A unitary system of government is a form of gove', 0, '2024-02-23 13:06:23'),
(465, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Tariff Is A Tax Imposed On&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Consumer goods ', 'Domestic Goods ', 'Â Imported Goods ', 'Exported Goods', '', 'C Explanation A tariff is a tax that a country imposes on its imports, sometimes to protect domestic industries from foreign competition. Therefore, the correct answer is &apos;Imported goods&apos;.', 0, '2024-02-28 11:43:27'),
(466, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Demand For A Good Is Price Inelastic If&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The price elasticity is less than one ', 'The Price Elasticity Is One ', 'The Price Elasticity Is Negative', 'The Price Elasticity Is Greater Than One', '', 'A Explanation Inelastic demand occurs when a change in demand is less than proportionate change in price. Inelastic demand is less than 1 i.e e &lt; 1', 0, '2024-02-28 11:45:32'),
(467, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of Free Good?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Free education ', 'Water In The Ocean', 'Dinner You Did Not Pay For ', 'Your Rented Apartment', '', 'B Explanation Free goods are goods whether consumer goods or productive inputs, which are useful but not scarce i.e. they are in sufficiently abundant supply that all agents can have as much of them as they wish at zero social opportunity cost e.g. air, w', 0, '2024-02-28 11:47:32'),
(468, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Marginal Propensity To Consume Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Options A, B and C B.Â C.Â  D.Â ', 'Î”C/Î”Y ', 'The Slope Of The Consumption Function', 'Coefficient C In The Equation C = C + CYd', '', 'A Explanation The marginal propensity to consume is the ratio of change in consumption to change in income. It is mathematically represented as: MPC = âˆ†C/âˆ†Y and also the consumption function is represented as C = a +bYd ( C = C + cYd) where the b(c) i', 0, '2024-02-28 11:50:14'),
(469, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Short Run Can Be Defined As The Period Of Time During Which&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'All inputs are fixed ', 'At Least One Of The Firm&apos;s Input Is Fixed', 'At Least Two Inputs Are Fixed', 'All Inputs Are Variable', '', 'B Explanation A short run period is a period of time in which some input factors are fixed and some are variable. In the short run, it is impossible for the producer to vary the quantity of some inputs.', 0, '2024-02-28 11:52:39'),
(470, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The &amp;quot;velocity&amp;quot; Of Money Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The real money supply divided by the real GDP ', 'Â The Money Supply Multiplied By The Price Level ', 'The Money Supply Divided By The Price Level', 'The Ratio Of Real GDP To The Real Money Supply', '', 'D Explanation Velocity of money is the total amount of money in circulation in an economy. It is calculated as Velocity of money = GDP/Money Supply', 0, '2024-02-28 11:54:18'),
(471, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Part Of Income After Tax That Is Not Consumed Is Defined As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Wages and salaries ', 'Saving ', 'Capital Investment ', 'Nondurable Goods Expenditure', '', 'B Explanation The part of income after tax that is not consumed is defined as saving. This is because when income is earned, it is either used for consumption or saved. Therefore, if it is not consumed, it is saved. Capital investment, wages and salaries,', 0, '2024-02-28 11:55:44'),
(472, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;An Industry Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'A group of firms producing differentiated products  ', 'A Group Of Firms Producing Distinct Commodities ', 'A Group Of Firms Producing Related Goods', 'A Group Of Firms Producing Unrelated Goods', '', 'C Explanation An industry is a group of firms producing similar products and under separate administration or management.', 0, '2024-02-28 11:57:11'),
(473, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Type Of Unemployment That Occurs When An Individual Cannot Find Job As A Result Of Obsolete Skill Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Structural unemployment', 'Â Cyclical Unemployment', 'Seasonal Unemployment', 'Frictional Unemployment', '', 'A Explanation Structural unemployment occurs when production structure changes or changes in demand or technology. It also occurs when a worker loses job because their jobs are transferred to other countries.', 0, '2024-02-28 11:58:35'),
(474, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Theory Of ............... Was Propounded By ..................&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Comparative advantage; Mercantilists', 'Â Absolute Advantage; Adam Smith ', 'Comparative Advantage; Adam Smith', 'Absolute Advantage; David Ricardo', '', 'B Explanation The theory of absolute advantage was propounded by Adam Smith while the theory of comparative advantage was propounded by David Ricardo.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:00:33'),
(475, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If A Business&amp;#39; Total Economic Cost Of Producing 10,000 Units Of A Product Is N750,000 And This Output Is Sold To Consumers For N1,000,000, Then The Firm Would Earn&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â A normal profit of N750,000 ', 'Â An Economic Profit Of N750,000 ', 'A Normal Profit O N1,750,000', 'An Economic Profit Of N250,000', '', 'D Explanation Economic profit = Total revenue(Output) - Opportunity cost of input = 1,000,000 - 750,000 = 250,000   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:01:57'),
(476, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;One Major Problem Facing West African Countries Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Relations with Colonial Masters ', 'Joint Military Operations In Member States ', 'Political Integration', 'Financial Crunch Of Member States', '', 'A Explanation One of the major problem of West African state is the relation of West African states with the colonial masters.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:03:09'),
(477, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Development Of An Economic Hypothesis Through Intuition, Insight, Or Logic Is Associated With&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Deduction ', 'Policy Economics', 'Normative Economics ', 'Induction', '', 'C Explanation Normative economics is a perspective on economics that reflects normative, or ideologically prescriptive judgments toward economic development, investment projects, statements, and scenarios. It expresses ideological judgments about what may', 0, '2024-02-28 12:04:59'),
(478, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Major Factor Contributing To Productivity Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Immigration of young workers ', 'The Labour Force ', 'The Baby Boom Of Generation ', 'The Rate Of GDP Per Year', '', 'B Explanation Labour is by far the most common of the factors used in measuring productivity. One reason for this is, of course, the relatively large share of labour costs in the value of most products.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:06:31'),
(479, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;.............is Presently Used In Nigeria To Measure Inflation&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'GNP implicit price deflator ', 'Consumer Price Index', 'Wholesale Price Index', 'Real Gross Domestic Product', '', 'B Explanation In Nigeria, the Consumer Price Index (CPI) is used to measure inflation. The CPI measures the average change over time in the prices paid by urban consumers for a market basket of consumer goods and services. It is the most widely used measu', 0, '2024-02-28 12:08:03'),
(480, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Fundamental Problem Of Economics Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Finding striking determinants between the forces of supply and demand', 'The Scarcity Of Productive Resources Relative To Society&apos;s Unlimited Wants ', 'The Establishment Of A Political Framework To Determine The What, How And For Whom Of Production', 'To Establish An Equitable Distribution Of Income', '', 'B Explanation The fundamental problem of Economics is Scarcity. Scarcity explains the basic economic problem that the world has limited or scarce resources to meet seemingly unlimited wants, and this reality forces people to make decisions about how to al', 0, '2024-02-28 12:09:56'),
(481, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/yp0NilMk5hvognwR8mmsqRM9GiOtegWTNVmOS12a.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Diagram Above Represent&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â perfect competition', 'Mononpoly ', 'Â Demand Curve ', 'Competitive Market', '', ' B Explanation The diagram above represent a monopolist diagram.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:11:41'),
(482, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/lk502iHbAF1SDF4NdGBY1WjIm7tXCICx2V5afhnc.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;What Is The Lowest Price The Monopolist Can Charge&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â P2 ', 'P1', 'Â P3', 'Â P4', '', 'A Explanation The monopolist can charge P2 price and still make profit as long as he covers his AVC. Any price below price P2, the monopoly will run at loss or shut down.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:13:00'),
(483, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/J5lRy5quHQXSO4dhRxbNsBm2SxjSGPFTaOZoPfn7.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Maximum Price Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â P1', 'Â P2 ', 'P3 ', 'P4', '', 'D Explanation The highest price is P4 the monopoly can charge.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:14:51'),
(484, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Real Cost Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Alternative commodities forgone', 'Â Amount Of Money Spent On Goods And Services', 'Cost Of Goods And Services ', 'Â True Cost', '', 'C Explanation Real cost is the cost of producing a good or service, including the cost of all resources used and the cost of not employing those resources in alternative uses.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:15:57'),
(485, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;..................... Is The Highest Body In ECOWAS Organogram&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Authority of Head of State and Government ', 'The Executive Secretariat', 'The Defense Council', 'Â Council Of Ministers', '', 'A Explanation The authority of heads of state and government is the foremost, and the highest authority of the organization. It is made up of heads of state and government within the sub-region. This organ is headed by a chairman, who holds office for one', 0, '2024-02-28 12:17:10'),
(486, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Government Uses All Of The Following Ways To Redistribute Income, Except&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Market intervention ', 'Â Transfer Earnings', 'Limited Liability ', 'Taxation', '', ' C Explanation Limited liability is not a mechanism Government use to redistribute income. Government redistribute income in the following ways: taxation, welfare, public services, land reform, monetary policies etc.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:18:45'),
(487, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Principle That Specified That The Amount, When And How To Pay Tax Should Be Made Known To Tax Payer Is Known As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Principle of economy', 'Principle Of Convenience', 'Principle Of Simplicity', 'Principle Of Certainty', '', 'D Explanation The principle of certainty states that a tax should be certain and clear to everybody concerned. The time of payment, the manner of payment and the amount to be paid should be clear and plain to the tax payer.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:20:15'),
(488, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Money Could Be Defined As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Options A, B and C  ', 'Â Medium Of Exchange', 'Settlement Of Debt', 'Â Medium Of Payment', '', 'A Explanation Money can be defined as anything that is generally acceptable as a medium of exchange (means of payment) and in the settlement of debt. It can also be defined as a medium of exchange recognized by law.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:21:33'),
(489, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Business Cycle Is Associated With&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Recession  ', 'Unemployment ', 'Seasonal Variation ', 'Inflation', '', 'A Explanation Business cycle are intervals of expansion followed by recession in economic activity. It is characterized by general upswings and downturns in a span of macroeconomics variable.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:22:45'),
(490, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Economic Problem Occurs When&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'There is scarcity relative to demand  ', 'All Raw Materials Are Imported', 'Many People Are Out Of Work ', 'There Are No Buyers For Our Goods', '', 'A Explanation Scarcity explains the basic economic problem that the world has limited or scarce resoures to meet seemingly unlimited wants, and this reality forces people to make decisions about how to allocate resources in the most efficient way.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:24:03'),
(491, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A ............ In The Price Of The Domestic Currency In Terms Of A Foreign Currency Is Referred To As .............&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Decrease, appreciation', 'Â Increase, De-Appreciation ', 'Decrease, Depreciation ', 'Â Increase, Consolidation', '', 'C Explanation Currency depreciation is a fall in the value of a currency in a floating exchange rate system. Therefore, a decrease in the price of the domestic currency in terms of a foreign currency is referred to as depreciation.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:25:17'),
(492, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Among All The Determinants Of Economic Growth, The Most Important One Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Human capital  ', 'Increased GDP ', 'Â Land And Natural Resources ', 'Technologies', '', 'B Explanation The Gross Domestic Product is the total monetary or market value of all the goods and services produced within a country. It is used to measure the rate of growth in an economy.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:26:38'),
(493, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;An Increase In Money Income With Constant Price Results In&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Outward shift in the budget line  ', 'Â Inward Parallel Shift In The Budget Line ', 'Options A And C ', 'Budget Line Remain Constant', '', 'A Explanation If the income of consumer changes (upward or downward), the aggregate satisfaction of the consumer would also change (upward or downward) provided the prices remain the same. An increase in consumers&apos; income will shift the budget line o', 0, '2024-02-28 12:28:01');
INSERT INTO `past_question` (`id`, `user_id`, `exam_body`, `subject`, `exam_year`, `question`, `option_a`, `option_b`, `option_c`, `option_d`, `option_e`, `correct_answer`, `publish`, `created_at`) VALUES
(494, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Law Of Supply States That, Other Things Being Constant, As Price Increases&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Supply increases ', 'Supply Decreases', 'Quantity Supplied Increases', 'Quantity Supplied Decreases', '', 'C Explanation The law of supply says that a higher price will induce producers to supply a higher quantity to the market i.e. the higher the price, the greater the quantity supplied and vice versa.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:29:20'),
(495, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Demand For Money Will Fall If&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â People expect deflation soon', 'Real GDP Rises ', 'Real Interest Rates Rise', 'The GDP Deflator Rises', '', 'C Explanation If GDP falls, then people demand less money for transactions. As interest rate rise (fall), the demand for money will fall(rise).', 0, '2024-02-28 12:30:40'),
(496, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is An Example Of Expansionary Monetary Policy By The Central Bank Of Nigeria?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Lowering income taxes ', 'Â Increasing The Discount Rate', 'Increasing The Reserve Ratio ', 'Buying Treasury Securities From Commercial Banks', '', ' D Explanation Expansionary monetary policy is used to increase the money supply in an economy. When the Central bank buys securities, it aims to expand the volume of money in circulation and where there is too much money in circulation, the CBN will sell', 0, '2024-02-28 12:32:13'),
(497, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If Commodities X And Y Are Substitute, Their Cross Elasticity Of Demand Will Be&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'One ', 'Positive', 'Negative ', 'Zero', '', ' B Explanation Cross elasticity of demand measures the responsiveness of the quantity demanded of one good to a change in the price of another good. If two goods are substitutes, an increase in the price of one will lead to an increase in demand for the o', 0, '2024-02-28 12:33:52'),
(498, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Term &amp;#39;investment&amp;#39; In Macroeconomics Means&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Profit ', 'Total Amount Of Money Invested In Bonds And Stocks ', 'The Total Amount Of Capital Goods In The Country ', 'The Production Of Goods For Immediate Consumption', '', 'D Explanation Investment is an activity of spending resources on creating assets that can generate income over a long period of time. It is flow of expenditures developed to projects producing goods which are intended for immediate consumption.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:35:29'),
(499, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Following Are Economic Agents In Any Economy EXCEPT&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Central Bank ', 'Â House Hold ', 'Firm', 'Â Government', '', 'A Explanation Economic agents are entities that make economic decisions. They include households, firms, and the government. The Central Bank, while an important institution, is not considered an economic agent as it does not make decisions about what, ho', 0, '2024-02-28 12:37:14'),
(500, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;One Major Criticism Of Foreign Aid To Developing Countries Is That It&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Gives too much power and control to world bank ', 'Encourages Growth In Government Bureaucracy ', 'Â Is Capital Using Rather Than Capital Saving ', 'Provides Incentives For Capital Flight', '', 'C Explanation The loans help to create poverty, as capital that could have been invested instead was channeled into debt repayment.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:39:18'),
(501, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Public Corporation Is Financed With&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Capital raised from shareholders  ', 'Tax Payer&apos;s Money', 'Capital Raised From Stock Exchange ', 'Capital Contributed By Owners', '', 'B Explanation Public corporations are run by the government through the tax paid by the people. They are established by an act of parliament or decree and it is controlled by the board of directors, appointed by the government.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:41:00'),
(502, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Type Of Price Elasticity Of Demand For A Commodity Whose Quantity Demanded Remain Unchanged Despite Changes In The Price Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Perfectly elastic ', 'Infinitely Elastic ', 'Inelastic ', 'Perfectly Inelastic', '', 'D Explanation Perfectly inelastic demand is also known as Zero elasticity demand. Zero elasticity of demand is one when whatever the change in price, there is absolutely no change in demand.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:42:49'),
(503, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;An Increase In Total Production (real GDP) Causes The Demand For Money To ______and The Interest Rate To _________&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Increase; decrease ', 'Â Decrease; Decrease', 'Increase; Increase', 'Decrease; Increase', '', 'C Explanation An increase in the real GDP will increase the demand for money and also the interest rate will also increase.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:44:55'),
(504, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Part-time Workers Who Desire Full-time Employment Are:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Underemployed and contribute to the unemployment statistic', 'Â Underemployed But Do Not Contribute To The Unemployment Statistic ', 'Â Not Part Of The Labour Force And Do Not Contribute To The Unemployment Statistic ', 'Cyclical Unemployment', '', 'B Explanation Underemployment includes three groups of people which are: Unemployment workers, Involuntary part-time workers and marginally attached workers. There is currently no data that track this form of unemployment.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:47:29'),
(505, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is The Resultant Effect Of A Fall In The Profit Margin Of Producers In An Economy?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Unemployment will fall ', 'Unemployment Will Remain Constant ', 'Unemployment Will Increase ', 'Unemployment Will Fluctuate', '', 'C Explanation In general, Okun&apos;s findings demonstrated that when unemployment falls, the production of a country will increase and vice versa.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:49:20'),
(506, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Indicator Of Underdevelopment Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'high life expectancy ', 'Â Low Birth Rate ', 'Low Population Growth Rate ', 'Low Per Capita Income', '', 'D Explanation The indicators of underdevelopment include: high birth rates, high infant mortality, low per capita GDP, high levels of illiteracy, and low life expectancy.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:50:59'),
(507, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Decision To Consume More Of One Product Under Normal Circumstances Will Apply&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â less of another product will be consumed  ', 'More Of Another Product Will Be Consumed', '.Â Less Of The Product Will Be Consumed', 'No Other Products Will Be Consumed', '', 'A Explanation Getting more of one commodity allows a consumer to demand less of the other product. The demand for substitute products shows a negative correlation. That is, consumption of one product reduces or replaces the need for the other.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:52:55'),
(508, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Identify One Of The Following Which Can NOT Be Used To Close Deflationary Gap&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Increased interest rate ', 'Increased Money Supply ', 'Â Increase Government Expenditure', 'Reduction In Taxes', '', ' A Explanation - Monetary policy is implemented by reducing the interest rates in the economy in order to increase the supply of money to enhance growth.  - The fiscal policy is implemented by the reduction of taxes and increasing government spending in o', 0, '2024-02-28 12:54:29'),
(509, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;An Increase In Nominal Income Without Increase In Price Will Result To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â increased real income ', 'Increased GDP', 'Decreased Real Income', 'Decreased GNP', '', 'A Explanation When nominal income increases without any change to prices, this means consumers can purchase more goods at the same price, and for most goods, consumers will demand more.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:55:48'),
(510, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If Demand Function For A Product Is Qd = 30 - 4P, And The Price And Quantity Of Products Is 4 And 14 Respectively. What Is The Price Elasticity Of Demand For The Product?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1.14', '7.1', '14.1', '1.7', '', 'A Explanation Q = 14, P = 4  Qd = 30 - 4p  âˆ†q/âˆ†p = - 4    Ed = Î”qÎ”pÃ—pq  = - 4 x 4/14  = Ed = -1.14 since price elasticity is positive, then Ed = 1.14   ', 0, '2024-02-28 12:57:25'),
(511, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Macroeconomics Focuses On The Following Units In An Aggregative Manner&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â household, firms, government, corporate sector and external sector  ', 'Individual Consumers, Individual Firms, Government And External Sector', 'Government, Household Firms, Individual Consumers And External Sector ', 'Individual Consumers, Household Firms And Manufacturing Sector', '', 'C Explanation Macroeconomics focuses on the following units in of government, household firms, individual consumers and external sector.', 0, '2024-02-28 12:59:23'),
(512, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Would Not Be A Reason For A Government To Impose A Quota On Imports?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'To support strategic industry ', 'Â To Prevent Dumping', 'To Decrease Tax Revenue ', 'Â Employment Oppourtunity', '', 'C Explanation Reasons for the imposition of tariffs or restriction of trade are: To protect infant industries, generation of revenue, to prevent dumping, to improve balance of payment deficit, employment generation, to promote self-sufficiency, political ', 0, '2024-02-28 13:00:59'),
(513, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Economies Of West African Countries Depend Majorly On&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'primary product ', 'Secondary Product ', 'Tertiary Product', 'Manufacturing Product', '', ' A Explanation The economies of West African Countries depend majorly on primary products. Primary products refer to goods that are available from cultivating plants or by extracting minerals from the earth. These include agricultural products, mining pro', 0, '2024-02-28 13:02:10'),
(514, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When A Generalization Is Made Based On Observed Facts, It Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â inductive reasoning ', 'Â Normative Reasoning ', 'Theoretical Reasoning', 'Deductive Reasoning', '', 'A Explanation Inductive reasoning is a process by which a person makes a generalization based on specific, individual experiences. This process begins with observation.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:03:31'),
(515, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Suppose The Public Expenditure As A Percentage Of GDP Of Four Countries Is Shown In The Table Below&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;table Border=&quot;1&quot; Cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; Cellspacing=&quot;1&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;A&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;40%&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;B&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;50%&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;C&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;33%&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;D&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;36%&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Which Type Of Economy Exists In These Countries?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Traditional  ', 'Planned ', 'Pure Market ', 'Mixed', '', 'D Explanation The economy is mixed with the highest GDP. It constitutes private expenditure as a percentage of GDP.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:11:58'),
(516, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/WPzdp0hfDyrRjP8Ou2F35apjvLMNPw4NWn3unxy1.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Diagram Above Represent&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Supply curve ', 'Production Possibility Curve', 'Indifference Curve ', 'Demand Curve', '', 'B Explanation The digram above represent the production possibility curve which is also known as production possibility frontier, production possibility boundary, or transformation curve.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:13:35'),
(517, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;40 Men Were Employed In A Farm, And They Produced An Average Of 30 Tonnes Of Cassava Per Person. Calculate The Total Product.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1,300 tonnes', '1,100 Tonnes', '1,200 Tonnes ', '1,400 Tonnes', '', 'C Explanation The total product can be calculated by multiplying the number of workers by the average product per worker. In this case, 40 men produced an average of 30 tonnes of cassava each. Therefore, the total product is 40 men * 30 tonnes/man = 1,200', 0, '2024-02-28 13:14:53'),
(518, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Economists Refer To Private Goods As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â rivalrous and non-excludable', 'Â Rivalrous And Excludable ', 'Â Non Rival And Non- Excludable ', 'Â Non Rival And Excludable', '', 'B Explanation They are goods that are divisible and to which principle of exclusion is fully applied. It is based on the following assumptions: Ability to pay, Rivalry in consumption, price is its basis, willingness to pay etc.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:16:10'),
(519, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Rate Of Output Per Worker (or Group Of Workers) Per Unit Time Is Called&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â labour productivity ', 'Total Output ', 'Individual Output', 'Workdone', '', 'C Explanation Individual output is also called average product and it is calculated as:  total output total number of labour', 0, '2024-02-28 13:17:23'),
(520, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Quantity Of Commodity A Consumer Is Willing And Able To Buy At A Particular Time Is Called&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â supply', 'Wish', 'Demand ', 'Desire', '', ' C Explanation Demand for a commodity is its quantity which consumers are willing and able to buy at various prices during a given period of time.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:18:49'),
(521, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;If The Supply Curve Of Labour Market Is Given As S = 4L + 8. What Is L When S = 20?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2 ', 'Â 4', '5', '3', '', 'D Explanation The supply curve of labour market is given as S = 4L + 8. To find the value of L when S = 20, we substitute S = 20 in the equation and solve for L. This gives us L = 3.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:19:53'),
(522, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/xKxJAwS7Q4e6E6u7r7zuiWk5vHbCte8qwBn2QsOG.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;From The Graph Above, The Consumer Is At Equilibrium At Point&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â k ', 'Â L', 'M', 'J', '', 'A Explanation The consumer is at equilibrium is at point k where the slope of the indifference curve is tangential to the budget line.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:25:24'),
(523, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Calculate The Equilibrium Level Of National Income (Y) Where Y = C + I + G; C = 100 + 0.75Y; I = 50; G = 200&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 2000', '100', '1500', '1400', '', 'D Explanation y = a+i+G1âˆ’b   where b = 0.75    = 100+50+2001âˆ’075  = 3500.25   = 1400  Alternatively: Y = C + I + G Y = 100 + 0.75Y + 50 + 200 Y - 0.75Y = 350 Y( 1 - 0.75) = 350    = 3500.25  Y = 1400', 0, '2024-02-28 13:27:07'),
(524, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When A Kilogram Of Carrot Is #8.00, 20 Kilograms Are Demanded And When The Price Decreased To #6.000 Per Kilogram, 30 Kilograms Are Demanded. The Elasticity Of Demand Equals To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 11', 'Â 12', ' 12', '2', '', 'D Explanation e = Î”QÎ”PÃ—pq   where âˆ†Q = Q2 - Q1 and âˆ†P = P2 - P1    e = 30âˆ’206âˆ’8Ã—820   = -2 since price elasticity of demand is always positive, then e = 2   ', 0, '2024-02-28 13:29:20'),
(525, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Agriculture Accounts For About 60% Of The&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'commodity market in West Africa', 'Arable Land In West Africa ', 'Â Active Labour Force In West Africa ', 'Service Sector Activities In West Africa', '', 'C Explanation Agriculture accounts for about 60% of the active labour force in West Africa. This is because a large portion of the population in West Africa is engaged in farming and other agricultural activities for their livelihood. The other options ar', 0, '2024-02-28 13:30:54'),
(526, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Shows Why Individual Demand Curve For A Good Usually Slopes Downward From Left To Right?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'More of commodities are offered for sale at a lower than higher prices', 'Marginal Utility Falls As Consumption Increases', 'Â The Higher The Price, The Higher The Quantity Offered For Sale', 'Â Prices Are Usually Falling When Demand Is Low', '', 'A Explanation A normal demand curve slopes downward from left to right indicating at higher price, less quantity will be demanded and vice versa.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:34:16'),
(527, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Multiplier Can Be Described As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'the ratio of change in an endogenous variable to the change spending  ', 'The Ratio Of Variables That Multiplies Autonomous Spending Plus Tax ', 'The Ratio Of Change In Output To A Change In Autonomous Spending ', 'Â The Ratio Of Variables That Multiplies Autonomous Spending', '', 'A Explanation A multiplier is a factor of proportionality that measures how much an endogenous variable changes in response to a change in some exogenous variable such as investment, consumption, government expediture etc.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:36:11'),
(528, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which One Of The Following Measures The Natural Growth Rate Of Population?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Natural increase - Birth rate + Net migration  ', 'Â Birth Rate - Death Rate', 'Birth Rate/Death Rate ', 'Â Birth + Net Migration = Death', '', 'B Explanation The natural growth rate of a population is measured by the difference between the birth rate and the death rate. This is because the birth rate indicates the number of births in a population, while the death rate indicates the number of deat', 0, '2024-02-28 13:37:45'),
(529, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In A Two By Two Model Of International Trade, It Is Assumed That&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â both countries could gain from trade at the same time, but term of trade is inconsequential for the distribution of the gains ', 'Both Countries Could Gain From Trade At The Same Time, But The Volume Of The Gains Depends On Terms Of Trade', 'Neither Country Could Ever Gain From Trade Since Term Of Trade Is Depends On The Distribution Of The Gains From Trade ', 'Both Countries Could Gain From Trade At The Same Time, And The Volume Of The Gains Does Not Depend On Terms Of Trade', '', 'B Explanation The model emphasizes the export of goods requiring factors of production that a country has in abundance. It also emphasizes the import of goods that a nation cannot produce as efficiently. It takes the position that countries should ideally', 0, '2024-02-28 13:43:51'),
(530, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;------------- Is NOT The Cause Of Balance Of Payments (BOP) Deficits In Nigeria&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Poor performance of non-oil sector ', 'Export Promotion ', 'No Import Substitution Strategies', 'High Servicing Of Debt', '', 'A Explanation The causes of balance of payment deficit are: low level of agriculture, low level of technological development, inadequacies in export promotion strategy, political instability, poor social and economic infrastructure, servicing of huge exte', 0, '2024-02-28 13:45:39'),
(531, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Institutions Serving As Links Between Surplus And Deficit Units Can Be Identified As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â tax officers', 'Pension Offices', 'Financial Intermediates ', 'Acceptance Houses', '', 'C Explanation A financial intermediary is typically an institution that facilitates the channeling of funds between lenders and borrowers indirectly.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:46:51'),
(532, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Will Cause An Increase In Cost Of Production?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Hyper-inflation ', 'Cost Push Inflation', 'Structural Inflation', 'Demand Pull Inflation', '', 'B Explanation Cost push inflation occurs when overall prices increase(inflation) due to increases in the cost of wages and raw materials. It can also occur when higher costs of production decrease the aggregate supply in the economy.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:48:02'),
(533, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Number Of People Who Are Qualified To Work And Who Offered Themselves For Employment Are Called&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'mobility of labour ', 'Working Population ', 'Â Migrant Labour', 'Labour Turnover', '', 'B Explanation working population also known as labour force refers to the total number of persons available to supply the labour for the production of economic goods and service. In other words, it is the total number of people of working age in a country', 0, '2024-02-28 13:49:19'),
(534, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/GvMtd3nXGYrfexFUblW6kazpAVPz4rfjG1IFyPzV.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Diagram Above Represent&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â structural unemployment', 'Cyclical Unemployment ', 'Volunatary Unempployment ', 'Frictional Unemployment', '', 'B Explanation The dotted line in the graph above represent the upturn and downturn of the econonmy. Therefore, the diagram is cyclical unemployment.   ', 0, '2024-02-28 13:50:28'),
(535, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Overpopulation Is Caused By&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â emigration ', 'Disease', 'Low Literacy Rates ', 'War And Conflicts', '', 'C Explanation The causes of overpopulation are: falling mortality rate, underutilized contraception, lack of female education etc.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:51:36'),
(536, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Must Be True To Have A Closed Economy With No Government, And Yet The Value Of The Investmet Multiplier Still Increase?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Marginal propensity to save has fallen', 'Actual Investment Had Fallen', 'Average Propensity To Invest Has Fallen', 'Actual Saving Has Fallen', '', 'A Explanation Investment multiplier (K) is a function of two factors; The MPS and MPC. If MPC is high, K will also be high but if MPC is low, K will also be low. on the other hand, If MPS is high, K will be low and if MPS is low, K will be high ( since th', 0, '2024-02-28 13:52:44'),
(537, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Economics Is Often Described As A Science Because It&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'employs the use of laboratory experiments ', 'Use Scientific Methods To Explain Observed Phenomena ', 'Make Use Of Controlled Experiments', 'Engages Accurate Predication Of Human Beings', '', 'B Explanation Economics is regarded as a science because it uses scientific methods to build theories that can help explain behaviour of individuals, groups and organisations.', 0, '2024-02-28 13:53:45'),
(538, 17, 'JAMB', 'ECONOMICS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is NOT One Of The Characteristics Of Developing Countries?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'High unemployment ', 'Â Mono- Product Economy', 'Â High Capital Formation ', 'Â Low Saving', '', 'B Explanation Mono- product economy ( an economy that produces one product or commodity) is not a characteristics of developing country. The characteristics are: high level of illiteracy, dependence on agriculture, low savings and investment, low standard', 0, '2024-02-28 13:56:16'),
(539, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Has The Same Rhyme Scheme As The Following Word:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;battle&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â raffle ', 'Latter ', 'Bitter', 'Kettle', '', 'D Explanation battle - /ËˆbÃ¦t.É™l/  raffle - /&apos;rÃ¦f.É™l/  latter - /&apos;lÃ¦t.É™/  bitter - /ËˆbÉªt.É™/  kettle - /&apos;ket.É™l/  Battle and kettle have the same rhyme scheme because they both end with the syllable /tÉ™l/.', 0, '2024-03-05 08:34:43'),
(540, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Words In Capital Letter Have The Emphatic Stress. Choose The Options To Which The Given Sentences Relate.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI Bought My WIFE A Red Dress&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Did I buy my husband a red dress? ', 'Did I Buy My Wife A Red Shoe? ', 'Did He Buy My Wife A Red Dress?', 'Did I Buy My Wife A Black Dress?', '', 'A Explanation Emphatic stress is the placement of greater stress on a particular word in a phrase or sentence. In this case, the word wife is emphasized to correct a mistake that has been made in the question. To find the appropriate question to the respo', 0, '2024-03-05 08:36:19'),
(541, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nDr. Samuel Johnson Is Also Known As_____&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'SamJson ', 'Samjohn ', 'All Of The Above', 'Johnsam', '', ' B Explanation He is also known as Samjohn. We can find this in pg. 19 of the novel where Ummi&apos;s husband casually refers to Dr Samuel Johnson as Dr. Samjohn, his friend who had helped with Ummi&apos;s admission.', 0, '2024-03-05 08:38:12'),
(542, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Has The Same CONSONANT SOUND As The One Represented By The Letter(s) Underlined.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWa&lt;ins&gt;sh&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'treasure ', 'Occasion ', 'Nation ', 'Â Equation', '', 'C Explanation wash - /Êƒ/  treasure - /Ê’/  occasion - /Ê’/  nation - /Êƒ/  equation - /Ê’/', 0, '2024-03-05 08:40:23'),
(543, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Each Of The Following Sentences, The Word That Resolves The Emphatic Stress Is Written In Capital Letters. From The Options Letters A To D, Choose The One To Which The Given Sentence Is The Appropriate Answer.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nDaddy Plays TENNIS On Saturday Afternoons&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Does mummy play tennis on Saturday afternoons? ', 'Does Daddy Play Tennis On Sunday Afternoons?', 'Does Daddy Play Tennis On Saturday Morning? ', 'Does Daddy Play Cricket On Saturday Afternoon?', '', ' D Explanation Emphatic stress is the placement of greater stress on a particular word in a phrase or sentence. In this case, the word wife is emphasized to correct a mistake that has been made in the question. To find the appropriate question to the resp', 0, '2024-03-05 08:42:58'),
(544, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Select The Option That Best Explains The Information Conveyed In The Sentence.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Though He Is Our Elected Representative, He Often Takes A Rather Jaundiced View Of Our Problems.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'He takes a rather hazy view of our problems ', 'He Takes An Unfavourable Position Concerning Our Problems', 'He Takes A Rather Forceful View Of Our Problems', 'He Takes A Sickly View Of Our Problems', '', 'B Explanation The phrase &apos;jaundiced view&apos; is an idiomatic expression that means having a cynical or sceptical view of something. It does not mean hazy, forceful or sickly. Therefore, the option that best explains the information conveyed in the ', 0, '2024-03-05 08:47:41'),
(545, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Is Opposite In Meaning To The Underlined Word(s)&lt;br /&gt;\r\nVictor Played The Role Of A&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;haughty&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;prince.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'a haunted ', 'A Modest', 'A Disturbed ', 'An Angry', '', 'B Explanation Haughty means arrogantly superior and disdainful. Its antonyms include modest, humble, unpretentious, unassuming, low-key and unostentatious.', 0, '2024-03-05 08:55:34'),
(546, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Fill In The Gap In The Sentence&amp;nbsp;below With The Appropriate Option:&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPeter And Jane Love Each Other ...... The Difficulties They Face.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'therefore ', 'Despite ', 'However ', 'Besides', '', 'B Explanation &quot;despite&quot; is used to join two contrasting situations in a sentence. e.g He was rich despite the difficulties he went through.', 0, '2024-03-05 08:59:28'),
(547, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI Was&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;skeptical&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;about The Story She Told Me.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'doubtful ', 'Convinced', 'Ignorant ', 'Confused', '', 'A Explanation The word &apos;skeptical&apos; means not easily convinced; or having doubts or reservations. Therefore, the nearest meaning to &apos;skeptical&apos; among the options is &apos;doubtful&apos;.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:00:53'),
(548, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\n_________ Is The Euphemism Use For Cheat Notes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Salvation note of rescue ', 'Note Of Deliverance', 'Holy Note Of Rescue', 'Notes Of Salvation', '', 'D Explanation In the context of the novel &apos;The Life Changer&apos;, the euphemism used for cheat notes is &apos;Notes of salvation&apos;.This can be found on page 52 of the novel where Salma convinced her seat partner, Kola, during her final examinati', 0, '2024-03-05 09:04:53'),
(549, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhy Did Omar Say He Passed His SSCE By No Means A Small Feat?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'all of the above ', 'Because He Failed Other Subjects But Passed Maths And English Â ', 'Because He Registered With One Of The Miracle Centers ', 'Because He Passed Excellently On His First Attempt', '', ' D Explanation In the novel &apos;The Life Changer&apos;, Omar says he passed his SSCE by no means a small feat because he passed excellently on his first attempt. This can be found on page 8 of the novel. He was bragging to his sister, Teemah, about how ', 0, '2024-03-05 09:08:36'),
(550, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Has The Same Vowel Sound As The One Represented By The Letter[s] Underlined.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;nak&lt;ins&gt;e&lt;/ins&gt;d&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'friend ', 'Bead ', 'Fed ', 'Bid', '', 'D Explanation The correct answer is bid.  The &apos;e&apos; in the word &apos;naked&apos; is pronounced as  /Éª/ - /ËˆneÉªkÉªd/. Therefore the word with the same vowel sound is &apos;bid&apos;.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:09:59'),
(551, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The List Of Words In A To D, Choose One That Best Describes The Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nJames And Henry Were At Daggers Drawn When I Knew Them. This Means That They&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'were always angry with each other Â ', 'Always Wore Daggers ', 'Were Good At Drawing Daggers', 'Were Fighting Everybody', '', ' A Explanation The phrase &apos;at daggers drawn&apos; is an idiom which means to be bitterly hostile or at enmity with someone. It does not literally mean that they always wore daggers or were good at drawing daggers or were fighting everybody. Therefore', 0, '2024-03-05 09:11:33'),
(552, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWho Among Salma&amp;#39;s Roommate Was Reserved And Withdrawn Yet Generous To A Fault?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ngozi ', 'Tomiwa', 'Ada ', 'None Of Them', '', 'A Explanation In the novel &apos;The Life Changer&apos;, Ngozi is described as being reserved and withdrawn yet generous to a fault. It is her generosity that leads to a strong bond between the roommates. She always shares her food with the rest and this ', 0, '2024-03-05 09:12:44'),
(553, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Has The Same Rhyme Scheme As The Word Below:&lt;br /&gt;\r\nDay&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Dare ', 'Anime ', 'Flight', 'Ball', '', 'B Explanation Rhyme scheme refers to the pattern of end sounds or words in a verse or line of poetry. In this case, we are looking for a word that rhymes with &apos;Day&apos; /deÉª/  dare -  /deÉ™/  anime  - /ËˆÃ¦nÉªmeÉª/  flight - /flaÉªt/  ball - /bÉ”Ë', 0, '2024-03-05 09:14:07'),
(554, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Fill Each Gap With The Most Appropriate Option From The List Provided.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Without Our Relentless Campaigns, We Might ...... Sure Of Victory In The Race For The National Assembly.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'be never ', 'Never Have Been ', 'Never Had Been ', 'Have Never Be', '', 'B Explanation never have been is most appropriate. Because of the use of the modal &quot;might,&quot; the form of anomalous HAVE to use is have. Then, after &quot;have&quot; comes the past participle &quot;been&quot;.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:15:54'),
(555, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Fill Each Gap With The Most Appropriate Option From The List Provided.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;We Are All Hungry; We ...... Anything To Eat Since Morning.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'hadn&apos;t had ', 'Never Had ', 'Haven&apos;t Had ', 'Didn&apos;t Have', '', 'C Explanation haven&apos;t had is most appropriate. This is known as the present perfect tense which is used to show that an action has been completed (or not) as of the time of speaking.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:17:13'),
(556, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Fill Each Gap With The Most Appropriate Option From The List Provided.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;To Check Desertification In The Arid Zones, ...... Trees Should Be Planted&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'drought-resisting', 'Drought-Resistant', 'Drought-Effective ', 'Drought-Proof', '', 'B Explanation drought-resistant is most appropriate. Drought tolerance refers to the degree to which a plant is adapted to arid or drought conditions.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:19:23'),
(557, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Options Lettered A-D, Choose The Option That Is Most Nearly Opposite In Meaning To The Underlined Word.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMy Father Is&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;parsimonious&lt;/ins&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'thrifty ', 'Frugal', 'Generous ', 'Ungenerous', '', ' C Explanation Parsimonious means to be very unwilling to spend money or use resources. The nearly opposite word is generous.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:20:42'),
(558, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Pick Out The Option With A Different Rhyme&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Roar', 'Four', 'Growl', 'Bore', '', 'C Explanation The word &apos;Growl&apos; has a different rhyme from the other words. Rhyming words are words that have the same ending sound. In this case, &apos;Bore&apos;, &apos;Four&apos;, and &apos;Roar&apos; all end with the &apos;-ore&apos; sound, w', 0, '2024-03-05 09:22:00'),
(559, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Primary Stress Is Indicated By Writing The Syllable On Which It Occurs In Capital Letters. From The Words Lettered A To D Choose The One That Has The Correct Stress.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nCategory&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'cat-e-GO-ry ', 'CAT-E-Go-Ry', 'Cat-E-Go-RY', 'Cat-E-Go-Ry', '', 'B Explanation In English pronunciation, the word &apos;category&apos; has the primary stress on the first syllable. Therefore, the correct option is &apos;CAT-e-go-ry&apos;.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:23:32'),
(560, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nUmmi Is An Arabic Word That Is Directly Translated To Mean_____&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'My mom', 'My Mother', 'Grandmother', 'Godmother', '', 'B Explanation In Arabic, &apos;Ummi&apos; is directly translated to mean &apos;My mother&apos;. This can be seen on page 3 of the novel. According to Ummi, she was named after her paternal grandmother.', 0, '2024-03-05 09:25:10'),
(561, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Words Lettered A To D Below, Choose The Word Or Group Of Words That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word As It Is Used In The Passage.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nBisi Has Become An&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;indispensable&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;member Of Staff.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'vital ', 'Principal ', 'Dedicated ', 'Effective', '', 'A Explanation The word &apos;indispensable&apos; means something or someone that is absolutely necessary or extremely important in a particular situation. In this context, it means that Bisi is a very important member of the staff. Therefore, the word &ap', 0, '2024-03-07 09:40:44'),
(562, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Has The Same Vowel Sound As The Letter(s) Underlined&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;ins&gt;e&lt;/ins&gt;xist&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'never', 'Isle ', 'Meant ', 'Helicopter', '', 'D Explanation exist - /ÉªgzÉªst/ helicopter - /helÉªkÉ’ptÉ™/ isle - /aÉªl/ meant - /ment/ never - /nevÉ™/', 0, '2024-03-07 09:42:19'),
(563, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIn Lafayette, Before A Stranger Is Hosted Or Accommodated, Permission Must Be Requested And Granted By_______&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â the Hakimi ', 'The High Priest ', 'The Governor', 'Community Oracle', '', 'A Explanation In the novel &apos;The Life Changer&apos;, in Lafayette, before a stranger is hosted or accommodated, permission must be requested and granted by the Hakimi. The Hakimi is a traditional title for a local or tribal leader in some areas of the', 0, '2024-03-07 09:44:11'),
(564, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Does Not Have The Same Vowel Sound As The Others&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'shun ', 'Son', 'Sun', 'Short', '', 'D Explanation The words &apos;sun&apos;, &apos;shun&apos;, and &apos;son&apos; have the same vowel sound /ÊŒ/, while &apos;short&apos; has a different vowel sound /É”:/. Therefore, &apos;short&apos; does not have the same vowel sound as the others.', 0, '2024-03-07 09:46:03'),
(565, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Use The Passage To Answer The Questions Below&lt;br /&gt;\r\nRead The Passage Carefully And Answer The Questions That Follow:&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Victory Of The Small Greek Democracy Of Athens Over The Mighty Persian Empire Was Furious Because Athens Had Interceded For The Other Greek City-states In Revolt Against Persian Domination. In Anger, The King Sent An Enormous Army To Defeat Athens. He Thought It Would Take Drastic Steps To Pacify The Rebellious Part Of The Empire.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPersia Was Ruled By One Man. In Athens, However, All Citiens Helped To Rule. Emboldened&amp;nbsp;by This Participation, Athenians Were Prepared To Die For Their City-state. Perhaps This Was The Secret Of The Remarkable Victory At The Marathon, The Persians Tried To Fool Some Greek City-states By Claiming To Have Come In Peace. The Frightened City Of Delos Refused To Believe This. Not Wanting To Abet The Conquest Of Greece, They Fled From Their City And Did Not Return Until The Persians Had Left. They Were Wise, For The President Next Conquered The City Of Eritrea And Captured Its People.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nTiny&amp;nbsp;Athens Stood Alone Against Persia. The Athenian People To Their Sanctuaries. There They Prayed For Deliverance. They Asked Their Gods To Expedite Their Victory. The Athenians Refurbished Their Weapons And Moved To The Plan Of Marathon Where Their Little Band Would Meet The Persians. At The Last Moment, Soldiers From Plataea Reinforced The Athenian Troops.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Athenian Army Attacked And Greek Citizens Fought Bravely. The Power Of The Mighty Persians Was Offset By The Love That The Athenians Had For Their City. Athenians Defeated The Persians In Both Archery And Combat. Greek Soldiers Seized Persian Sheep&amp;nbsp;and Burned Them And The Persians Fled In Terror. Herodotus, A Famous Historian, Reports That 6400 Persians Died, Compared To Only 192 Athenians.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Athens Had _________ The Greek-states Against Persians.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'refused to help ', 'Wanted To Fight', 'Intervened On Behalf ', 'Given Orders To Fight', '', 'C Explanation From the passage, it is clear that Athens had interceded for the other Greek city-states against the Persian domination. This means that Athens had intervened on behalf of the other Greek city-states. Therefore, the correct answer is option ', 0, '2024-03-07 09:47:52'),
(566, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Use The Passage To Answer The Questions Below&lt;br /&gt;\r\nRead The Passage Carefully And Answer The Questions That Follow:&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Victory Of The Small Greek Democracy Of Athens Over The Mighty Persian Empire Was Furious Because Athens Had Interceded For The Other Greek City-states In Revolt Against Persian Domination. In Anger, The King Sent An Enormous Army To Defeat Athens. He Thought It Would Take Drastic Steps To Pacify The Rebellious Part Of The Empire.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPersia Was Ruled By One Man. In Athens, However, All Citiens Helped To Rule. Emboldened&amp;nbsp;by This Participation, Athenians Were Prepared To Die For Their City-state. Perhaps This Was The Secret Of The Remarkable Victory At The Marathon, The Persians Tried To Fool Some Greek City-states By Claiming To Have Come In Peace. The Frightened City Of Delos Refused To Believe This. Not Wanting To Abet The Conquest Of Greece, They Fled From Their City And Did Not Return Until The Persians Had Left. They Were Wise, For The President Next Conquered The City Of Eritrea And Captured Its People.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nTiny&amp;nbsp;Athens Stood Alone Against Persia. The Athenian People To Their Sanctuaries. There They Prayed For Deliverance. They Asked Their Gods To Expedite Their Victory. The Athenians Refurbished Their Weapons And Moved To The Plan Of Marathon Where Their Little Band Would Meet The Persians. At The Last Moment, Soldiers From Plataea Reinforced The Athenian Troops.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Athenian Army Attacked And Greek Citizens Fought Bravely. The Power Of The Mighty Persians Was Offset By The Love That The Athenians Had For Their City. Athenians Defeated The Persians In Both Archery And Combat. Greek Soldiers Seized Persian Sheep&amp;nbsp;and Burned Them And The Persians Fled In Terror. Herodotus, A Famous Historian, Reports That 6400 Persians Died, Compared To Only 192 Athenians.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Darius Took Drastic Steps To __________ The Rebellious Athenians.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â irritate ', 'Weaken', 'Destroy ', 'Calm', '', 'D Explanation In the passage, it is mentioned that &apos;In anger the king sent an enormous army to defeat Athens. He thought it would take drastic steps to pacify the rebellious part of the empire.&apos; This implies that Darius, the king, took drastic s', 0, '2024-03-07 09:49:31'),
