(580, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Passage Below Has Gaps. Immediately Following Each Gap, Four Options Are Provided. Choose The Most Appropriate Option For Each Gap.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPASSAGE IV&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWith The Most Profound Respect To The Members Of The Senate, I Do Not Think That It Is Within The Competence Of That ...1... Body To Pass A Motion To ...2... The Executive Action Of The President. The Senate Is ...3... Of The National Assembly. But It Is Not By Itself Alone The National Assembly. One Can Imagine The Confusion, Which Would Be Created If The ...4... Were To Take A View Diametrically Opposed To That Reflected In The Senate Resolution. The Strongest Objection To The Action Of The Senate In Passing The Resolution Is The Fact That It Constituted Itself The ...5... As Well As The Judge Of The Constitutionality Of The Action Of The President. The Function Of The Senate Is To ...6... Laws. But The Senate Has No Authority Or ...7... To Control The President In The Exercise Of His ...8... Powers. It Cannot By A Mere Resolution Or Motion Give Any Directive To The President Regarding The Exercise Of His Powers Nor Can It Undo What The President Has Done In The Exercise Of Those Powers. The Only Way In Which The Exercise Of The Powers Of The President Can Be ...9... Is By ...10... Of The National Assembly.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAdapted From The Guardian Of July 8, 1999, P. 8.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;...9...&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â modified', 'Regulated ', 'Standardized', 'Ordered', '', 'B Explanation In the context of the passage, the exercise of the powers of the President can be &apos;regulated&apos;. This means that the actions of the President can be controlled or governed according to a system or set of rules, which is the role of t', 0, '2024-03-07 10:41:27'),
(581, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;rom The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAccording To The Novel, Which Of These Characters Had A Nasty Experience On The Account Of Using Social Media?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Tomiwa ', 'Salma', 'Salim', 'Ummi', '', 'C Explanation Salim had a nasty experience using social media.', 0, '2024-03-07 11:40:46'),
(582, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word(s)&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;ins&gt;Repugnant&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;rules In The Society Should Be Repealed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Enacted ', 'Exemplary', 'Abhorrent', 'Justified', '', 'C Explanation Repugnant means extremely distasteful. Its synonyms include abhorrent, revolting, repulsive, repellent and offensive.', 0, '2024-03-07 11:42:20'),
(583, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Options To Which The Given Sentence Relate.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSpain Won Their Last Friendly FOOTBALL Match&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Who won their last friendly football match? ', 'Did Spain Win Their Last Competitive Football Match', 'Did Spain Lose Their Last Competitive Football Match ', 'Did Spain Win Their Last Friendly Basketball Match?', '', ' D Explanation Emphatic stress usually emphasis contrast, thus the right option should contain a word that contrasts with the emphasized word.', 0, '2024-03-07 11:54:53'),
(584, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Boss Is Quite&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;inflexible&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;once He Has Made Up His Mind.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'wicked ', 'Â Relaxed', 'Excited', 'Unyielding', '', 'D Explanation The word &apos;inflexible&apos; means unwilling to change or compromise. Therefore, the nearest meaning to &apos;inflexible&apos; among the options is &apos;unyielding&apos;.', 0, '2024-03-07 11:56:07'),
(585, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Following Question, Choose The Option That Best Completes The Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Guest Would Have Arrived Earlier But He Was _______ In Traffic.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'held down ', 'Held Up', 'Held About ', 'Â Held Off', '', 'B Explanation The correct phrase to use is &apos;held up&apos;. &apos;Held up&apos; is a phrasal verb that means to be delayed or obstructed. So, &apos;The guest would have arrived earlier but he was held up in traffic&apos; is the correct sentence.', 0, '2024-03-07 11:59:44'),
(586, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word(s)&lt;br /&gt;\r\nNo One Would Complain If You&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;emulate&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;good Behaviour&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'differentiate ', 'Condemn ', 'Imitate ', 'Exhibit', '', 'C Explanation Emulate means to match or surpass, typically by imitation. Its synonyms include imitate, copy, reproduce, mimic, mirror, echo and follow.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:01:28'),
(587, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;He Was Both A Writer And A Politician, But He Was Better ........ A Singer&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'like ', 'To Be', 'As If ', 'As', '', 'D Explanation The correct preposition to use after &apos;better&apos; in this context is &apos;as&apos;. When comparing roles or functions, &apos;as&apos; is used. For example, &apos;He works better as a manager than as a clerk.&apos; Therefore, the sente', 0, '2024-03-07 12:03:00'),
(588, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Has The Same Consonant Sound As The One In Bracket.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Smoo[th]&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'worth ', 'Dress', 'Brother ', 'Wealthy', '', 'C Explanation Brother is the correct answer. The sound present here is pronounceable from the &apos;TH&apos; in &apos;these&apos; /Ã°/ (not /d/ as in &apos;drug&apos; or /Î¸/ as in &apos;thanks&apos;).', 0, '2024-03-07 12:04:26'),
(589, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Identify The Option With A Different Stress Pattern&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'reservoir ', 'Contribute ', 'Importance', 'Deposit', '', 'A Explanation In this case, &apos;importance&apos;, &apos;contribute&apos;, and &apos;deposit&apos; all have the stress on the first syllable. However, &apos;reservoir&apos; has a different stress pattern with the stress on the third syllable, making it t', 0, '2024-03-07 12:06:03'),
(590, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Each Of The Questions, The Word In Capital Letters Has The Emphatic Stress. Choose The Option To Which The Given Sentence Relates.The Union Congratulated The ELECTED President.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Did the union reject the elected president? ', 'Did The Union Congratulate The Elected Chairman? ', 'Did The Management Congratulate The Elected President?', 'Did The Union Congratulate The Ousted President?', '', 'D Explanation The correct answer is - Did the union congratulate the ousted president? The option without the emphatic word - ELECTED is the correct answer.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:07:43'),
(591, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhat Appellation Was Given To Talle For All His Amazing Show Of Personality.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The cool and calm one ', 'The Moody Ones ', 'The Simple And Delicate One ', 'The Quiet One', '', 'D Explanation He was known as the quiet one.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:08:59'),
(592, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Each Of The Questions, The Word In Capital Letters Has The Emphatic Stress. Choose The Option To Which The Given Sentence Relates.A Good Description INCLUDES Specific Nouns.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Does a good description exclude specific nouns? ', 'Does A Good Description Include Specific Verbs?', 'Â Does A Good Description Include Obscure Nouns? ', 'Does A Poor Description Include Specific Nouns?', '', ' A Explanation The correct answer is - Does a good description exclude specific nouns?. The option without the emphatic word - INCLUDES is the correct answer.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:10:35'),
(593, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhose Reticent Nature While Growing Up Earned Him The Title: &amp;quot;The Quiet One&amp;quot;.?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Talle ', 'Bint', 'Omar', 'Ummi', '', 'A Explanation Talle was regarded as the quiet one while growing', 0, '2024-03-07 12:13:51'),
(594, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Select The Option That Best Explains The Information Conveyed In The Sentence.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Solution Lies In Choosing Between Various Negative Alternatives.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The solutions are many ', 'The Solution Lies In Choosing Between The Positive And Negative ', 'The Solution Can Be Found In One Of The Negative Options ', 'The Solution Is A Negative One', '', 'C Explanation The sentence &apos;The solution lies in choosing between various negative alternatives&apos; implies that the solution can be found among several unfavorable or less-than-ideal options. Therefore, the option &apos;The solution can be found i', 0, '2024-03-07 12:15:26'),
(595, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, The Word In Capital Letters Has The Emphatic Stress. Choose The Option To Which The Given Sentence Relates.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;EMEKA Finished His Homework Yesterday.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Who finished his home work yesterday? ', 'When Did Emeka Finish His Home Work? ', 'Did Emeka Do His Home Work Yesterday?', 'Was Emeka Helped To Do His Home Work?', '', 'A Explanation In the sentence, the word &apos;Emeka&apos; is stressed. This means the emphasis is on &apos;who&apos; did the action. Therefore, the question that relates to the sentence is &apos;Who finished his home work yesterday?&apos;.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:17:12'),
(596, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word(s)&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAfter Thousands Of Years Of Existing, Elephants Still Remain&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;extant&lt;/ins&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'subdued ', 'Pulverized ', 'Strong', 'Enduring', '', 'D Explanation Extant means still in existence. It&apos;s synonyms include still existing, in existence, surviving, abiding, enduring and existent.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:18:37'),
(597, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSalma Stayed At The Most Coveted And Famous ______ Hostel.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Queen Amina ', 'Queen Moremi ', 'Queen Lateefat ', 'Queen Haneefat', '', 'A Explanation Salma stayed in Queen Amina&apos;s hostel', 0, '2024-03-07 12:20:27'),
(598, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWho Called The Attention Of The District Head When It Was Discovered That Talle Buys More Than He Could Consume From The Supermarket?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'his friends ', 'The Grocers ', 'His Neighbors', 'His Colleagues', '', 'B Explanation Self-explanatory', 0, '2024-03-07 12:22:46'),
(599, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Identify The Word That Has The Stress On The First Syllable.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'confirm ', 'Intact', 'Resist', 'Salon', '', 'D Explanation reSIST SALon conFIRM inTACT', 0, '2024-03-07 12:24:17'),
(600, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Each Of The Following Sentences, The Word That Receives The Emphatic Stress Is Written In Capital Letters . From The Options Lettered A To D, Choose The One Which The Sentence Is The Appropriate Answer.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nLambusa TOOK OFF The Wig.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'what did Lambusa do? ', 'Who Took Off The Wig? ', 'Did Lambusa Take Off A Wig? ', 'Did Lambusa Take Off A Ring?', '', 'A Explanation When answering emphatic stress questions, the option that does not have the &quot;stressed word&quot; becomes the correct answer.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:25:52'),
(601, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option Opposite In Meaning To The Underlined Word In Each Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nDuring The Maths Test, Some Students Got An&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;approximate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/ins&gt;score Of 20.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'a frank', 'A Measured ', 'A Precise', 'An Inaccurate', '', 'C Explanation The word &apos;approximate&apos; means something that is close to the actual, but not completely accurate or exact. Therefore, the opposite of &apos;approximate&apos; is &apos;precise&apos;, which means marked by exactness and accuracy of de', 0, '2024-03-07 12:27:29'),
(602, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Has The Same Rhyme Scheme.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;sweet&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'twice ', 'Sweat ', 'Suite', 'Suit', '', 'C Explanation The correct answer is - suite. It has the same rhyming pattern with the word - suite. Also, they are homophones.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:32:26'),
(603, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Primary Stress Is Indicated By Writing The Syllable On Which It Occurs In Capital Letters. From The Words Lettered A To D Choose The One That Has The Correct Stress.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPresidency&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'pre-SI-den-cy ', 'Pre-Si-Den-CY', 'Pre-Si-DEN-Cy', 'PRE-Si-Den-Cy', '', 'D Explanation The correct stress for the word &apos;presidency&apos; is &apos;PRE-si-den-cy&apos;. In English, stress means pronouncing one syllable of a multisyllabic word with greater emphasis (stress) than the other syllables in the word. The primary s', 0, '2024-03-07 12:34:58'),
(604, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nHow Old Is Bint?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '5years old ', '10years Old', '8years Old ', '7years Old', '', 'A Explanation Bint is five years of age', 0, '2024-03-07 12:37:25'),
(605, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option Opposite In Meaning To The Underlined Word In Each Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;abeyance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/ins&gt;of School Activities Last Semester Was A Reason For Concern.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'continuance ', 'Collapse', 'Reduction ', 'Intensity', '', 'A Explanation &apos;Abeyance&apos; means a state of temporary disuse or suspension. Its antonyms include resume, continue, recommence and reopen.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:38:57'),
(606, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/english-language?exam_type=jamb&amp;amp;exam_year=2023&quot;&gt;English Language&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/english-language?exam_type=jamb&amp;amp;exam_year=2023&quot;&gt;JAMB 2023&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;From The Words Lettered A To D Below, Choose The Word Or Group Of Words That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word As It Is Used In The Passage.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMr. Brown Is Often Described As An&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;astute&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;businessman&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'shrewd  ', 'Miserly', 'Proud', 'Thrifty', '', 'A Explanation An astute person is someone who is clever and quick at seeing what to do in a particular situation. Such person can also be described as shrewd.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:40:27'),
(607, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Read The Passage Carefully And Answer This Question.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMay Your Road Be Rough. I Am Not Cursing You: I Am Wishing You What I Wish Myself Every Year, I Therefore Repeat, May You Have A Hard Time This Year. May There Be Troubles For You This Year. If You Are Not Sure Of What To Say Back, Why Not Just Say &amp;quot;same To You&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; I Ask For No More.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nOur Successes Are Conditioned By The Amount Of Risk We Are About To Take. Earlier Today, I Visited A Local Farmer About Five Kilometers From Where I Live. He Could Not Have Been 55, But He Said He Was Already Too Old To Farm Vigorously. He Still Suffered, He Said, From The Energy He Displayed As A Farmer In His Younger Days. Around His Hut Were Two Pepperbushes. There Were Cocoyam Growing Around Him. There Were Snail Shells Which Had Given Him Meat. There Must Have Been More Snails Around The Banana Trees Than I Saw. He Hardly Ever Went To Town To Buy Things. He Was Self-sufficient. The Car, The Television Or Radio And The Newspaper Were Things He Could Live Without. He Had No Ambition Whatsoever, He Told Me.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI Am Not Sure If You Are Already Envious Of Him, But Were We All To Revert To Such A Life, We Would Be Driven Back Like Aimless Sheep To Cave Dwelling. On The Other Hand, Try To Put Yourself In The Shoes Of The Russian Or American Astronauts. Any Moment You Are Shot Into Space, You Have To Be Mentally Alert, Else, If You Forget What To Do, One Of The Things That Might Happen To You Is That You Could Forever Become A Satellite Going Round Until You Die Of Starvation, And Even Then, Your Dead Body Would Continue The Gyration.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nNaturally, They May Have Some Slight Foreboding On The Contingency Of Their Non-return. However, It Is Their Courage For Going In Spite Of These Apprehensions That Makes The World Hail Them So Loudly Today.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n(Akinyemi, A., Olupe, F., &amp;amp; Adetutu, S. (2012): Rubrics Of English Language For Schools And Colleges. Divine Glory Printers, Abeokuta.)&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;According To The Passage, Astronauts&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'are always successful ', 'Always Do What Is Expected Of Them ', 'Know They May Not Return From Their Journey Into Space', 'Â Have Courage And Mental Stability', '', 'C Explanation The passage mentions that astronauts may have some slight foreboding on the contingency of their non-return. This implies that they are aware of the risks involved in their journey, including the possibility that they may not return from spa', 0, '2024-03-07 12:42:01'),
