(611, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word With The Same Vowel Sound As The One In Bracket.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Band[a]ge&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'cacophony ', 'Says', 'Cage', 'Kite', '', 'A Explanation The vowel /i/ as in bit is present here. Only the very last sound pronunciation of &apos;cacophony&apos; bears the same answer.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:52:46'),
(612, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Options Lettered A-D, Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI Have An&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;aversion&amp;nbsp;&lt;/ins&gt;for War Movies.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'dislike ', 'Addiction', 'Preference', 'Bitterness', '', 'A Explanation The word &apos;aversion&apos; refers to a strong dislike or disinclination. Therefore, the option that is nearest in meaning to &apos;aversion&apos; is &apos;dislike&apos;.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:54:08'),
(613, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word(s)&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhen Night Fell, We Had To&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;hasten&amp;nbsp;&lt;/ins&gt;to The Motor Park.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'disperse ', 'Averse', 'Hurry', 'Return', '', 'C Explanation Hasten means to move or travel hurriedly. Its synonyms include hurry, hurtle, haste, dash, race and bolt.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:55:28'),
(614, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Has The Same Rhyme Scheme.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nLaugh&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â life ', 'Half ', 'Ghost', 'Â Light', '', 'B Explanation The word &apos;laugh&apos; rhymes with &apos;half&apos;. Rhyme scheme refers to the pattern of sounds that repeats at the end of a line or verse.', 0, '2024-03-07 12:56:57'),
