(616, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Fill In The Gap With The Appropriate Option:&lt;br /&gt;\r\nChildren Are Not Allowed In The Park ...... Dark.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'at ', 'Over', 'Â After ', 'In', '', 'C Explanation The phrase &quot;after dark&quot; is an idiomatic expression that means after nightfall or when it becomes dark. In this context, the sentence states that children are not permitted to be in the park during the nighttime. ', 0, '2024-03-07 12:59:41');
