(625, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Choose The Option Opposite In Meaning To The Underlined Word Or Phrase.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Choose The Option Opposite In Meaning To The Underlined Word Or Phrase.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;It Is&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;inconceivable&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;that The Cat Devoured The Cat.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'unimaginable ', 'Contestable', 'Incomprehensible', 'Credible', '', 'D Explanation The correct answer is - credible. The word inconceivable means, that which cannot be believed;credible.', 0, '2024-03-07 13:25:08'),
(626, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Has The Same Stress Pattern As The Given Word.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nStudent&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Propose  ', 'Superb', 'Refuse(N) ', 'Rebel(V)', '', 'C Explanation Refuse(N) and student are both stressed on the first syllable unlike other options stressed on the second syllable.', 0, '2024-03-07 13:26:17'),
(627, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhat Were Ummi&amp;#39;s Children Waiting For When Bint Narrates Her Encounter With Mr. Salihu?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Their father ', 'Lesson Teacher', 'Dinner', 'Arabic Teacher', '', 'A Explanation Self-explanatory', 0, '2024-03-07 13:27:52'),
(628, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhere Did The Police Apprehend Talle?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'at the village stream', 'At His Residence ', 'At The Palace Of Hakimi', 'At The Village Square', '', 'C Explanation He was arrested when he ran into Hakimi&apos;s house.', 0, '2024-03-07 13:33:06'),
(629, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\n_____ Was Always On The First Row During Prayer At His Office.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ahmed ', 'Zaki ', 'Habeeb', 'Talle', '', 'D Explanation Self-explanatory', 0, '2024-03-07 13:35:32'),
(630, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The List Of Words Letter A To D, Choose The One That Is Most Nearly Opposite In Meaning To The Underlined Word And That Will, At The Same Time, Correctly Fill The Gap In The Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nEating Fresh Fruits And Vegetables Is&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;beneficial&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;to One&amp;#39;s Health While Eating Processed Foods Is ......&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'worrying ', 'Painful ', 'Tasteless', 'Harmful', '', 'D Explanation Something beneficial is helpful or good to something or someone. The antonyms are detrimental, harmful and unfavourable.', 0, '2024-03-07 13:36:41'),
(631, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Select The Option That Best Explains The Information Conveyed In The Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Stadium Had A Capacity Crowd In Spite Of The Weather.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The stadium was not filled because of the weather', 'The Crowd Defied The Weather To Fill The Stadium', 'The Crowd Loved The Weather At The Stadium ', 'The Weather Favoured The Crowd At The Stadium', '', 'B Explanation The sentence implies that despite the weather conditions, the stadium was filled to capacity. This suggests that the crowd defied the weather to fill the stadium. Therefore, the option &apos;The crowd defied the weather to fill the stadium&a', 0, '2024-03-07 13:37:41'),
(632, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Select The Option That Best Explains The Information Conveyed In The Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Conference Is Biennial.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The conference lasts for two years', 'The Conference Is Held Once Every Other Year ', 'The Conference Is Held Twice Every Year', 'The Conference Is Held Twice In Two Years', '', 'B Explanation Occurring once every two years.', 0, '2024-03-07 13:38:43'),
(633, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Select The Option That Best Explains The Information Conveyed In The Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nOnly Two Ministers Survived The Recent Cabinet Reshuffle.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'In recent changes in government, all but two ministers retained their postsÂ ', 'In The Recent Changes In Government, All But Two Ministers Remained Alive', 'In Recent Changes In Government, All But Two Ministers Were Sacked ', 'In The Recent Changes In Government, Only Two Ministers Were Sacked', '', 'C Explanation This is the best interpretation', 0, '2024-03-12 11:05:09'),
(634, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In This Question, Choose The Option That Best Completes The Gap(s).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Proprietor Of Our School With His Administrator ------------ Expected Yesterday.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'are ', 'Is ', 'Was', 'Were', '', 'C Explanation The correct answer is - was. &quot;with&quot; in the sentence above only introduces the &quot;attachment&quot; of false subjects. Other words that introduce false subjects are: as well as, in conjunction with, alongside, together with etc. W', 0, '2024-03-12 11:06:30'),
(635, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Is Nearest In Meaning To The Underlined Word(s)&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIn Nigeria, It Is A Crime To&amp;nbsp;&lt;ins&gt;plagiarize&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;nbsp;someone Else&amp;#39;s Work.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'initiate ', 'Pirate', 'Compose', 'Desecrate', '', 'B Explanation &apos;Plagiarize&apos; means to use and pass off as one&apos;s own. Someone else&apos;s writing or speech. Its synonyms include pirate, steal and copy.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:07:53'),
(636, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;He Started His Career As An ........ Teacher&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'auxillary ', 'Auxilliary', 'Auxilary', 'Auxiliary', '', 'D Explanation Auxiliary being an adjective to the noun &quot;teacher&quot; indicates providing supplementary or extra help, support or assistance.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:09:10'),
(637, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Interpretation That You Consider Most Appropriate For Each Sentence.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhat I Told You Is The Gospel Truth. This Means That The Information Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'unconfirmed ', 'Partly True', 'False', 'Completely True', '', 'D Explanation The phrase &apos;gospel truth&apos; is an idiomatic expression that means &apos;absolute truth&apos;. Therefore, the information is completely true.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:11:00'),
(638, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Option That Has The Same Vowel Sound As The One Represented By The Letter(s) Underlined&lt;br /&gt;\r\nC&lt;ins&gt;a&lt;/ins&gt;sualty&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'sure ', 'Amateur ', 'Juice', 'Aesthetic', '', 'B Explanation casualty - /kÃ¦Ê’juÉ™lti/ juice - /dÊ’uËs/ sure - /ÊƒÊŠÉ™/ amateur - /Ã¦mÉ™tÉ™/ aesthetic - /iËsÎ¸etÉªk/', 0, '2024-03-12 11:12:20'),
(639, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Choose The Word That Has The Same CONSONANT SOUND As The One Represented By The Letter(s) Underlined.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMar&lt;ins&gt;ks&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'exhaust ', 'Axe', 'Mosque', 'Exist', '', 'B Explanation The underlined sound is /ks/ which can only be found in axe: /Ã¦ks/.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:13:48'),
(640, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Words Lettered A To D, Choose The Word That Rhymes With The Given Word Below.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPitch&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Witch ', 'Lease', 'Bleach', 'Bite', '', 'A Explanation The word &apos;Witch&apos; rhymes with &apos;Pitch&apos;. In English, words are said to rhyme when the stressed vowel sounds in their final syllables are the same. Here, &apos;Pitch&apos; and &apos;Witch&apos; both have the /ÉªtÊƒ/ sound in ', 0, '2024-03-12 11:15:07'),
(641, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWhy Did Habib Call Tomiwa Instead Of Salma That He Gave A Ride?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Because Tomiwa is a Muslim and Salma is not Â ', 'Because Salma Gave Him Tomiwa&apos;s Number Instead Of Hers', 'All Of The Above ', 'Because Habib Likes Tomiwa More Than Salma', '', 'B Explanation In the novel &apos;The Life Changer&apos;, Habib called Tomiwa instead of Salma because Salma gave him Tomiwa&apos;s number instead of hers. This was a trick played by Salma to avoid Habib&apos;s advances.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:17:01'),
(642, 17, 'JAMB', 'ENGLISH LANGUAGE', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;From The Novel;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a Href=&quot;https://myschool.ng/classroom/novels/the-life-changer&quot; Target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life Changer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;This Question Is Based On &amp;quot;The Life Changer&amp;quot; Novel.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAda And Ngozi Were From The Imo State And Benue State, While Salma And Tomiwa Were From______ And ______.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'East and North ', 'South And North ', 'North And West', 'West And South', '', 'C Explanation Self-explanatory', 0, '2024-03-12 11:18:33'),
(643, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Babylonian Exile Was A Consequence Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The division of the kingdom into Israel and Judah ', 'The Israelites&apos; Disobedience To God And Their Social Injustices', 'The Israelites&apos; Refusal To Pay Tribute To Babylon ', 'The Assyrian Invasion And Destruction Of Jerusalem', '', 'B Explanation The Babylonian Exile was a consequence of the Israelites&apos; disobedience to God and their social injustices. The Bible records that the Israelites had turned away from God and were worshipping idols, and their society was marked by injust', 0, '2024-03-12 11:29:11'),
(644, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Prophet Confronted King Ahab And Challenged The Prophets Of Baal On Mount Carmel?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Isaiah ', 'Elijah', 'Ezekiel ', 'Jeremiah', '', 'B Explanation The prophet Elijah confronted King Ahab and challenged the prophets of Baal on Mount Carmel. This is recorded in the Book of Kings in the Bible. Elijah&apos;s challenge was a demonstration of God&apos;s power over the false gods of Baal.   ', 0, '2024-03-12 11:31:19'),
(645, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Prophet Warned The People Of Nineveh About God&amp;#39;s Impending Judgment?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Micah ', 'Jonah ', 'Amos', 'Nahum', '', 'B Explanation The prophet Jonah was the one who warned the people of Nineveh about God&apos;s impending judgment. This is recorded in the Book of Jonah in the Bible.   ', 0, '2024-03-12 11:32:49'),
(646, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Downfall Of The Northern Kingdom Of Israel Was Mainly Due To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Invasion by the Philistines Â ', 'Division And Infighting Among Tribes', 'The Rise Of Powerful Neighboring Kingdoms ', 'Rejection Of The Mosaic Law', '', 'D Explanation The downfall of the Northern Kingdom of Israel was mainly due to the rejection of the Mosaic Law. This led to moral decay and spiritual decline, which eventually led to their downfall.   ', 0, '2024-03-12 11:34:47'),
(647, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Book Of Lamentations Is Traditionally Attributed To Which Prophet And Describes The Sorrow And Mourning Over The Fall Of Jerusalem?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ezekiel ', 'Amos', 'Daniel', 'Jeremiah', '', 'D Explanation The Book of Lamentations is traditionally attributed to the prophet Jeremiah. It describes the sorrow and mourning over the fall of Jerusalem in 586 B.C. by the Babylonians. Jeremiah, often referred to as the &apos;weeping prophet&apos;, lam', 0, '2024-03-12 11:36:15'),
(648, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;According To The Apostle Peter, What Will Happen To The Heavens And The Earth On The Day Of The Lord&amp;#39;s Return?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'They will merge into a new dimension ', 'They Will Be Destroyed By Fire ', 'They Will Be Transformed Into Paradise', 'They Will Disappear Completely', '', ' B Explanation According to the Apostle Peter, the heavens and the earth will be destroyed by fire on the day of the Lord&apos;s return. This is mentioned in 2 Peter 3:10, where Peter describes the day of the Lord as a time when the heavens will disappear', 0, '2024-03-12 11:38:32'),
(649, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Prophet Confronted The People With The Challenge Of Rebuilding The Temple After The Exile?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Micah ', 'Haggai', 'Zechariah', 'Ezekiel', '', 'B Explanation The prophet Haggai confronted the people with the challenge of rebuilding the temple after the exile. In the book of Haggai, the prophet encourages the people to rebuild the temple, promising that God&apos;s glory will fill the new temple an', 0, '2024-03-12 11:39:45'),
(650, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Which Book Of The New Testament Do We Find The Account Of The Apostle Paul&amp;#39;s Conversion And Subsequent Missionary Journeys?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Luke', 'Matthew ', 'John ', 'Acts Of The Apostles', '', 'D Explanation The account of the Apostle Paul&apos;s conversion and subsequent missionary journeys is found in the &apos;Acts of the Apostles&apos;. The book of Acts, written by Luke, provides a detailed account of Paul&apos;s dramatic conversion on the r', 0, '2024-03-12 11:40:52'),
(651, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Story Of Gideon Showcases Leadership Qualities Like Humility And Reliance On Divine Guidance During&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The Period of Judges', 'The Conquest Of Canaan', 'The Reign Of David', 'The Babylonian Exile', '', 'A Explanation The story of Gideon is found in the book of Judges in the Bible. Gideon was a judge who led the Israelites to victory over the Midianites. His story is characterized by his humility and reliance on divine guidance, which were key to his lead', 0, '2024-03-12 11:42:13'),
(652, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Gospel Gives The Most Detailed Account Of Jesus&amp;#39; Temptation?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Luke ', 'Mark ', 'John ', 'Matthew', '', 'D Explanation The Gospel of Matthew gives the most detailed account of Jesus&apos; temptation. In Matthew 4:1-11, the writer provides a detailed narrative of how Jesus was led by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:43:32'),
(653, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Book Of Acts, Which Event Symbolizes The Inclusion Of The Gentiles Into The New Covenant?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â The Pentecost experience ', 'The Stoning Of Stephen', 'The Conversion Of Saul (Paul) ', 'The Baptism Of Cornelius', '', 'D Explanation In the book of Acts, the baptism of Cornelius, a Gentile, symbolizes the inclusion of the Gentiles into the new covenant (Acts 10). The other options refer to other significant events in the book of Acts, but they do not symbolize the inclus', 0, '2024-03-12 11:45:09'),
(654, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Which Epistle Does The Apostle Paul Extensively Discuss The Concept Of &amp;quot;New Life In Christ&amp;quot;?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Acts of the Apostles', 'Revelation ', 'Ephesians ', 'Corinthians', '', 'C Explanation The apostle Paul extensively discusses the concept of &apos;New Life in Christ&apos; in the Epistle to the Ephesians. This concept refers to the transformation that occurs in a person&apos;s life when they accept Jesus Christ as their Lord a', 0, '2024-03-12 11:46:15'),
(655, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which City Served As A Central Hub For The Early Church&amp;#39;s Fellowship And Growth?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Athens', 'Rome ', 'Antioch ', 'Jerusalem', '', 'D Explanation Jerusalem served as a central hub for the Early Church&apos;s fellowship and growth. After the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ, the apostles stayed in Jerusalem where they preached and converted many to Christianity.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:47:29'),
(656, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;According To The Gospel Accounts, What Was The First Miracle Performed By Jesus?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Feeding the five thousand ', 'Calming A Storm', 'Â Turning Water Into Wine', 'Healing A Blind Man', '', 'C Explanation According to the Gospel of John (John 2:1-11), the first miracle performed by Jesus was turning water into wine at a wedding in Cana. The other options refer to other miracles performed by Jesus, but they were not his first.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:48:32'),
(657, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Gospel Emphasizes The Role Of The Holy Spirit As The Comforter Or Advocate?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'John ', 'Matthew ', 'Luke', 'Mark', '', 'A Explanation The Gospel of John emphasizes the role of the Holy Spirit as the Comforter or Advocate. In John 14:16, Jesus promises to ask the Father to give another Advocate to help and be with the disciples forever.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:49:38'),
(658, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Prophet Warned The Israelites About The Consequences Of Their Disobedience?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Jonah ', 'Isaiah ', 'Hosea', 'Ezekiel', '', 'C Explanation The prophet Hosea warned the Israelites about the consequences of their disobedience. This is recorded in the Book of Hosea in the Bible.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:51:39'),
(659, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;How Did The Early Christian Community In Acts Make Decisions About The Distribution Of Resources To The Needy?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'They left it to chance and luck ', 'They Appointed Deacons To Oversee The Process', 'They Gave Everything To The Apostles For Distribution ', 'They Relied On The Guidance Of Local Rulers', '', ' B Explanation In the book of Acts, the early Christian community appointed deacons to oversee the distribution of resources to the needy. This was done to ensure fairness and to allow the apostles to focus on prayer and the ministry of the word (Acts 6:1', 0, '2024-03-12 11:53:42'),
(660, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Jesus Often Referred To Himself As The &amp;quot;Good Shepherd.&amp;quot; Which Gospel Contains This Metaphor?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Matthew', 'Luke', 'Mark', 'John', '', 'D Explanation The metaphor of Jesus referring to Himself as the &apos;Good Shepherd&apos; is found in the Gospel of John, specifically in John 10:11 and 10:14. In these verses, Jesus uses the metaphor to illustrate His care and sacrifice for His followers', 0, '2024-03-12 11:56:14'),
(661, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Prophet Is Associated With The &amp;quot;valley Of Dry Bones&amp;quot; Vision, Symbolizing The Restoration Of Israel From Exile?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ezekiel ', 'Daniel ', 'Jeremiah', 'Â Zechariah', '', 'A Explanation The prophet associated with the &quot;valley of dry bones&quot; vision is Ezekiel. In the book of Ezekiel, chapter 37, Ezekiel has a vision where he is set in the middle of a valley full of dry bones. He prophesies to these bones that they w', 0, '2024-03-12 11:57:21'),
(662, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Decision Did Pilate&amp;#39;s Wife Make When She Had A Dream About Jesus?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'She kept the dream to herself ', 'She Warned Pilate Not To Get Involved', 'She Sought Advice From The Chief Priests', 'She Urged Pilate To Release Jesus Immediately', '', 'B Explanation In Matthew 27:19, Pilate&apos;s wife sent him a message warning him not to have anything to do with Jesus because she had suffered a great deal in a dream because of him. This shows that she warned Pilate not to get involved with Jesus.', 0, '2024-03-12 11:58:46'),
(663, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;During The Trial Before Pontius Pilate, Which Roman Custom Allowed The Release Of One Prisoner During Passover?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Barabbas ', 'Pax Romana', 'Prima Nocte ', 'Quinquennium', '', 'B Explanation It was a period of Peace.', 0, '2024-03-12 12:01:07'),
(664, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In A Diverse And Multicultural Society, Civic Responsibility Includes&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Promoting stereotypes and prejudice', 'Isolating Oneself From People Of Different Backgrounds ', 'Disrespecting Other Cultures And Beliefs ', 'Embracing Diversity And Promoting Inclusivity', '', 'D Explanation In a diverse and multicultural society, civic responsibility includes embracing diversity and promoting inclusivity. This means respecting and valuing the differences among people, including their backgrounds, cultures, and beliefs, and prom', 0, '2024-03-12 12:05:21'),
(665, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Prophet Who Emphasized The Concept Of &amp;quot;the Day Of The Lord&amp;quot; As A Time Of Judgment And Salvation Was&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Amos ', 'Habakkuk', 'Joel ', 'Zephaniah', '', 'C Explanation The prophet Joel emphasized the concept of &quot;the day of the Lord&quot; as a time of judgment and salvation. In the book of Joel, the &apos;day of the Lord&apos; is described as a time when God will judge His enemies and save His people. ', 0, '2024-03-12 12:06:31'),
(666, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Gospel Of Matthew, Which Group Of Religious Leaders Were Particularly Hostile Towards Jesus?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Zealots ', 'Sadducees ', 'Pharisees ', 'Â Essenes', '', 'C Explanation The Pharisees were particularly hostile towards Jesus, according to the Gospel of Matthew. They often challenged Jesus&apos; authority and teachings, leading to many confrontations.', 0, '2024-03-12 12:07:38'),
(667, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Prophet Who Spoke Extensively About The Restoration Of Israel And The Coming Of The Messiah Was&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Zephaniah ', 'Micah ', 'Malachi', 'Obadiah', '', 'C Explanation The prophet Malachi spoke extensively about the restoration of Israel and the coming of the Messiah. In the book of Malachi, he prophesies about the coming of the &apos;messenger&apos; who will prepare the way for the Lord. This is interpret', 0, '2024-03-12 12:08:41'),
(668, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Prophet Had A Vision Of A &amp;quot;wheel Within A Wheel,&amp;quot; Symbolizing God&amp;#39;s Divine Presence And Sovereignty?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Daniel ', 'Ezekiel', 'Amos ', 'Joel', '', 'B Explanation The prophet Ezekiel had a vision of a &quot;wheel within a wheel,&quot; which is recorded in the Book of Ezekiel in the Bible. This vision symbolizes God&apos;s divine presence and sovereignty, showing that God is omnipresent and has control', 0, '2024-03-12 12:09:46'),
(669, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Which Gospel Do We Find The Parable Of The Good Samaritan?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Luke', 'Matthew ', 'John ', 'Mark', '', 'A Explanation The Parable of the Good Samaritan is found in the Gospel of Luke, specifically in Luke 10:25-37. In this parable, Jesus uses a Samaritan, considered an outsider by the Jews, as an example of a neighbor who showed mercy to a man who was robbe', 0, '2024-03-12 12:10:48'),
(670, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The New Covenant Is Based On&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Keeping the Ten Commandments ', 'Human Efforts And Good Deeds ', 'Â Faith In Jesus Christ And His Sacrifice', 'Strict Adherence To Religious Rituals', '', 'C Explanation The new covenant, as described in the New Testament of the Bible, is based on faith in Jesus Christ and His sacrifice. This is a shift from the old covenant, which was based on adherence to the Law (the Ten Commandments and other laws). The ', 0, '2024-03-12 12:12:05'),
(671, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Significant Event Led To The Division Of Languages Among Humankind?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The Exodus ', 'The Flood', 'The Tower Of Babel', 'The Crucifixion', '', 'C Explanation The significant event that led to the division of languages among humankind was the Tower of Babel. This is recorded in Genesis 11:1-9 in the Bible.', 0, '2024-03-12 12:13:12'),
(672, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Nahum&amp;#39;s Prophecy Mainly Focused On The Impending Doom Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Egypt ', 'Israel ', 'Nineveh ', 'Babylon', '', 'C Explanation Nahum&apos;s prophecy mainly focused on the impending doom of Nineveh. The Book of Nahum in the Bible is essentially an oracle of judgment against the city of Nineveh, which was the capital of the Assyrian Empire.', 0, '2024-03-12 12:14:17'),
(673, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Apostle Paul&amp;#39;s Life In Acts Exemplifies God&amp;#39;s Sovereignty Through&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'His unwavering devotion to Jewish traditions ', 'His Escape From Imprisonment Through Supernatural Means', 'His Transformation From A Persecutor To A Proclaimer Of The Gospel', 'His Ability To Convert Everyone He Encountered', '', 'C Explanation The Apostle Paul&apos;s life in Acts exemplifies God&apos;s sovereignty through his transformation from a persecutor to a proclaimer of the Gospel. Before his conversion, Paul (then known as Saul) was a zealous persecutor of Christians. Howe', 0, '2024-03-12 12:40:41'),
(674, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Setting Boundaries And Rules For Children Helps Them&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Develop a sense of discipline and responsibility', 'Become Isolated From Their Peers ', 'Rebel Against Authority Figures', 'Develop A Fear Of Their Parents', '', 'A Explanation Setting boundaries and rules for children helps them develop a sense of discipline and responsibility. Boundaries provide a safe space for children to explore and understand their environment, while rules guide their behavior and actions, te', 0, '2024-03-12 12:42:05'),
(675, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;According To The Gospels, What Was The Profession Of Peter And Andrew Before Becoming Disciples Of Jesus?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Tentmakers ', 'Tax Collectors', 'Shepherds ', 'Â Fishermen', '', 'D Explanation Peter and Andrew were fishermen before they became disciples of Jesus. This is stated in the Gospels, where Jesus tells them to follow him and he will make them &apos;fishers of men&apos;.', 0, '2024-03-12 12:42:58'),
(676, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Event Marked The Beginning Of The Early Church&amp;#39;s Fellowship?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The crucifixion of Jesus', 'Pentecost', 'The Resurrection Of Jesus ', 'The Last Supper', '', ' B Explanation The event that marked the beginning of the Early Church&apos;s fellowship was Pentecost. This is when the Holy Spirit descended upon the apostles, as recorded in Acts 2. The resurrection of Jesus, the crucifixion of Jesus, and the Last Supp', 0, '2024-03-12 12:45:23'),
(677, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;How Do The Gospels Portray God&amp;#39;s Sovereignty Concerning Human Salvation?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â It is only accessible to a select few ', 'Â It Is Exclusively Determined By Human Choices ', 'It Is Based On God&apos;s Grace And Mercy', 'It Depends On Human Effort And Achievements', '', 'C Explanation The Gospels portray God&apos;s sovereignty concerning human salvation as being based on God&apos;s grace and mercy. This is evident in passages such as Ephesians 2:8-9, which states that it is by grace through faith that we are saved, not by', 0, '2024-03-12 12:46:56'),
(678, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Who Were The Three Disciples Who Witnessed The Transfiguration With Jesus?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Matthew, Mark, and Luke ', 'Â Andrew, Simon, And Philip', 'Mary, Martha, And Lazarus', 'Peter, James, And John', '', 'D Explanation The three disciples who witnessed the Transfiguration with Jesus were Peter, James, and John. This event is recorded in all three Synoptic Gospels (Matthew 17:1-9, Mark 9:2-8, Luke 9:28-36).', 0, '2024-03-12 12:47:58'),
(679, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Leadership Qualities Such As Integrity And Honesty Are Illustrated In The Life Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Judas Iscariot ', 'Joseph ', 'Jezebel', 'Jacob', '', 'B Explanation Leadership qualities such as integrity and honesty are illustrated in the life of Joseph. This is evident in his life story as recorded in the Book of Genesis in the Bible.   ', 0, '2024-03-12 12:49:11'),
(680, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Law Was Given To Humanity Primarily To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Bring condemnation ', 'Guide Them In Righteous Living ', 'Establish A Covenant With God ', 'Save Them From Sin', '', 'B Explanation The law was given to humanity primarily to guide them in righteous living. The law provides a moral and ethical framework for humans to follow, which helps them distinguish between right and wrong and guides their actions and decisions. It d', 0, '2024-03-12 12:51:11'),
(681, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Gospel Of Matthew, Jesus Walks On Water To Meet His Disciples In A Boat. Which Disciple Attempts To Walk On Water But Begins To Sink?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Peter ', 'James ', 'Andrew ', 'John', '', 'A Explanation In the Gospel of Matthew (Matthew 14:22-33), Peter is the disciple who attempts to walk on water to meet Jesus but begins to sink because of his doubt. The other options refer to other disciples who did not attempt to walk on water in this a', 0, '2024-03-12 12:52:45'),
(682, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Event In The Old Testament Marked The Beginning Of The Exodus Of The Israelites From Egypt, Eventually Leading To The Ten Commandments?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Passover ', 'The Last Supper', 'Crossing Of The Jordan River', 'Building Of The Ark Of The Covenant', '', 'A Explanation The event in the Old Testament that marked the beginning of the Exodus of the Israelites from Egypt, eventually leading to the Ten Commandments, was the Passover. During the Passover, God spared the Israelites from the final plague in Egypt ', 0, '2024-03-12 12:53:46'),
(683, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Divine Love In Christianity Is Primarily Expressed Through&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Rituals and ceremonies ', 'Church Attendance', 'God&apos;s Grace And Mercy', 'The Ten Commandments', '', ' C Explanation Divine love in Christianity is primarily expressed through God&apos;s grace and mercy. This is evident in the Christian belief that God sent His Son, Jesus Christ, to die for the sins of humanity, offering forgiveness and eternal life to al', 0, '2024-03-12 12:56:43'),
(684, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Prophet From The Old Testament Strongly Condemned The Greed Of The Wealthy And Powerful?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ezekiel ', 'Isaiah ', 'Amos', 'Jeremiah', '', 'C Explanation The prophet Amos strongly condemned the greed of the wealthy and powerful. Amos was a shepherd and a farmer before God called him to be a prophet. He was an outsider from Judah who was called to deliver a message to Israel. His message was o', 0, '2024-03-12 12:58:08'),
(685, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Was The Name Of The High Priest Who Played A Prominent Role In Opposing The Early Christian Movement?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Annas ', 'Caiaphas ', 'Gamaliel ', 'Nicodemus', '', 'B Explanation Caiaphas was the high priest who played a prominent role in opposing the early Christian movement. He was the one who plotted to kill Jesus after the raising of Lazarus, as mentioned in John 11:49-50. He also presided over the Sanhedrin tria', 0, '2024-03-12 12:59:01'),
(686, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Who Was The First Gentile To Receive The Holy Spirit And Be Baptized, As Mentioned In Acts?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Philip ', 'Timothy ', 'Cornelius ', 'Barnabas', '', 'C Explanation The first Gentile to receive the Holy Spirit and be baptized, as mentioned in the book of Acts, was Cornelius. This event is recorded in Acts 10, where Peter is shown in a vision that the Gospel is for all people, not just the Jews, leading ', 0, '2024-03-12 13:01:39'),
(687, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Which Gospel Does Jesus Say, &amp;quot;Before Abraham Was, I Am&amp;quot;?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Luke', 'Matthew ', 'John ', 'Mark', '', 'C Explanation The statement, &quot;Before Abraham was, I am&quot; is found in the Gospel of John, specifically John 8:58. Here, Jesus is declaring His eternal existence and His identity as God. The phrase &apos;I am&apos; is a direct reference to God&apos', 0, '2024-03-12 13:02:34'),
(688, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Epistle Encourages Believers To &amp;quot;eagerly Desire Spiritual Gifts, Especially The Gift Of Prophecy&amp;quot;?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1 Corinthians ', 'Ephesians ', 'Romans ', '1 Timothy', '', 'A Explanation The quote &apos;eagerly desire spiritual gifts, especially the gift of prophecy&apos; is from 1 Corinthians 14:1. Therefore, the epistle that encourages believers to eagerly desire spiritual gifts, especially the gift of prophecy, is 1 Corin', 0, '2024-03-12 13:03:45'),
(689, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Context Of Prayer, What Does &amp;quot;intercession&amp;quot; Mean?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Personal requests ', 'Praying For Others', 'Thanksgiving', 'Silent Meditation', '', 'B Explanation Intercession in the context of prayer refers to the act of intervening on behalf of another through prayer. This is often done by praying for others, making requests to God on their behalf. Therefore, the correct answer is &apos;Praying for ', 0, '2024-03-12 13:08:34'),
(690, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;David&amp;#39;s Skill In Playing The Harp Made Him A Favorite Musician In The Court Of Which King?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'King Herod ', 'Pharaoh Of Egypt ', 'King Saul', 'King Nebuchadnezzar', '', 'C Explanation David&apos;s skill in playing the harp made him a favorite musician in the court of King Saul. This is documented in the Bible, specifically in the book of 1 Samuel 16:23. Whenever King Saul was troubled by an evil spirit, David would play t', 0, '2024-03-12 13:09:33'),
(691, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;True Religion In Christianity Emphasizes The Importance Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Material wealth and prosperity', 'Â Rigid Adherence To Traditions ', 'Isolation From The World', 'Unity Among Believers', '', 'D Explanation True religion in Christianity emphasizes the importance of unity among believers. This is based on the teachings of Jesus Christ who prayed for unity among his followers in John 17:21. The other options do not accurately represent the emphas', 0, '2024-03-12 13:10:47'),
(692, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In 1 Corinthians 12, Paul Compares The Church To What Metaphorical Body?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'A tree', 'A Human Body ', 'A Flock Of Sheep', 'Â A Building', '', ' B Explanation In 1 Corinthians 12, Paul uses the metaphor of a human body to describe the Church. He explains that just as a body, though one, has many parts, but all its many parts form one body, so it is with Christ. Therefore, the correct answer is &a', 0, '2024-03-12 13:11:41'),
(693, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is A Prominent Theme In St. James&amp;#39; Epistles?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Faith and works ', 'Love And Forgiveness ', 'The Trinity And Divinity', 'End Times And Prophecy', '', 'A Explanation The Epistle of James emphasizes practical aspects of Christian conduct. It stresses the ethical and moral responsibilities of Christians in dealing with social issues. The prominent theme in St. James&apos; Epistles is &apos;Faith and works&', 0, '2024-03-12 13:12:45'),
(694, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Who Was The Prophet That Warned Israel About The Impending Babylonian Exile?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Hosea ', 'Micah ', 'Jeremiah ', 'Amos', '', ' C Explanation The prophet Jeremiah warned Israel about the impending Babylonian exile. Jeremiah prophesied during the last forty years of Judah, the southern kingdom, warning God&apos;s people of their coming fate if they did not turn from their sins.', 0, '2024-03-12 13:13:39'),
(695, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Gospel Of Mark, Which Group Of People Did Jesus Specifically Mention That We Should Love With All Our Hearts?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'The poor and needy ', 'Family Members', 'Our Enemies', 'Fellow Believers', '', 'C Explanation In the Gospel of Mark, Jesus specifically mentions that we should love our enemies. This is found in Mark 12:30-31, where Jesus states the greatest commandment is to love God with all our heart, soul, mind, and strength, and the second is to', 0, '2024-03-12 13:14:32'),
(696, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In The Epistles, Corruption Is Often Linked To Which Of The Following Vices?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Generosity and benevolence', 'Austerity And Frugality', 'Greed And Selfishness ', 'Tolerance And Acceptance', '', 'C Explanation In the epistles, corruption is often linked to vices such as greed and selfishness. These vices are seen as moral corruption and are often warned against in the teachings of the apostles. Therefore, the correct answer is &apos;Greed and self', 0, '2024-03-12 13:15:44'),
(697, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;David Was Known For His Musical Talents And Was Credited For Composing Many&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Prophecies ', 'Sermons ', 'Psalms ', 'Hymns', '', 'C Explanation David was known for his musical talents and was credited for composing many Psalms. The Book of Psalms in the Bible contains many songs and poems attributed to David. These psalms express a range of human emotions and were often used as hymn', 0, '2024-03-12 13:16:59');
