(700, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Which Gospel(s) Do We Find An Account Of The Triumphal Entry Of Jesus Into Jerusalem?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â Matthew, Mark, John and Luke ', 'Â Luke And John ', 'Matthew And Luke ', 'Â Mark And John', '', 'A Explanation The triumphal entry of Jesus into Jerusalem is an event that is described in all four canonical Gospels. In Matthew 21:1â€“11, Mark 11:1â€“11, Luke 19:28â€“44, and John 12:12â€“19.', 0, '2024-03-12 13:24:17'),
(701, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;What Is The Key To Effective Prayer According To The Selected Epistles?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Persistence', 'Impressive Language ', 'Lengthy Prayers', 'Faith', '', 'D Explanation According to the selected epistles, the key to effective prayer is faith. This is based on the belief that God hears and answers prayers, and that He is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power', 0, '2024-03-12 13:25:16'),
(702, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;According To The Epistles, What Is The Root Cause Of Showing Partiality To Others?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ignorance and lack of knowledge', 'Fear Of Being Judged By Others ', 'Lack Of Self-Confidence ', 'Â Favoring Those Who Can Offer Personal Benefits', '', 'D Explanation According to the epistles, the root cause of showing partiality to others is favoring those who can offer personal benefits. This is a form of selfishness and is contrary to the teachings of the Bible, which encourages believers to treat eve', 0, '2024-03-12 13:27:02'),
(703, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Which Epistle Does The Apostle Peter Remind Believers That They Are Part Of A &amp;quot;chosen Race, A Royal Priesthood, A Holy Nation&amp;quot; While Facing Persecution?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 1 Peter', '1 Corinthians', 'Colossians', 'Galatians', '', ' A Explanation The apostle Peter reminds believers that they are part of a &apos;chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation&apos; in the face of persecution in the epistle of 1 Peter, specifically in 1 Peter 2:9. Therefore, the correct answer is &apos', 0, '2024-03-12 13:28:43'),
(704, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;How Many Books Are There In The New Testament Of The Bible?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '66 ', '12 ', '39', '27', '', 'D Explanation There are 27 books in the New Testament of the Bible. These books include the four Gospels, the Acts of the Apostles, the Epistles, and the book of Revelation.', 0, '2024-03-12 13:31:22'),
(705, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;How Many Recorded Appearances Did Jesus Make After His Resurrection?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '7', '10 ', '12 ', '40', '', 'A Explanation Jesus made 7 recorded appearances after his resurrection. These appearances were to Mary Magdalene, the other women, two disciples on the road to Emmaus, Peter, the ten disciples (Thomas was absent), the eleven disciples (Thomas was present)', 0, '2024-03-12 13:33:20'),
(706, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Who Was The First King Of The Divided Kingdom Of Israel?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Jeroboam', 'Rehoboam', 'David ', 'Solomon', '', 'A Explanation The first king of the divided kingdom of Israel was Jeroboam. After the death of King Solomon, the kingdom of Israel was divided into two: the northern kingdom of Israel and the southern kingdom of Judah. Jeroboam became the king of the nort', 0, '2024-03-12 13:34:05'),
(707, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Epistle Of Romans Is Significant In Discussing The Contrast Between Law And Grace. Who Is The Author Of The Epistle To The Romans?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'James ', 'John ', 'Paul ', 'Peter', '', 'C Explanation The Epistle to the Romans, often shortened to Romans, is the sixth book in the New Testament. Biblical scholars agree that it was composed by the Apostle Paul to explain that salvation is offered through the gospel of Jesus Christ. Hence, Pa', 0, '2024-03-12 13:35:55'),
(708, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Why Did The Pharisees Criticize Jesus During The Triumphal Entry?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'They were jealous of Jesus&apos; popularity ', 'They Thought Jesus Was A Roman Sympathizer', 'They Believed Jesus Was Claiming To Be The Messiah', 'They Were Upset About The Disruption Caused By The Crowd', '', 'C Explanation During the triumphal entry, the Pharisees criticized Jesus because they believed He was claiming to be the Messiah. This is evident in Luke 19:39 where the Pharisees in the crowd said to Jesus, &apos;Teacher, rebuke your disciples!&apos; The', 0, '2024-03-12 13:37:06'),
(709, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE(CRK)', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Epistle Addresses The Issue Of Moral Purity And Living A Sanctified Life Within The Christian Community?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1 Peter', '1 Timothy', 'Titus ', 'Â 2 Corinthians', '', 'B Explanation The First Epistle to Timothy addresses the issue of moral purity and living a sanctified life within the Christian community. In this letter, Paul provides guidance to Timothy, a young leader in the church, on how to conduct himself and lead', 0, '2024-03-12 13:40:22'),
