(799, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;table Border=&quot;1&quot; Cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; Cellspacing=&quot;1&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;#&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Stock Jan&amp;nbsp;1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;2600&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;Purchases&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;4000&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;Carriage Inwards&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;500&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;Sales&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;9000&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;Carriage Outwards&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;500&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Determine The Net Profit&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â â‚¦4,000 ', 'â‚¦4,500 ', 'â‚¦5,000', 'â‚¦1,400', '', 'D Explanation Cost of goods sold = 2600 + 4000 + 500 = 7100  Gross profit = 9000 - 7100 = 1900  Therefore, Net profit = Gross profit - Expenses = 1900 - 500 = â‚¦1400', 0, '2024-03-19 09:19:53'),
(800, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;table Border=&quot;1&quot; Cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; Cellspacing=&quot;1&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;â‚¦&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Balance As Per Cash Book&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;5467&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Uncredited Cheques&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;4410&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;Unpresented Cheques&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 19404&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The Balance As Per Bank Statement Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'â‚¦20,461 ', 'â‚¦21,091', 'â‚¦21,109', 'Â â‚¦19,021', '', 'A Explanation The balance as per bank statement is calculated by adding the balance as per cash book and the unpresented cheques then subtracting the uncredited cheques. Therefore, the balance as per bank statement is â‚¦5467 + â‚¦19404 - â‚¦4410 = â‚¦20,', 0, '2024-03-19 09:24:13'),
(801, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When Goods Are Received From Head Office, Head Office Will Be Credited While&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'sales will be debited  ', 'Requisition Will Be Debited', 'Issue Will Be Debited', 'Purchases Will Be Debited', '', 'D Explanation Goods received from head office Accounting entries: Dr: Purchase account Cr: Head office current account', 0, '2024-03-19 09:25:09'),
(802, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Changes In The Profit Sharing Ratio May Occur As A Result Of&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI. Skill Contributed By Partners&lt;br /&gt;\r\nII. Health Status&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIII. Old Age&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIV. Intangible Asset Increase&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'I, III and IV', 'I And III ', 'I, II And III ', 'I, II And IV', '', 'C Explanation Change in profit sharing ratio may occur as a result of the following: - changes in skill contributed by partners - ill health - old age', 0, '2024-03-19 09:26:45'),
(803, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Given:&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI. Cash Refunds&lt;br /&gt;\r\nII. Debit Note Issued&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIII. Dishnoured Cheque&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIV. Purchases&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Item On The Credit Side Of Purchase Ledger Control Account Includes&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'I, II and IV only  ', 'Â I And IV Only', 'I And II Only ', 'Â I, II And III Only', '', 'B Explanation The item on the credit side of the purchase control account or total creditor control account are: purchase (credit), cash refunds, discount withdrawn, debit note received.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:28:10'),
(804, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Given:&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nI. It Records Subscription In Arrears&lt;br /&gt;\r\nII. Payments Of Liabilities Is Effected&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIII. The Account Does Not Show If Cash Payment Is Revenue Or Capital Expenditure&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIV. It Performs The Same Function As Cash Book&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThe Features Of Receipts And Payment Account Includes:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'III and IV  ', 'I, II And IV', 'II, III And IV', 'I, II And III', '', ' C Explanation The features are: - include capital and revenue items - accruals and prepayments are not included - it is a real account - only actual receipts and payments are recorded - balance represent cash in hand', 0, '2024-03-19 09:29:32'),
(805, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is Used To Service All Operations Of Government?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â general reserve fund  ', 'Consolidated Revenue Fund', 'Special Operational Fund ', 'Consolidated Reserve Fund', '', 'B Explanation Consolidate revenue fund shows the total income derived by the government from all the sources of revenue.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:30:36'),
(806, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Effect Of Transaction When Cash Is Paid Into The Bank Is?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'bank balance decrease and cash balance increase ', 'Cash Balance Decrease And Bank Balance Increase', 'Bank Balance Decrease And Cash Balance Decrease', 'Cash Balance Increase And Bank Balance Increase', '', 'B Explanation When cash is paid into the bank, the cash balance decreases because you are taking cash out of your possession and depositing it into the bank. On the other hand, your bank balance increases because you are adding money to your bank account.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:31:53'),
(807, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of These Is Not A Subsidiary Books?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'sales day book  ', 'Purchase Day Book', 'Credit Note', 'Return Inward Day Book', '', 'C Explanation The subsidiary book is a book of original entr or prime entry which consists of: purchases day book, sales day book, returns inwards day book, returns outward day book, cash book, journal, petty cash book.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:32:56'),
(808, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Salaries In Arrears Is Treated In The Balance Sheet As A&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'current asset ', 'Current Liability ', 'Long Term Liability', 'Fixed Asset', '', 'B Explanation Salaries in arreas is an unpaid salary with amount due from the past. It is treated as current liabilities in the balance sheet.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:34:05'),
(809, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Capital For A Profit Making Organization Is Generated Through&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'gift ', 'Donation ', 'Shares ', 'Subscription', '', 'C Explanation Shares can be issued to the public for subscription. A lot of money can be raised to finance the operation of the business through the issue of new shares to members of the public.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:35:17'),
(810, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;One Of The Options Below Have The Same Features As The Profit And Loss Account In Non-profit Organization&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'non profit account  ', 'Profit And Loss Account', 'Income And Expenditure Account', 'Receipts And Payment Account', '', 'C Explanation The income and expenditure account shows the summary of revenue and running costs of a non-profit making organization. It follows the same principles as the profit and loss account of a trading concern.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:37:22'),
(811, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of These Is Not Method Of Stock Valuation?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â FIFO method  ', 'Base Method', 'Standard Method', 'Â LIFO Method', '', ' C Explanation The methods of stock valuation are: FIFO, LIFO, Weighted Average Price Method, Simple Average Price Method, Base stock method.   ', 0, '2024-03-19 09:43:33'),
(812, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;An Evidence Of Payment Issued To A Government Ministry By A Revenue Collector Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â treasury card  ', 'Payment Voucher', 'Treasury Receipt', 'Receipt Voucher', '', 'D Explanation Receipt voucher are documents used for acknowledgement the receipt of public revenue. They must be issued out anytime revenue is collected by government ministries.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:45:18'),
(813, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Account Where The Profit Are Distributed To The Partner In Their Profit Sharing Ratio In Partnership&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'appropriation account ', 'Profit And Loss Account ', 'Balance Sheet', 'Trading Account', '', 'A Explanation For a partnership, the primary purpose of the appropriation account is to show how profits are distributed among the partners.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:46:50'),
(814, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Main Purpose Of Transaction File Is?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'to record assets and liabilities ', 'To Update Income And Expenses', 'To Make Organization Decision', 'To Update Master Files', '', 'D Explanation A transaction file is used to hold data during transaction processing. The file is later used to update the master file and audit daily, weekly or monthly transactions.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:48:27'),
(815, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;When Starting With The Cash Book Balance In Preparing The Bank Reconciliation Statement, The Followings Are Added Except&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'uncredited cheque', 'Credit Transfer', 'Dividend', 'Unpresented Cheque', '', 'A Explanation When starting with balanace as per cash book, unpresented cheques, dividend, credit transfers are added while uncredited cheques, bank charges, dishonoured cheuqes, standing order are substracted.', 0, '2024-03-19 09:55:57'),
