(844, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Current Assets Are Shown In The Balance Sheet In Order Of Performance As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'debtors, stock, bank and cash ', 'Stock, Debtors, Bank And Cash ', 'Stock, Bank, Debtors And Cash', 'Â Debtors, Stock, Cash And Bank', '', ' B Explanation The current assets are usually listed on the balance sheet in the following order: - inventory (stock) - account receivables e.g debtors - marketables securities - cash and cash equivalent', 0, '2024-03-19 12:28:02'),
(845, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is Found On The Credit Side Of A Profit And Loss Account?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'advertising ', 'Dividend Received', 'Wages And Salaries', 'Bank Charges', '', 'B Explanation Dividend received as as revenue i.e income or money received in trading transactions. It is credited to the profit or loss account.', 0, '2024-03-19 12:29:09'),
(846, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Shares Are Said To Be Authorized When They Are&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'paid -up ', 'Called Up', 'Offered For Sale', 'Subscribed', '', ' C Explanation Authorized shares are defined as the maximum number of shares that a company is legally allowed to issue to investors as per its own determinations', 0, '2024-03-19 12:30:22'),
(847, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Assumption That A Business Will Continue To Exist Into The Foreseeanle Future Is Recognized By A Concept Called&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'matching ', 'Business Entity', 'Going Concern', 'Historical Cost', '', 'C Explanation The going concern concept states that a business will continue to operate for an indefinte period of time or perpectual existence.', 0, '2024-03-19 12:31:50'),
(848, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Short Term Solvency Of A Company Is Determined With ------- Ratio&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'acid test ', 'Gross Profit Margin ', 'Debt To Equity', 'Current', '', 'D Explanation The current or working capital ratio is a test of a business&apos;s short-term solvency â€” its capability to pay its liabilities that come due in the near future (up to one year).   ', 0, '2024-03-19 12:33:04'),
(849, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is Charged To Trading Account?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'rent ', 'Discount Allowed', 'Carriage Inwards', 'Carriage Outwards', '', 'C Explanation Carriage inwards is the cost of transportation charged on goods purchased. It must be added to the goods purchased, hence it is debited to trading account.', 0, '2024-03-19 12:34:08'),
(850, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Expenses Is *not* Apportined In Proportion To Turnover?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'rent ', 'Commission ', 'Discount Allowed', 'Carriage Outwards', '', 'A Explanation Rent is typically not apportioned in proportion to turnover. Rent is a fixed cost, meaning it does not change with the level of output or sales (turnover). It is usually apportioned based on the space occupied by each department or activity,', 0, '2024-03-19 12:35:14'),
(851, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Purchases Ledger Control Account Is Also Known As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'bill payable control account ', 'Credit Purchase Control Account', 'Creditors Control Account', 'Total Purchase', '', 'C Explanation The purchases ledger control account is also known as the creditors control account. This account is used in a business&apos;s accounting to record the total amount owed to suppliers for purchases made on credit. It is a summary account that', 0, '2024-03-19 12:36:26'),
(852, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Accounting Term Used To Describe A Partnership Firm That Stops Operation And Disposes Its Assets Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Amortization ', 'Revaluation ', 'Realization ', 'Dissolution', '', 'D Explanation Dissolution of partnership is the process whereby a partnership is automatically dissolved or brought to an end by the happenings of any event which makes it unlawful to carry on the business.', 0, '2024-03-19 12:37:28'),
(853, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Income And Expenditure Account Is The Same As The --------- Of A Sole Trader&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'balance sheet ', 'Trading Account', 'Profit And Loss Account', 'Cash Book', '', 'C Explanation The income and expenditure account shows the summary of revenue and running cost of a non-profit making organization. It follows the same principles as the profit and loss account of a trading concern.', 0, '2024-03-19 12:38:34'),
(854, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;In Company Account, Dividend Payments Are Effected In Which Of The Following Accounts?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'realization', 'Current ', 'Appropriation', 'Capital', '', 'C Explanation In company accounting, dividend payments are effected in the appropriation account. The appropriation account is a part of the profit and loss account where the net profit is appropriated or distributed among various heads like dividends, ge', 0, '2024-03-19 12:39:30'),
(855, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Which Of The Following Is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;an Advantage Of Control Account?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'difficulty in committing fraud ', 'Â It Can Be Used To Detect Missing Figure', 'Helps To Determine Profit And Loss', 'Helps In Locating Errors', '', 'A Explanation The uses of control account are: - location of errors - prevention of fraud - preparation of interim final account - saves time - easy detection of missing figures', 0, '2024-03-19 12:42:39'),
(856, 17, 'JAMB', 'ACCOUNTS-PRINCIPLES OF ACCOUNTS', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Factory Overheads Are Also Known As&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'direct manufacturing ', 'Direct Expenses ', 'Indirect Cost', 'Direct Labour', '', 'C Explanation Factory overhead are costs necessary for production which are not directly traceable to a specific quantity of physical units e,g factory rent, depreciation, fuel, indirect wages etc.', 0, '2024-03-19 12:43:53'),
