(858, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/PUdEREpCcJVZ3R9xQU56E8ctGdN909nokr99Stpo.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In The Diagram, O Is The Center Of The Circle QRS And&amp;nbsp;&amp;ang;SQR = 28&amp;deg;. Find &amp;ang;ORS.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '560', '280', ' 760 ', '620', '', 'D Explanation âˆ SOR = 2 Ã— 28Â° = 56Â° (angle at the centre is twice the angle at the circumference) From âˆ†SOR |OS| = |OR| (radii) So, âˆ†SOR is isosceles.  âˆ ORS = 1800âˆ’5602=12402     ( base angles of isosceles triangle are equal)  âˆ´ âˆ ORS = 62Â', 0, '2024-03-21 08:01:39'),
