(867, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Interior Angle Of A Regular Polygon Is 6 Times Its Exterior Angle Find The Number Of Sides Of The Polygon.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '12 Â ', '15 ', '10', '14', '', 'D Explanation each interior angle of a polygon = (nâˆ’2)Ã—180n  where n = no of side of a polygon  each exterior angle of a polygon = 360n then  (nâˆ’2)Ã—180n  = 6Ã—  360n = (n - 2) 180 = 2160  = 180n - 360 = 2160  = 180n = 2160 + 360  = 180n = 2520  ther', 0, '2024-03-21 08:28:20'),
