(870, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Find The Roots Of The Equations:&amp;nbsp;3m2&amp;minus;2m&amp;minus;65=0&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', ' (âˆ’5,âˆ’133)', '(5,âˆ’133)', ' (5,133)', '(âˆ’5,133)', '', ' B Explanation Find the roots of the equations: 3m2âˆ’2mâˆ’65=0 = m2âˆ’15m+13mâˆ’65=0 = 3m(m - 5) + 13( m - 5) = 0  ( m - 5)(3m + 13) = 0   m-5 = 0 or 3m + 13 = 0  therefore, m = 5 or âˆ’133 therefore the roots of the quadratic equation = ( 5, âˆ’133)', 0, '2024-03-21 08:34:44'),
(871, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;A Student Measured The Height Of A Pole As 5.98 M Which Is Less Than The Actual Height. If The Percentage Error Is 5%, Find Correct To&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;two&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;d.p The Actual Height Of The Pole.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '6.29m', '7.67m ', '7.18m', '6.65m', '', ' A Explanation %error=5%, measured height = 5.98m  let the actual height = y   error=x - 5.98 (since &apos;y&apos; is more than 5.98)  %error = erroractualheightÃ—100 5% =  yâˆ’5.98yÃ—100 5100=yâˆ’5.98y 5y = 100(y - 5.98)  5y = 100y - 598  5y - 100y = - 5', 0, '2024-03-21 08:35:49'),
(872, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Radius And Height Of A Solid Cylinder Is 8 Cm And 14 Cm Respectively. Find, Correct To&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;two&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;d.p The Total Surface Area.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;(Take&amp;nbsp;&amp;pi;=227)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1,106.29cm2', '1,016.29cm2', '1,106.89cm2', '1,206.27cm2', '', 'A Explanation radius = 8cm , height = 14cm  and Ï€=227 total surface area of a solid cylinder =2Ï€rh+2Ï€r2  = 2Ï€r( h + r )   2Ã—227Ã—8(8+14)  2Ã—227Ã—8Ã—22 77447 = 1,106.29cm2  ', 0, '2024-03-21 08:37:18'),
