(886, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;Write The Name Of A Triangle With The Vertices (1, -3), (6, 2) And (0,4)?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Scalene triangle ', 'Isosceles Triangle', 'Right -Angle Triangle ', 'Equilateral Triangle', '', 'B Explanation   Let A = (1, -3), B = (6, 2) and C = (0,4)  d=(y2âˆ’y1)2+(x2âˆ’x1)2âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆš  |AB| = (2âˆ’(âˆ’3))2+(6âˆ’1)2âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆš   = (2+3)2+(6âˆ’1)2âˆ’âˆ’âˆ', 0, '2024-03-21 09:11:56'),
(887, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Price Of A Shoe Was Decreased By 22%. If The New Price Is $27.3. What Is The Original Price.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '$62.30', '$42.30', '$72.00 ', '$35.00', '', 'D Explanation Let x = original price  A decrease of 22% = (100-22)% = 78% of the original price.  78% of x = 27.30  = 78x100=27.30 78x = 2730  then, x = 273078 x =  35  Therefore, the original price of the shoe was  $35.00.', 0, '2024-03-21 09:13:20'),
