(890, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;The Length Of The Diagonal Of A Square Is 12 Cm. Calculate The Area Of The Square.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '36cm2   ', '48cm2   ', '72cm2', '18cm2', '', 'C Explanation  Let each side be l, then area = l2 Using Pythagoras theorem   l2+l2=122   2l2=144 divide both sides by 2  l2=72 Therefore, the Area of the square is 72cm2     ', 0, '2024-03-21 09:20:27'),
