(892, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;img Src=&quot;https://myschool.ng/storage/classroom/mFIU1oQP44xALPh3XIS9COiDPtZugVsb4Fif2oAQ.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Find The Value Of M In The Diagram Above.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', ' 400', '500', '1300', '1400', '', 'C Explanation  âˆ EHI = âˆ DEH = 40Â° (alternate angles are equal) âˆ BEH = 90Â° (given) âˆ BED = 90Â° - 40Â° = 50Â° âˆ BEF = 180Â° - 50Â° = 130Â° (sum of angles on a straight line is 180o) âˆ BEF = âˆ ABE = 130Â° (alternate angles are equal) âˆ´ m = 130Â', 0, '2024-03-21 09:24:07'),
