(912, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;a. In A Town, Chief X Resides 60 M Away On A Bearing Of 057&amp;deg;&amp;nbsp;from Palace P, While Chief Y Resides On A Bearing Of 150&amp;deg;&amp;nbsp;from The Same Palace P. The Residence Of X And Y Are 180 M Apart.&amp;nbsp;Illustrate The Information In A Diagram.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;b. Find And Correct To&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;three&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;significant Figures, The: I.&amp;nbsp;bearing Of X From Y; Ii.&amp;nbsp;distance Between P And Y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', '.....', '......', '......', '......', '', '  a. the diagram above solution to question a.  bi. Using the sine rule  sinPXY=sinYPX = sin93Â°180=sinY60 cross multiply  sinYÃ—180=sin93Â°Ã—60 sinY = 0.3329  Y = sinâˆ’10.3329 Y = 19.44Â°  the angle between 30Â° and 19.44Â° at Y = 30Â° - 19.44Â° = 10.56', 0, '2024-03-21 10:34:40'),
(913, 17, 'WAEC', 'MATHEMATIC', '2023', '&lt;p&gt;a.&amp;nbsp;Two Regular Polygons P And Q Are Such That The Number Of Sides Of P Is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;twice&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the Number Of Sides Of Q. The Difference Between The Exterior Angle Of P And Q Is 45&amp;deg;.find The Number Of Sides Of P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;b.&amp;nbsp;The Area Of A Semi-circle Is 32&amp;pi;&amp;nbsp;cm2ï¿½ï¿½2. Find, In Terms Of &amp;pi;, The Circumference Of The Semi-circle.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '.....', '......', '......', '......', '', 'a. Let the number of sides of polygon Q be x   therefore, No. of sides of polygon P = 2x  then, 360xâˆ’3602x  =  45,  360xâˆ’180x  = 45    L. C. M = x  360 - 180 = 45x  x = 1804  = 4  therefore, the number of P polygon = 2x = 2 x 4 = 8  b. Area of semi-ci', 0, '2024-03-21 10:35:29'),
