(915, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Group Of Market Women Sell At Least One Of Yam, Plantain And Maize. 12 Of Them Sell Maize, 10 Sell Yam And 14 Sell Plantain. 5 Sell Plantain And Maize, 4 Sell Yam And Maize, 2 Sell Yam And Plantain Only While 3 Sell All The Three Items. How Many Women Are In The Group?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '25 ', '19 ', '18 ', '17', '', 'A Explanation Let the three items be M, Y and P. n{M âˆ© Y} only = 4-3 = 1 n{M âˆ© P) only = 5-3 = 2 n{ Y âˆ© P} only = 2 n{M} only = 12-(1+3+2) = 6 n{Y} only = 10-(1+2+3) = 4 n{P} only = 14-(2+3+2) = 7 n{Mâˆ©Pâˆ©Y} = 3 Number of women in the group = 6+4+', 0, '2024-03-21 10:40:01'),
