(917, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Find The Value Of X If&amp;nbsp;2&amp;radic;x+2&amp;radic;=1x&amp;minus;2&amp;radic;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', ' 3âˆš2+4', '3âˆš2-4', '3-2âˆš2', '4+2âˆš2', '', 'A Explanation Start your solution by cross-multiplying,  2âˆšx+2âˆš=1xâˆ’2âˆš [x - âˆš2] âˆš2  = x + âˆš2  where âˆš2Ã—âˆš2=2   xâˆš2 - âˆš2 * âˆš2 = x + âˆš2  then collect like terms  xâˆš2 - x = âˆš2 + 2  and factorize accordingly to get the unknown.  x', 0, '2024-03-21 10:42:52'),
(918, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If&amp;nbsp;(a2b&amp;minus;3c)34a&amp;minus;1b4c5=apbqcr(ï¿½2ï¿½&amp;minus;3ï¿½)34ï¿½&amp;minus;1ï¿½4ï¿½5=ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½&amp;nbsp;What Is The Value Of P+2q?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '(5/2)', '-(5/4) ', ' -(25/4)', '-10', '', 'D Explanation Hint: apply basic mathematics rules beginning from BODMAS to algebra, and follow solution carefully to arrive at  p = 52 , q = -254  and r = -174    NUMERATOR:   a21âˆ—34           bâˆ’31âˆ—34           c11âˆ—34                            a3', 0, '2024-03-21 10:44:12'),
(919, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Trader Bought 100 Oranges At 5 For N1.20, 20 Oranges Got Spoilt And The Remaining Were Sold At 4 For N1.50. Find The Percentage Gain Or Loss.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '30% gain', '25% Gain', '30% Loss', '25% Loss', '', ' B Explanation Cost price (cp) = (100/5) x N1.20 =N24.00 Selling price (sp) = 100-20 = 80 (80/4) x N1.50 = N30.00  Gain = SP-CP = N30.00-N24.00 = N6.00 Gain% = (gain/CP) x 100 = 25%', 0, '2024-03-21 10:45:31'),
