(925, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Binary Operation * Is Defined By A*b = Ab+a+b For Any Real Number A And B. If The Identity Element Is Zero, Find The Inverse Of 2 Under This Operation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2/3', '1/2 ', ' -1/2', '-2/3', '', ' D Explanation aâˆ—aâˆ’1=aaâˆ’1+a+aâˆ’1=e   if e = 0  2.2âˆ’1+2+2âˆ’1=0 collecting like terms, we have: 3.2âˆ’1+2=0   = 2âˆ’1  = -23', 0, '2024-03-21 10:53:23'),
(926, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Factorize Completely&amp;nbsp;x2+2xy+y2+3x+3y&amp;minus;18ï¿½2+2ï¿½ï¿½+ï¿½2+3ï¿½+3ï¿½&amp;minus;18.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', ' (x+y+6)(x+y-3) ', '(X-Y-6)(X-Y+3)', '(X-Y+6)(X-Y-3) ', '(X+Y-6)(X+Y+3)', '', 'A Explanation Expand the options and collect like terms to check which gives the presented expression.  Expansion of Options A:  (x+y+6)(x+y-3) â†’ x2+xyâˆ’3x+xy+y2âˆ’3y+6x+6yâˆ’18    Collect like terms: x2+xy+xy+y2+6xâˆ’3x+6yâˆ’3yâˆ’18 = x2+2xy+y2+3x+3yâ', 0, '2024-03-21 10:54:46'),
