(928, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Three Consecutive Positive Integers K, L And M Are Such That L22&amp;nbsp;= 3(k+m). Find The Value Of M.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4 ', '5 ', '6 ', 'Â 7', '', 'D Explanation l2  = 3 (k + m)  Since they are consecutive positive numbers, we have  l = k+1, m = k+2.  â†’  (k+1)2  = 3(k + k + 2)  k2  + 2k + 1 = 3(2k + 2)  k2  + 2k + 1 = 6k + 6  k2  + 2k - 6k + 1 - 6 = 0  k2  - 4k - 5 = 0  k2  - 5k + k - 5 = 0  k(k - ', 0, '2024-03-21 10:56:40'),
(929, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Express &amp;nbsp;1x3&amp;minus;11ï¿½3&amp;minus;1in Partial Fractions&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', ' 13(1xâˆ’1âˆ’(x+2)x2+x+1)', '13(1xâˆ’1âˆ’xâˆ’2x2+x+1)', '(1xâˆ’1âˆ’(xâˆ’2)x2+x+1)', '13(1xâˆ’1âˆ’(xâˆ’1)x2âˆ’xâˆ’1)  ', '', 'A Explanation 1x3âˆ’1 x3âˆ’1=(xâˆ’1)(x2+x+1) 1x3âˆ’1=Axâˆ’1+Bx+Cx2+x+1 1x3âˆ’1=A(x2+x+1)+(Bx+C)(xâˆ’1)x3âˆ’1 Comparing the two sides of the equation,  A+B=0...(1) Aâˆ’B+C=0...(2) Aâˆ’C=1...(3) From (3), C=Aâˆ’1 , putting that in (2),  Aâˆ’B=âˆ’CâŸ¹Aâˆ’B=1', 0, '2024-03-21 10:58:12'),
(930, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;The First Term Of A Geometric Progression Is Twice Its Common Ratio. Find The Sum Of The First Two Terms Of The G.P If Its Sum To Infinity Is 8.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 8/5 ', '8/3', '72/25', '56/9', '', 'C Explanation Let the common ratio be r so that the first term is 2r.  Sum, s = a1âˆ’r  ie. 8 = 2r1âˆ’r   8(1-r) = 2r,  8 - 8r = 2r  8 = 2r + 8r  8 = 10r  r = 45 .  where common ratio (r) = secondterm(n2)firstterm(a) ,  r = n22r r = 45  and a = 2r or 85 4', 0, '2024-03-21 10:59:15'),
