(933, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Man 1.7m Tall Observes A Bird On Top Of A Tree At An Angle Of 30&amp;deg;. If The Distance Between The Man&amp;#39;s Head And The Bird Is 25m, What Is The Height Of The Tree?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '26.7m ', '14.2m', '1.7+(253âˆš3m', ' 1.7+(252âˆš2m', '', 'B Explanation Hint: Make a sketch forming a right angled triangle. Let x = height of the tree above the man. Such that x/25 = sin 30.  x = 12.5m  The height of the tree = 12.5 + 1.7  = 14.2 m', 0, '2024-03-21 11:02:44'),
