(935, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Tangent To The Acute Angle Between The Lines 2x + Y = 3 And 3x - 2y = 5.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '-7/4 ', '7/8', '7/4', 'Â 7/2', '', 'C Explanation Let Ï•  be the angle between the two lines.  tan Ï•  = m1âˆ’m21+m1m2 where m1  = slope of line 1; m2  = slope of line 2.  Line 1: 2x + y = 3 âŸ¹  y = 3 - 2x.  Line 2: 3x - 2y = 5 âŸ¹  -2y = 5 - 3x.  y = 32 x - 52 .  m1  = -2, m2  = 32 .  tan', 0, '2024-03-21 11:04:40'),
