(950, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If 3141010&amp;nbsp;- 25677&amp;nbsp;= 340xï¿½, Find X.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '7 ', '8 ', '9', '10', '', 'A Explanation 31410âˆ’2567=340x  Convert 2567 and 340x to base 10, such that: 314 - 139 = 3x2 + 4x =&gt; 3x2  + 4x - 175 = 0 (quadratic) Factorising, (x - 7) (3x + 25) = 0, either x = 7 or x = -25/3 ( but x cannot be negative)  Therefore, x = 7.', 0, '2024-03-21 11:25:22'),
(951, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Simplify&amp;nbsp;3(2n+1)&amp;minus;4(2n&amp;minus;1)2n+1&amp;minus;2n&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2n+1', '2n-1', ' 4 ', '1/4', '', 'C Explanation Start by expanding 3(2n+1)âˆ’4(2nâˆ’1)2n+1âˆ’2n :  3Ã—2nÃ—21âˆ’22Ã—2nÃ—2âˆ’12nÃ—2âˆ’2n NUMERATOR : 2n  (  31  X 21   -  22  X 2âˆ’1  )  --&gt; 2n  ( 3 X 2 â€” 4 X 12  )  --&gt; 2n  ( 6 - 2 )   --&gt; 2n  (4)  DENOMINATOR : 2n  ( 21   -  1 ) ', 0, '2024-03-21 11:26:55'),
(952, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If&amp;nbsp;P3446&amp;minus;23P26=2PP26ï¿½3446&amp;minus;23ï¿½26=2ï¿½ï¿½26, Find The Value Of The Digit P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2', '3 ', '4 ', '5', '', ' D Explanation Convert everything to base 10 and collect like terms, such that  210Pâˆ’42P=434+406 168P=840 P=840/168=5', 0, '2024-03-21 11:28:32'),
(953, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Binary Operation * Is Defined By A * B = Abï¿½. If A * 2 = 2 - A, Find The Possible Values Of A.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1, -1', 'Â 1, 2', '2, -2', '1, -2', '', 'D Explanation a * b = ab a * 2 = a2  = 2 - a  a2  + a - 2 = 0  a2  + 2a - a - 2 = 0  a(a+2) - 1(a+2) = 0  (a-1)(a+2) = 0  a = 1, -2', 0, '2024-03-21 11:29:24'),
(954, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Inverse Of P Under The Binary Operation * Defined By P*q = P + Q - Pq, Where P And Q Are Real Numbers And Zero Is The Identity&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â p ', 'P -1', 'P/(P-1) ', 'P/(P+1)', '', 'C Explanation If P-1 is the inverse of P and O is the identity, Then P-1 * P = P * P-1 = 0 i.e. P-1 + P - P-1.P = 0 P-1 - P-1.P = -P P-1(1 - P) = -P P-1 = -P/(P-1) = P/(P-1)', 0, '2024-03-21 11:32:14'),
(955, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Evaluate (1/2 - 1/4 +&amp;nbsp;1/8 - 1/16 + ...) - 1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2/3 ', 'Zero', 'Â -2/3', '-1', '', 'C Explanation S = a/(1-r), where a = 1/2, r = -1/2.  S = 1/2 3/2 = 1/2 x 3/2 = 1/3. 1/3 - 1 = -2/3', 0, '2024-03-21 11:33:34'),
(956, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;if (x - 1), (x + 1) And (x - 2) Are Factors Of The Polynomial Ax3&amp;nbsp;+ Bx2&amp;nbsp;+ Cx - 1, Find A, B, C In That Order.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â -1/2, 1., 1/2', '1/2, 1, 1/2', '1/2, 1, -1/2 ', '1/2, -1, 1/2', '', 'A Explanation This is a polynomial of the 3rd order, thus x should have three answers. Use the factors given to get values of x as 1, -1 and -2.  Form three equations, and carry out elimination and subsequent substitution to get a = -1/2, b = 1, and c = 1', 0, '2024-03-21 11:34:37'),
(957, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Trader Realizes 10x - X22&amp;nbsp;naira Profit From The Sale Of X Bags On Corn. How Many Bags Will Give Him The Desired Profit?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4 Â ', '5', '6 ', '7', '', 'B Explanation y = 10x - x2  dy/dx = 10 - 2x As dy/dx = 0, 10 - 2x = 0 2x = 10 x = 5', 0, '2024-03-21 11:35:40'),
(958, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Solve The Inequality 2 - X &amp;gt; X22.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â x &lt; -2 or x &gt; 1 Â ', 'X &gt; 2 Or X&lt; -1 ', '-1 &lt; X &lt; 2', '-2 &lt; X &lt; 1', '', ' D Explanation 2 - x &gt; x2 2 - x - x2  &gt; 0  (x+2)(x-1) &lt; 0  Either (x + 2) &gt; 0 and (x - 1) &lt; 0.  x + 2 &gt; 0 âŸ¹  x &gt; -2.  -2 &lt; x &lt; 1', 0, '2024-03-21 11:37:00'),
(959, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If &amp;alpha; And &amp;beta; Are The Roots Of The Equation 3x22&amp;nbsp;+ 5x - 2 = 0, Find The Value Of 1/&amp;alpha; + 1/&amp;beta;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '-5/3 ', '-2/3', '1/2', 'Â 5/2', '', ' D Explanation 1/Î± + 1/Î² = Î²+Î±/Î±Î² 3x2  + 5x - 2 = 0 x2  + 5x/3 - 2/3 = 0 Î±Î² = -2/3 Î²+Î± = -5/3  Thus; Î²+Î±/Î±Î² = -5/3 Ã·  -2/3 = 5/2', 0, '2024-03-21 11:38:22'),
(960, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Frustrum Of Pyramid With Square Base Has Its Upper And Lower Sections As Squares Of Sizes 2m And 5m Respectively And The Distance Between Them 6m. Find The Height Of The Pyramid From Which The Frustrum Was Obtained.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 8.0 m', '8.4 M', '9.0 M', '10.0 M', '', 'D Explanation The lateral view of the frustrum    tanÎ¸=61.5=4 Î¸=tanâˆ’14=75.96Â° Extending to the full height of the pyramid, we have    The height of the pyramid which formed the frustrum = (6 + x)m,  tan75.96=6+x2.5 6+x=2.5Ã—4=10.0 âˆ´The height of th', 0, '2024-03-21 11:39:24'),
(961, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;P Is A Point On One Side Of The Straight Line UV And P Moves In The Same Direction As UV. If The Straight Line ST Is On The Locus Of P And Angle VUS = 60&amp;deg;, Find Angle UST.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '310Â°', '130Â°', '80Â°', '50Â°', '', 'B Explanation Make a good sketch of the question, and follow this steps. Since ST is parallel to UV =&gt; angle USR = 50Â°(alternate to VUS. Angle UST = 180Â° - 50Â° = 130Â° (angle on a straight line)', 0, '2024-03-21 11:40:34'),
(962, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;An Equilateral Triangle Of Side &amp;radic;3cm Is Inscribed In A Circle. Find The Radius Of The Circle.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 2/3 cm ', '2 Cm ', '1 Cm ', '3 Cm', '', 'C Explanation Since the inscribed triangle is equilateral, therefore the angles at all the points = 60Â°  Using the formula for inscribed circle,   2R = asinA=bsinB=csinC where R = radius of the circle; a, b and c are the sides of the triangle.  â‡’ 2R = ', 0, '2024-03-21 11:41:41'),
(963, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;3y = 4x - 1 And Ky = X + 3 Are Equations Of Two Straight Lines. If The Two Lines Are Perpendicular To Each Other, Find K.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '-4/3', '-3/4', '3/4', 'Â 4/3', '', ' A Explanation Grad of 3y = 4x - 1 y = 4x/3 - 1/3 Grad = 4/3  Grad of Ky = x + 3 y = x/k + 3/4 Grad = 1/k  Since two lines are perpendicular, 1/k = -3/4 -3k = 4 k = -4/3', 0, '2024-03-21 11:42:56'),
(964, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;In A Regular Polygon, Each Interior Angle Doubles Its Corresponding Exterior Angle. Find The Number Of Sides Of The Polygon.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 8 ', '6', '4', '3', '', 'B Explanation 2x + x = 180Â°, =&gt; 3x = 180Â°, and thus x = 60Â°  Each exterior angle = 60Â° but size of ext. angle = 360Â°/n Therefore 60Â° = 360Â°/n n = 360Â°/60Â° = 6 sides', 0, '2024-03-21 11:45:29'),
(965, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Predator Moves In A Circle Of Radius &amp;radic;2 Centre (0,0), While A Prey Moves Along The Line Y = X. If 0&amp;nbsp;&amp;le;&amp;le;&amp;nbsp;x&amp;nbsp;&amp;le;&amp;le;&amp;nbsp;2, At Which Point(s) Will They Meet?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '(1,1) only ', '(1,1) And (1,2)', '(0,0) And (1,1) ', '(âˆš2,âˆš2) Only', '', 'A Explanation x2 + y2 = (âˆš2)2 x2 + y2 = 2 but y = x  Thus; x2 + x2 = 2 2x2 = 2 x2 = + or - 1  But x2 + y2 = 2 12 + y2 = 2 1 + y2 = 2 y2 = 2 - 1 y2 = 1 y = + or - 1  Thus point (x,y) = (1,1) only.', 0, '2024-03-21 11:46:54'),
(966, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Value Of&amp;nbsp;&amp;int;&amp;pi;0cos2&amp;theta;&amp;minus;1sin2&amp;theta;d&amp;theta;&amp;int;0ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½2ï¿½&amp;minus;1ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½2ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ï€ ', 'Î /2', 'Â -Î /2 ', 'Â -Î ', '', 'D Explanation âˆ«Ï€0cos2Î¸âˆ’1sin2Î¸dÎ¸=âˆ«Ï€0âˆ’sin2Î¸sin2Î¸=âˆ«Ï€0dÎ¸=âˆ’Ï€', 0, '2024-03-21 11:47:55'),
(967, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If Y = 2x - Sin2x, Find Dy/dx When X = &amp;pi;/4&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ï€ ', 'Â -Î ', 'Â Î /2', '-Î /2', '', 'D Explanation y = 2x cos2x - sin2x dy/dx = 2 cos2x +(-2x sin2x) - 2 cos2x = 2 cos2x - 2x sin2x - cos2x = -2x sin2x = -2 x (Ï€/4) sin2 x (Ï€/4) = -(Ï€/2) x 1 = -(Ï€/2)', 0, '2024-03-21 11:48:59'),
(968, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Bowl Is Designed By Revolving Completely The Area Enclosed By Y = X2&amp;nbsp;- 1, Y = 3 And X &amp;ge; 0 Around The Axis. What Is The Volume Of This Bowl?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 7Ï€ cubic units ', '15Ï€/2 Cubic Units', '8Ï€ Cubic Units', '17Ï€/2 Cubic Units', '', ' B Explanation âˆ«30 Ï€(y+1) dy = Ï€[y2 + y30 = Ï€(9/2 + 3) = 15Ï€/2', 0, '2024-03-21 11:50:05'),
(969, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If The Volume Of A Hemisphere Is Increasing At A Steady Rate Of 18&amp;pi; M33&amp;nbsp;s&amp;minus;1&amp;minus;1, At What Rate Is Its Radius Changing When Its Is 6m?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2.50m/s ', '2.00 M/S ', '0.25 M/S ', 'Â 0.20 M/S', '', 'C Explanation V=23Ï€r3 Given: dVdt=18Ï€m3sâˆ’1 dVdt=dVdrÃ—drdt dVdr=2Ï€r2 18Ï€=2Ï€r2Ã—drdt drdt=18Ï€2Ï€r2=9r2 The rate of change of the radius when r = 6m,  drdt=962=14 = 0.25msâˆ’1', 0, '2024-03-21 11:50:58'),
(970, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;X And Y Are Two Events. The Probability Of X Or Y Is 0.7 And That Of X Is 0.4. If X And Y Are Independent, Find The Probability Of Y.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '0.30', '0.50 ', '0.57 ', '1.80', '', 'A Explanation P (X or Y) = P(X) + P(Y), when they are independent as given. 0.7 = 0.4 + P(Y) P(Y) = 0.7 - 0.4 = 0.30', 0, '2024-03-21 11:51:51'),
(971, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If The Mean Of The Numbers 0, (x+2), (3x+6), And (4x+8) Is 4, Find Their Mean Deviation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '0.0', '2', '3', '4', '', 'C Explanation Mean = {0 + (x+2) + (3x+6) + (4x+8)}/4 = 4 =&gt; 0 + (x+2) + (3x+6) + (4x+8) = 16 8x + 16 = 16 x = 0  Now prepare a table showing the deviation of each of 0, (x+2), (3x+6) and (4x+8), adding the deviations will give 12.  Thus M.D = 12/4 = 3', 0, '2024-03-21 11:52:53'),
(972, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;In How Many Ways Can The Word MATHEMATICS Be Arranged?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '11!/(9! 2!) ', '11!/(9! 2! 2!) ', '11!/(2! 2! 2!)', '11!/(2! 2!)', '', 'C Explanation Number of letter in MATHEMATICS = 11 Number of letter M = 2 Number of letter T = 2 Number of letter A = 2  Arrangement = 11!/(2! 2! 2!) ways   ', 0, '2024-03-21 11:54:06'),
(973, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Given That The Various Faces Of A Fair Dice 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 Appeared 30, 43, 54, 40, 41, 32 Times Respectively In A Single Toss. Picture The Figures As Being Represented In A Simple Table With Number (X) Against Frequency (f).&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIf A Pie Chart Is Used To Depict The Data, The Angle Corresponding To 4 Is?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '10Â°', '16Â°', '40Â°', '60Â°', '', 'D Explanation Angle corresponding to 4 is 40/240 x 360/1 = 60Â°  Note that total angle in a circle is 360Â°. Note also that sum of the frequencies given is 240.', 0, '2024-03-21 11:55:18'),
(974, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If U = {x : X Is An Integer And 1&amp;nbsp;&amp;le;&amp;le;&amp;nbsp;x&amp;nbsp;&amp;le;&amp;le;&amp;nbsp;20&lt;br /&gt;\r\nE1&amp;nbsp;= {x : X Is A Multiple Of 3}&lt;br /&gt;\r\nE2&amp;nbsp;= {x : X Is A Multiple Of 4}&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAnd An Integer Is Picked At Random From U, Find The Probability That It Is Not In E2&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '3/4 ', '3/10', '1/4', '1/20', '', 'A Explanation U = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5,..., 20} E1 = {3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18} E2 = {4, 8, 12, 16, 20} P(E1) = 5/20 P(not E1) = 1 - (5/20) = 15/20 = 3/4', 0, '2024-03-21 11:57:11'),
(975, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;The Variance Of X, 2x, 3x, 4x And 5x Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â xâˆš2', '2x2 ', 'X2', '3x', '', 'B Explanation Hint: prepare a three-columned table, one for (x), another for the (deviation), and the last for the (squared-deviation).  Sum of (x) = 15x, algebraic sum of (deviation) = zero (0) Sum of (squared-deviation) = 10x2  Variance = âˆ‘(squared-de', 0, '2024-03-21 11:58:13'),
(976, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Sum Of The Range And The Mode Of The Set Of Numbers 10, 9, 10, 9, 8, 7, 7, 10, 8, 10, 8, 4, 6, 9, 10, 9, 10, 9, 7, 10, 6, 5&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '16', '14 ', '12 ', '10', '', 'A Explanation Range = Highest - lowest number =&gt; 10-4 = 6 Mode is the number with highest occurrence =&gt; Mode = 10  Sum = 6 + 10 = 16', 0, '2024-03-21 11:59:11'),
(977, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;In How Many Ways Can A Delegation Of 3 Be Chosen From Among 5 Men And 3 Women, If At Least One Man And At Least One Woman Must Be Included?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 15 ', '28 ', '30 ', '45', '', 'D Explanation No of ways of choosing 1 man, 2 women = 5C1 x 3C2 No of ways of choosing 2 men, 1 woman = 5C2 x 3C1 Summing, =&gt; (5C1 x 3C2) + (5C2 x 3C1) = 15 + 30 = 45', 0, '2024-03-21 12:00:00'),
(978, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Function F(x) Passes Through The Origin And Its First Derivative Is 3x + 2. What Is F(x)?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â y = (3x2/)2 + 2x ', 'Y = (3x2)/2 + X', 'Y = 3x2Â + (X/2) ', 'Y = 3x2Â +2x', '', 'A Explanation Hints: 1. Integrate the given first derivative of f(x) at the boundaries, (0,0)  Then solve accordingly to get f(x) = y = (3x2/)2 + 2x', 0, '2024-03-21 12:00:56'),
(979, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;The Expression Ax2&amp;nbsp;+ Bx + C Equals 5 At X = 1. If Its Derivative Is 2x + 1, What Are The Values Of A, B, C Respectively?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '1, 3, 1', '1, 2, 1', '2, 1, 1', '1, 1, 3', '', 'D Explanation At x = 1, substituting x = 1 in the equation: ax2 + bx + c = 5; f(1) =&gt; a + b + c = 5 .....(1)  Taking the first derivative of f(x) in the original equation gives dy/dx = 2ax + b = 2x + 1 (given)....(2)  From (2),=&gt; b = 1, and 2ax = 2x', 0, '2024-03-21 12:01:47'),
(980, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Evaluate 21.05347 - 1.6324 X 0.43 To 3 Decimal Places&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 20.980 ', '20.351 ', '20.981 ', '20.352', '', ' Explanation Hint: Use BODMAS, in other words, do multiplication of the second and the last first before subtracting value obtained from the first.', 0, '2024-03-21 12:02:52'),
(981, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Simplify&amp;nbsp;(64a3&amp;minus;&amp;minus;&amp;minus;&amp;minus;&amp;radic;3)&amp;minus;1(64ï¿½33)&amp;minus;1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n', 'Â 4a', 'Â 1/8a ', '8a ', '1/4a', '', 'D Explanation (64a3âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆš3)âˆ’1=((4a)3âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆš3)âˆ’1 = (4a)âˆ’1 = 14a', 0, '2024-03-21 12:05:22'),
(982, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Given That&amp;nbsp;p=1+2&amp;ndash;&amp;radic;ï¿½=1+2&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;q=1&amp;minus;2&amp;ndash;&amp;radic;ï¿½=1&amp;minus;2, Evaluate&amp;nbsp;p2&amp;minus;q22pqï¿½2&amp;minus;ï¿½22ï¿½ï¿½.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2(2+âˆš2)  ', '-2(2+âˆš2)', '2âˆš2', '-2âˆš2', '', 'D Explanation p2âˆ’q22pq=(p+q)(pâˆ’q)2pq = (1+2âˆšâˆ’(1âˆ’2âˆš))(1+2âˆš+1âˆ’2âˆš)2(1+2âˆš)(1âˆ’2âˆš) = (22âˆš)(2)âˆ’2 = âˆ’22â€“âˆš', 0, '2024-03-21 12:06:25'),
(983, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Car Dealer Bought A Second-hand Car For N250,000 And Spent N70,000 Refurbishing It. He Then Sold The Car For N400,000. What Is The Percentage Gain?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '60% ', '32%', '25% ', 'Â 20%', '', ' C Explanation Total cost = N(250,000 + 70,000) = N320,000 Selling price = N400,000 (given) Gain = SP - CP = N(400,000 - 320,000) = N80,000 Gain % = gain/CP x 100 = (80,000/320,000) x 100  Gain % = 25%', 0, '2024-03-21 12:07:48'),
(984, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If&amp;nbsp;x=y2ï¿½=ï¿½2,evaluate(x3y3+12)&amp;divide;(12&amp;minus;x2y2)(ï¿½3ï¿½3+12)&amp;divide;(12&amp;minus;ï¿½2ï¿½2)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '5/8', '5/2', '5/32', '5/16', '', ' B Explanation x=y2 (x3y3+12)Ã·(12âˆ’x2y2) x3y3+12=(y2)3Ã·y3+12 = y38Ã—1y3+12 = 18+12 = 58 12âˆ’x2y2=12âˆ’(y2)2Ã·y2) = 12âˆ’y24Ã—1y2 = 12âˆ’14 = 14 âˆ´(x3y3+12)Ã·(12âˆ’x2y2)=58Ã·14 = 52', 0, '2024-03-21 12:09:09'),
(985, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Principal Which Amounts To N5,500 At A Simple Interest In 5 Years At 2% Per Annum.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â N4,900 ', 'N5,000 ', 'N4,700', 'N4,800', '', 'B Explanation Principal, P = Amount, A - Interest, I. A = P + I  I = (P.T.R)/100 = (P x 5 x 2)/100 = 10P/100 = P/10  But A = P + I, =&gt; 5500 = P + (P/10) =&gt; 55000 = 10P + P =&gt; 55000 = 11P  Thus P = 55000/11 = N5,000', 0, '2024-03-21 12:10:07'),
(986, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Evaluate&amp;nbsp;(0.142&amp;times;0.275)7(0.02)(0.142&amp;times;0.275)7(0.02)&amp;nbsp;to 3 Decimal Places.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 0.039 ', '0.385 ', '0.033', '0.038', '', 'A Explanation (0.14)2Ã—0.2757(0.02)=(0.14)2Ã—0.2750.14 = 0.14Ã—0.275 = 0.0385â‰Š0.039 Note: Embedded zeroes are counted just the same as non-zero digits and For the number of decimal places stated, count that number of digits to the right of the decimal a', 0, '2024-03-21 12:11:10'),
(987, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Divide:&amp;nbsp;a3x&amp;minus;26a2x+156ax&amp;minus;216ï¿½3ï¿½&amp;minus;26ï¿½2ï¿½+156ï¿½ï¿½&amp;minus;216&amp;nbsp;by&amp;nbsp;a2x&amp;minus;24ax+108ï¿½2ï¿½&amp;minus;24ï¿½ï¿½+108.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'axÂ - 2', 'AxÂ + 2', 'AxÂ - 8', 'ax - 6', '', 'A Explanation a3xâˆ’26a2x+156axâˆ’216a2xâˆ’24ax+108 Let ax=z âˆ´=z3âˆ’26z2+156zâˆ’216z2âˆ’24y+108...(i) Dividing (i) above, we get zâˆ’2 = axâˆ’2', 0, '2024-03-21 12:12:27'),
(988, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Integral Values Of X And Y Satisfying The Inequality 3y + 5x&amp;nbsp;&amp;le;&amp;le;&amp;nbsp;15, Given That Y &amp;gt; 0, Y &amp;lt; 3 And X &amp;gt; 0.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â (1,1), (1,2), (1,3)  ', '(1,1), (2,1), (1,3)', '(1,1), (3,1), (2,2)', '(1,1), (1,2), (2,1)', '', 'D Explanation Hint: Sketch the inequality graph for the 3 conditions given and read out your points from the co-ordinates.', 0, '2024-03-21 12:17:14'),
(989, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Solve The Equations&lt;br /&gt;\r\nM2&amp;nbsp;+ N2&amp;nbsp;= 29&lt;br /&gt;\r\nM + N = 7&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '(2, 3) and ( 3, 5) ', 'Â (2, 5) And (5, 2) ', '(5, 2) And ( 5, 3)', 'Â (5, 3) And (3, 5)', '', 'B Explanation m2 + n2 = 29 .......(1) m + n = 7 ............(2)  From (2), m = 7 - n but m2 + n2 = 29, substituting; (7-n)2 + n2 = 29 49 - 14n + n2 + n2 = 29 =&gt; 2n2 -14n + 20 = 0 Thus n2 -7n + 10 = 0  Factorizing; (n-5)(n-2) = 0 n - 5 = 0, =&gt; n = 5 ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:19:05'),
(990, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;An Operation * Is Defined On The Set Of Real Numbers By A*b = A + B + 1. If The Identity Elements Is -1, Find The Inverse Of The Element 2 Under *.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4 ', 'Zero ', 'Â -2 ', 'Â -4', '', 'D Explanation By definition a*b = a + b + 1. Let the inverse of the element 2 be x,  Therefore 2*x = -1 i.e. 2 + x + 1 = -1 3 + x = -1 x = -1 - 3 x = -4', 0, '2024-03-21 12:21:14'),
(991, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;The Sixth Term Of An A.P Is Half Of Its Twelfth Term. The First Term Of The A.P Is Equal To&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'zero ', 'Half Of The Common Difference', 'Double The Common Difference', 'The Common Difference', '', 'D Explanation 1st statement: U6 = 1/2(U12) a + (n -1)d = 1/2[a + (n-1)d] a + 5d = a + 11d 2(a + 5d) = a + 11d 2a + 10d = a + 11d  Solving, =&gt; a = d Hence the first term is equal to the common difference', 0, '2024-03-21 12:22:29'),
(992, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Sector Of A Circle Of Radius 7.2cm Which Subtends An Angle Of 300&amp;deg; At The Centre Is Used To Form A Cone. What Is The Radius Of The Base Of The Cone?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '8cm ', '6cm ', '9cm ', '7cm', '', 'B Explanation (r/L) = (Î¸/360Â°) Given Î¸ = 300, and L = 7.2cm,  =&gt; r = (300 x 7.2)/360 r = 6cm', 0, '2024-03-21 12:25:08'),
(993, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Point P Moves Such That It Is Equidistant From Points Q And R. Find QR When PR = 8cm And Angle PRQ = 30&amp;deg;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4âˆš3cm', '8cm ', '8âˆš3cm', '4cm', '', 'C Explanation Hint: Make a sketch of an isosceles triangle with two of its sides and angles angles.  : PQ (r)  = PR (q) = 8cm  : RÂ° = QÂ° = 30Â°  Sum of angles in a triangle = 180Â°  PÂ° + QÂ° + RÂ° = 180Â°  PÂ° + 30Â° + 30Â° = 180Â°  PÂ° = 180Â° - 60Â° ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:26:03'),
(994, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Straight Line Makes An Angle Of 30&amp;deg; With The Positive X-axis And Cuts The Y-axis At Y = 5. Find The Equation Of The Straight Line.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'y = (x/10) + 5  ', 'Y = X + 5 ', 'âˆš3y = - X + 5âˆš3', 'âˆš3y = X + 5âˆš3', '', ' D Explanation Cos 30 = 5/x x cos 30 = 5, =&gt; x = 5âˆš3  Coordinates of P = -5, 3, 0 Coordinates of Q = 0, 5 Gradient of PQ = (y2 - y1) (X2 - X1) = (5 - 0)/(0 -5âˆš3) = 5/5âˆš3 = 1/âˆš3  Equation of PQ = y - y1 = m (x -x1) y - 0 = 1/âˆš3 (x -(-5âˆš3))  ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:27:10'),
(995, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Given An Isosceles Triangle With Length Of 2 Equal Sides&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;t&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;units And Opposite Side&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;radic;3t&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;units With Angle &amp;theta;. Find The Value Of The Angle &amp;theta; Opposite To The&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;radic;3t&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;units.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '100Â°  ', '120Â°', '30Â°', '60Â°', '', 'B Explanation Cos Î¸Â° = t2 + t2 -(âˆš3t)2 2 x t x t  = 2t2 - 3t2 2t2 = -t2/2t2 = -1/2  Thus Î¸ = cos-1 (-0.5) = 120Â°', 0, '2024-03-21 12:28:04'),
(996, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Value Of P If The Line Joining (P, 4) And (6, -2) Is Perpendicular To The Line Joining (2, P) And (-1, 3).&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4  ', '6', 'Â 3', '0.0', '', 'A Explanation The line joining (P, 4) and (6, -2).  Gradient: âˆ’2âˆ’46âˆ’P=âˆ’66âˆ’P The line joining (2, P) and (-1, 3)  Gradient: 3âˆ’Pâˆ’1âˆ’2=3âˆ’Pâˆ’3 For perpendicular lines, the product of their gradient = -1.  (âˆ’66âˆ’P)(3âˆ’Pâˆ’3)=âˆ’1 6âˆ’2P6â', 0, '2024-03-21 12:29:27'),
(997, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;P(-6, 1) And Q(6, 6) Are The Two Ends Of The Diameter Of A Given Circle. Calculate The Radius.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '6.5 units ', '13.0 Units', '3.5 Units', '7.0 Units', '', 'A Explanation PQ2  = (x2 - x1)2   + (y2 - y1)2    = 122   + 52   = 144 + 25 = 169  PQ = âˆš169 = 13  But PQ = diameter = 2r, r = PQ/2 = 6.5 units', 0, '2024-03-21 12:32:20'),
(998, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;The Bearings Of P And Q From A Common Point N Are 020&amp;deg; And 300&amp;deg; Respectively. If P And Q Are Also Equidistant From N, Find The Bearing Of P From Q.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '040Â°  ', '070Â°', '280Â°', '320Â°', '', 'B Explanation Hint: Simply make a sketch of the question and find the bearing to be 070Â°', 0, '2024-03-21 12:34:00'),
(999, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;A Cylindrical Tank Has A Capacity Of 3080 M3. What Is The Depth Of The Tank If The Diameter Of Its Base Is 14 M?&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\n(Take Pi = 22/7)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '23 m ', '25 M', '20 M', 'Â 22 M', '', 'C Explanation Capacity = 3080 m3 Base diameter = 14 m, thus radius = 7 m.  Volume of cylinder = capacity of cylinder = Ï€r2h. = 3080 22/7 x 72 x h = 3080 h = 3080/(22x7) h = 20 m  ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:35:33'),
(1000, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Locus Of A Point Which Moves Such That Its Distance From The Line Y = 4 Is A Constant, K.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'y = 4Â Â±Â±Â k', 'Y = KÂ Â±Â±Â 4', 'Y = 4 + K ', 'Â Y = K - 4', '', 'A', 0, '2024-03-21 12:36:51'),
(1001, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;The Chord ST Of A Circle Is Equal To The Radius, R, Of The Circle. Find The Length Of Arc ST.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Ï€r/6 ', 'Î r/2', 'Î r/12 ', 'Î r/3', '', 'D Explanation Since ST = the radius r, =&gt; SOT is equilateral. Each angle = 60Â° Length of arc ST = Î¸/360 x 2Ï€r = 60/360 x 2 x Ï€ x r = Ï€r/3', 0, '2024-03-21 12:38:50'),
(1002, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If The Gradient Of The Curve Y = 2kx2&amp;nbsp;+ X + 1 At X = 1 Is 9, Find K.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4', '3', '2', '1', '', 'C Explanation y = 2kx2 + x + 1 Gradient function dy/dx = 4kx + 1 at dy/dx = 9, =&gt; 9 = 4kx + 1 =&gt; 8 = 4kx, and k = 8/4x.  At x = 1, k = 8/4 = 2', 0, '2024-03-21 12:39:57'),
(1003, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Evaluate&amp;nbsp;&amp;int;2(2x&amp;minus;3)23dx&amp;int;2(2ï¿½&amp;minus;3)23dï¿½&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '3/5(2x-3)5/3Â + k ', '6/5(2x-3)5/3', '2x-3+k', '2(2x-3)+K', '', ' A Explanation âˆ«2(2xâˆ’3)23dx Let u=2xâˆ’3 du=2dx = âˆ«u23du = u5353+k = 35(2xâˆ’3)53+k  ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:41:05'),
(1004, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Differentiate&amp;nbsp;(2x+5)2(x&amp;minus;4)(2ï¿½+5)2(ï¿½&amp;minus;4)&amp;nbsp;with Respect To X.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '4(2x+5)(x-4) ', '4(2x+5)(4x-3) ', '(2x+5)(2x-13)', '(2x+5)(6x-11)', '', 'D Explanation y=(2x+5)2(xâˆ’4) dydx=(2x+5)2(1)+(xâˆ’4)(2)(2)(2x+5) = (2x+5)(2x+5+4xâˆ’16) = (2x+5)(6xâˆ’11)', 0, '2024-03-21 12:41:57'),
(1005, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Area Bounded By The Curves Y = 4 - X2 And Y = 2x + 1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '20(1/3) sq. units ', '20(2/3) Sq. Units', '10(2/3) Sq. Units ', '10(1/3) Sq. Units', '', 'C Explanation Hint: y = 4 - x2  and y = 2x + 1 =&gt; 4 - x2 = 2x + 1 =&gt; x2 + 2x - 3 = 0 (x+3)(x-1) = 0 thus x = 1 or x = -3.  Integrating x2  + 2x - 3    = 3x - x2  - x33     from (1, to -3) : 3 (1) - 12  - 133    -    3 (-3)  -  -32  - âˆ’333    = 53 ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:43:01'),
(1006, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Rate Of Change Of The Volume, V Of A Sphere With Respect To Its Radius, R When R = 1.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '12Ï€  ', '4Ï€ ', '24Ï€ ', '8Ï€', '', 'B Explanation Volume of sphere, V = 4/3 x Ï€r3 Rate of change of V = dv/dr Thus if V = 4/3 x Ï€r3, =&gt; dv/dr = 4Ï€r2  At r = 1, Rate = 4 x Ï€ x 1 = 4Ï€', 0, '2024-03-21 12:44:15'),
(1007, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If Y = X Sinx, Find Dy/dx When X = &amp;pi;/2.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '-Ï€/2', '-1', '1 ', 'Â Î /2', '', ' C Explanation y = x sin x dy/dx = 1 x sinx + x cosx = sinx + x cosx At x = Ï€/2, = sin (Ï€/2) + (Ï€/2) cos (Ï€/2) = 1 + (Ï€/2) x (0) = 1', 0, '2024-03-21 12:45:08'),
(1008, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Find The Dimensions Of A Rectangle Of Greatest Area Which Has A Fixed Perimeter P.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'square of sides p', 'Square Of Sides 2p ', 'Square Of Sides (P/2)', 'Square Of Sides (P/4)', '', 'D Explanation Let the rectangle be a square of sides p/4.  So that perimeter of square = 4p 4 x (p/4) = p.', 0, '2024-03-21 12:46:13'),
(1009, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Given The Scores: 4, 7, 8, 11, 13, 8 With Corresponding Frequencies: 3, 5, 2, 7, 2, 1 Respectively. The Mean Score Is&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '7.0 ', '8.7 ', '9.5', '11.0', '', 'B Explanation Mean = âˆ‘fx/âˆ‘f Mean = (4x3) + (7x5) + ... + (8x1) all divided by 20 Mean = 174/20 = 8.7  ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:49:10'),
(1010, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Teams P And Q Are Involved In A Game Of Football. What Is The Probability That The Game Ends In A Draw?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2/3 ', '1/2', '1/3 ', '1/4', '', 'D Explanation P (games end in draw) =&gt; Team P wins and Q wins P(P wins) = 1/2 P(Q wins) = 1/2 Therefore P (games ends in draw) = 1/2 x 1/2 = 1/4', 0, '2024-03-21 12:50:14'),
(1011, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If&amp;nbsp;6Pr&amp;nbsp;= 6, Find The Value Of&amp;nbsp;6Pr+1&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '30 ', '33 ', '35 ', '15', '', 'A Explanation 6Pr = 6 Thus r = 1  N.B 6P1 = 6!(6 - 1)!   = 6!5!   = 6Ã—5!5!  = 6  6Pr + 1 = 6P2 = 6!(6âˆ’2)!=6!4!   = 6Ã—5Ã—4!4!   = 30', 0, '2024-03-21 12:51:04'),
(1012, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Without Using Tables, Evaluate&amp;nbsp;(343)13&amp;times;(0.14)&amp;minus;1&amp;times;(25)&amp;minus;12(343)13&amp;times;(0.14)&amp;minus;1&amp;times;(25)&amp;minus;12&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '10 ', '12 ', '8', '7', '', 'A Explanation (343)13Ã—(0.14)âˆ’1Ã—(25)âˆ’12 = 343âˆ’âˆ’âˆ’âˆš3Ã—(14100)âˆ’1Ã—(25âˆ’âˆ’âˆš)âˆ’1 = 7Ã—10014Ã—15 = 10.', 0, '2024-03-21 12:51:50'),
(1013, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;In A School, 220 Students Offer Biology Or Mathematics Or Both. 125 Offer Biology And 110 Mathematics. How Many Offer Biology But Not Mathematics?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '95 ', '80 ', '125', '110', '', 'D Explanation Hint: Represent the question in a venn diagram, such that n(B âˆ© M) = x n(B) only = 125-x n(M) only = 110-x =&gt; 125-x + 110-x + x = 220 =&gt; x = 15.  n(B) only = 125 - 15 = 110  ', 0, '2024-03-21 12:52:49'),
(1014, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Simplify 52.4 - 5.7 - 3.45 - 1.75&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â 41.4 ', '41.5 ', '42.1', 'Â 42.2', '', 'B Explanation 52.4 - 5.7 - 3.45 - 1.75  = 52.4 - (5.7 + 3.45 + 1.75)  = 52.4 - 10.90  = 41.5', 0, '2024-03-21 12:53:40'),
