(1018, 17, 'JAMB', 'MATHEMATIC', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;If Dy/dx = 2x - 3 And Y = 3 When X = 0, Find Y In Terms Of X.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', '2x2Â - 3x  ', 'X2Â - 3x ', 'X2Â - 3x - 3', 'X2Â - 3x + 3', '', 'D Explanation dy/dx = 2x - 3 y = âˆ«2x - 3 dx =&gt; y = x2 - 3x + c 3 = (0)2 - 3(0) + c =&gt; c = 3  Thus y = x2 - 3x + 3', 0, '2024-03-21 12:57:02'),
