(1046, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;In Being Unfaithful To Her Husband, _____ Represented Israel Whilst Being Unfaithful To God&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Rahab ', 'Jezebel', 'Gomer', 'Rebecca', '', ' C Explanation The prophet Hosea uses his adulterous wife Gomer as a metaphor for God as the faithful husband to Israel.', 0, '2024-04-11 19:08:56'),
(1047, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;And The King (Artaxerxes) Said To Me, &amp;#39;&amp;#39;why Is Your Face Sad, Seeing You Are Not Sick? This Is Nothing Else But Sadness Of The Heart&amp;#39;&amp;#39;. Who Was The King Addressing&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Jeremiah  ', 'Nehemiah', 'Amos', 'Joel', '', 'B Explanation The king was addressing Nehemiah when he was sent to Jerusalem.', 0, '2024-04-11 19:10:24'),
(1048, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;According To Mark, What Was The Only Thing The Disciples Wasn&amp;#39;t Forbidden To Take For Their Journey?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Bread ', 'Bag', 'Staff', 'Money', '', 'C Explanation These were his instructions: &quot;Take nothing for the journey except a staffâ€”no bread, no bag, no money in your belts. (Mark 6:8-9)', 0, '2024-04-11 19:12:10'),
