(1052, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;The Secon Temptation According To The Gospel Of Luke Was&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'worship Satan to receive great power.', 'To Leap From The Temple Pinnacle To Show His Divine Nature. ', 'To Turn Stones Into Bread To Satisfy His Physical Hunger. ', 'To Invoke God&apos;s Presence', '', ' A Explanation The temptations of Christ are identical in the two accounts, but Matthew records them as:  1. Turn stones into bread to satisfy his physical hunger. 2. Leap from the temple pinnacle to show his divine nature. 3. Worship Satan to receive gre', 0, '2024-04-11 19:18:08'),
(1053, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Hophni And Phinehas Were The Sons Of&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Samuel  ', 'Eli', 'Jeroboam', 'Asa', '', 'B Explanation They were the two sons of Eli. The first book of Samuel describes them as the officiating priests at the sanctuary of Shiloh at the time of Hannah.', 0, '2024-04-11 19:19:30'),
(1054, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;At The Transfiguration Of Jesus, Moses And Elijah Appeared To Represent The ______ And ______.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Israelites and their leaders ', 'Law And The Prophets', 'The Book And The Gods', 'None Of The Above', '', 'B Explanation Matthew 17:2 states that Jesus &quot;was transfigured before them; his face shining as the sun, and his garments became white as the light.&quot; At that point the prophet Elijah representing the prophets and Moses representing the Law appea', 0, '2024-04-11 19:21:06'),
(1055, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Under King _______, Daniel Was Thrown Into The Lion&amp;#39;s Den.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Nebuchadnezzar', 'Asa ', 'Darius', 'Ahab', '', ' C Explanation Upon the advice of these men, King Darius had rashly issued a decree forbidding anyone from making petitions to &quot;any god or man for thirty days&quot; (Daniel 6:6-9)', 0, '2024-04-11 19:23:17'),
(1056, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;#39;Hear Now, You Rebels&amp;#39; Shall We Bring Forth Water For You Out Of This Rock? This Statement Was Made By _____ To The Israelites.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Abram', 'Joshua', 'Caleb', 'Moses', '', 'D Explanation In the first month, the whole congregation of Israel entered the Wilderness of Zin and stayed in Kadesh. There Miriam died and was buried. Now there was no water for the congregation, so they gathered against Moses and Aaron. The people quar', 0, '2024-04-11 19:24:42'),
