(1064, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Forty More Days And Nineveh Will Be Overturned.&amp;quot; When Jonah Passed This Message To The People Of Nineveh, What Did They Do?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'They turned deaf ears. ', 'They Declared A Feast', 'They Declared A Fast And Put On Sack Clothes', 'They Threw Jonah Into The River', '', 'C Explanation On the first day, Jonah started into the city. He proclaimed: &quot;Forty more days and Nineveh will be overturned.&quot; The Ninevites believed God. They declared a fast, and all of them, from the greatest to the least, put on sackcloth. (J', 0, '2024-04-11 19:38:53'),
