(1086, 17, 'JAMB', 'CHRISTIAN RELIGIOUS STUDIES(CRK)', '2022', '&lt;p&gt;Naboth Refused To Give Up His Vineyard To King Ahab Because&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'Â it was expensive  ', 'Ahab Was A Terrible King', 'It Was His Family&apos;s Inheritance ', 'Â It Was His Only Source Of Income', '', 'C Explanation 1 Kings 21:1-16 states that Naboth owned a vineyard, in proximity to King Ahab&apos;s palace in the city of Jezreel. Because of this, Ahab desired to acquire the vineyard so that he could use it for a vegetable (or herb) garden. Since he inh', 0, '2024-04-11 21:49:58'),
